Item_Response: New learner Circus Clowns        Once Upon A Circus, there was a clown. His name was Freddy. He needed to hire somebody cause his boss said that he needed another clown to intertain the kids on Saturday for the big Circus play. If he did hire somebody, all of the other clowns would have to teach the clown to do tricks and everything. That might take a while, so Freddy thought he needed to hire one almost right away.            So, Freddy took a walk down to the park. He took a glance at the park from around the corner. He didn't see anybody from around the corner, but he needed glasses because he had bad eyesight. So he walked farther, until he finally got there. Freddy saw two 2 year-olds, two 5 year-olds, three 13 year-olds, and 1, just one, 18 year-old. The perfect age to become a circus clown. Freddy thought. Even more perfect that there's only one. Fred let out some humour. (if you couldn't notice, sometimes Fred had a bad sense of humour. Fred is short for Freddy so you don't have to say FREDDY. As the other circus clowns said.)   'Hi, what's your name?' Fred went up to the girl that was 18.   'Hi, my name is Meg, do I know you?' The girl replied.   'No, I don't think so, but I was going to ask you something.'   'What was that sir?' Meg said.   'I was wondering if you would like to come work for me at the circus?'   'I would have to know what time and what days it would be on.'   'It would be the whole week. Some days you would be working for long hours but other days short hours.' Fred inquired.   'Yeah, I would be okay with that,' Meg said happily.   'Awesome! The one thing I would have to know from you is what your talent is, if that's okay with you.' Fred announced.   ' Oh, sure. My talent is that I LOVE gymnastics, and I go to practice in Iowa Falls. Crowds of people come to watch me do my fancy trick called THE SPIN. One time Taylor Swift came and watched me. It was the best day of my life!' Meg was excited talking about that.   'Sounds fun, do you want to go home and talk to your parents about it real fast?' Fred said.   'Yeah, be right back.' Meg replied.   'Okay,' Fred responded.            As soon as she got back, she said her parents said yes. Freddy was happy. Then they got to right back to the circus and practice.            Meg was so good at gymnastics that she mastered the new moves she had to learn in no time. Circus clowns were so proud of her and she did great at the big play!                 And all of the circus clowns lived happily ever after!!!!!

Item_Response: It's not easy living the life of a circus performer. You have to have lots of skill and talent to live in a circus. Even if your a kid you still go to bed about at twelve o'clock a.m. You have to give up absaloutly everything to become a circus preformer. We interviewed nine year old Loki about how she liked the circus life.        'It's fun but not the easiest job. And you might think you get to skip school because you joined the circus, but you still have to read, write, and do math in a one classroom trailer that comes with us where ever we go. I started doing gymnastics when I was five years old so I am rather good at being a trapize artist. My trick to not being scared even though i'm so high up is to just look at my mom on the other side. My whole family is in the circus but we do not all do the same thing. My brother, Tio, is an assintant clown. He gets to ride unicycles. My dad is the lion tamer. At dinner time we dont get to get to much because we are performing in a little while. We do ten shows a week so when the show is over I am very tired. The show goes to ten thirty p.m. and I go to bed at 12:00 a.m. In a couple of days we head to a different town. You may think it's exciting going from place to place but sometimes I wish that we could just settle in one spot that I can call home.'             As you can see it is not an easy life. You have to do many things to become a circus performer. With the crowd going wild and clapping their hands, you think it would be wonderfull, but ask yourself, do you think that you would want to swich lives with a circus performer?

Item_Response: WHAT WE DO AT THE CIRCUS                             I am Jordyn I work at the circus my friends names at my work are Mary,Miranda,Amanda,and Alex we are all professional acrobats. We were in gymnastic for eleven years before we started here.  My friends and I love showing off our talents thats why we work here. We've been working here at the circus for seven years i am tired  after a day of work. You have to wake up early got to bed late and go on long trips all the time but we are are used to that but its very fun though.                    Today we are going to japan for a show we have to take some of our animals because they are needed in the show we will be doing acrobats fire dancing and a cupple acts with the animals. Mary,Amanda,Alex,and I will be preforming acrobats and jack another person that works with me will be preforming the fire dance.We are going to have a fun time. When we come back we will be preforming another show at our home town. We are going to preform most of the same things as Japan but not exactly we will not be preforming with the same animals as the show in Japan but we will be preforming with animals and we will  also be doing acrobats and fire dancing with every one that did it before.                             Everything is done and I am really really tired so I am going to clean up my things and head out of the circus and home but I want to say bye to every body first. 'bye everyone' I said, 'see you later' Mary,Amanda, Alex,and Jack said. 'See you tommorrow'I said , ' bye ' Amanda said. I am home now and I am getting ready for work tomorrow. I love working at the circus and I hope kids become like me but I am really tired and I need to go to bed. Goodbye.

Item_Response: Life in a Circus   By: Diego        April 11, 2013                    Things that happen in a circus is crazy like when people perform on tight ropes they have to walk on the rope trying not to fall of the rope. If they fall then everyone will laugh at the person who is doing that trick so that is just one thing and there are more tricks that are harder than that so it is hard. When people perform it is hard because they have to practice lots of times so they don't fail that is why when they do tricks they practice lots of times so they don't fail so practice makes perfect.                     My first reason that you should practice is that when you are on a balance beam you don't fall and get caught in the net when they fall off they get laughed at when they fall. Also when you fall off you might get injured when you mess up or maybe the net is to long and you still hit the ground a little hard. Some people that are on the balance beam they are sometimes blind and have a large stick that is about 10 or 15 or 20 feet long. They have to carry that all the way across the rope blinded. One person did that and fell on the rope which made him sit down on the rope and again he fell off this time. That is why you need to practice all the time so you can master it.                      My second reason is that when elephants go on bouncy balls they have to train them to stand on the balls and they train them to hold each other so they don't fall. They have to keep them skinny so that when they get on the balls the ball doesn't pop right when they are in the middle of doing their trick. The balls that they use to put the elephant on are strong so that when they get on the ball won't pop. The elephants hold on to each other because the elephants can't hold their balance they don't fall on their back or slip to their side. That is another reason why you should practice all the time.                      My Third reason why you should practice is that when clowns fold and twist balloons they have to practice folding and twisting the balloon. When people become clowns they practice before they go out and give kids balloon animals he has to know how to make them and how to do it without popping the balloon in the kids face. When clowns do tricks like the flower that shoots out water when you try to smell it they have to know where he should shoot it. If he shoots it anywhere then he might get the person in the eye. That is another reason why you should practice before you so your act on stage.                                                                                                                                                            Those are reasons why when you go to a circus and sign up for it then you have to practice all the time so that you won't fall or get hurt. Practicing make perfect because if you try to be a juggler them you have to learn how to juggle about five which should be a maximum amount of rings to juggle. So if you mess up them some people will laugh about how you failed or boo at you. That is why you should practice all the time when you try to join a circus.

Item_Response: I slowly open my eyes I know where I am, I panic then remember I joined the circus! I jump out of bed and throw on my clothes.       I run to the Pie Car for breakfast. They are serving Pancakes and Bacon. After breakfast I run to the ringmaster for instruction, He tells me I need to feed the animals then practice shooting out of a cannon!   After feeding the animals I slowly shuffled over to the cannon, I was to afraid to get in it.       I walk back to the bedrooms lay down to read a book before I knew it I dozed off, I awaked to the ring masters voice 'Show starts in 5 minutes!' I jumped up and ran to my position. The crowd ran in voices filled the room. The ring master did a flip and landed on the elephant he yelled 'Are you ready?!?!' The crowed roared back 'YES!' Clowns came petaling in and started there act lions roared horns beeped, When it was finally my act I realized I had never practiced for the cannon.       I stared at the huge cannon in fear I approched it and the clowns picked me up without notice and stuffed me in the cannon, The ring master fired and I went flying out of the circus tent screaming. Then I woke up from my dream.

Item_Response: In the Circus                                By Kallen Miller             Hi, I'm Anthony Kastellor. I live with a circus group called Magic Wonders Circus. I live all over the world, because we never stay in one place for long. I've been to all the continents, including Australia, my favorite one. I travel every week for 7 months and 14 days. I work from 5:00am to 11:00pm.                Here is a normal day at Magic Wonders Circus:            5:00am I wake, get dressed in uniform and head to pie car for breakfast. The crew at this time is setting up tents, lights, and music for todays show. I have time before school, so I normally go to see Giggles and Bunny-Hunn the clown. They let me play around with their bowling pins and trinkets. We usually, to get excersize, play tag.             8:00am I go to school with the other boys and girls. we learn everything that normal kids learn and how to do some circus acts. Many of us speak English, but all of us now every language there is. It helps us with our travels.              2:30pm School is over. Now we get a 30 minute break. I play with my friends, Ayessha and Herbert. We usually play games with the clowns for awhile. Then we just play our own.              3:00pm practicing and dishes. My daily activities. I am an acrobat. I practice on a trampoline and do tricks on horses. One time my mother fell off one and onto a trampoline. She was not hurt.             6:30pm It is now dinnertime. We don't eat alot before a show. We do 14 shows each week. 2 on each day.              10:30pm The show is over. I am sooooo pooped out! Usually we dont do very long shows. oh well.              11:00pm Good night.

Item_Response: Life at the Circus                               I nevously peaked behind the big, red, velvet curtains and listend the spectators cheering, hungry for action, as the ring master had a smart dog jump into a orange hoop. Worried that someone would see my face, (which was covered with bright makeup) looking at them, I quickly ducked back be hind the curtain. As soon as the audience gave one last cheer, I knew that I would have to go on. 'don't be scared, don't be scared, don't be sacared,' I told myself.                    I am Kathrine, and I spend my life at the circus. I work as a acrobat. Every week we have to preform. Every day, we have to practice. I had known I wanted to be in the circus when I was only about four years old. My family and I were at our very first circus together. A clown with a bright smile came up to me and handed me a polka dot flower. I smiled big too and laughed so hard. Then I saw the acrobats. I begged my parents to take gymnastics class. When they had heard enough of my whining and complaints, they finally let me.                    That is how I became an acrobat. I worked very hard, in fact a little too hard. I guess my legs were too straight, or my toes were too pointed, or I was too shakey. It was tough, but when I FINALLY got everything right, my toes were perfectly pointed, my legs were perfectly straight, and I was perfectly still, I was so proud. I congragulated myself and was hoping that that would be my start as a professinal acrobat.                     That was my start as a professional acrobat. Because of that now I am on posters and huge billboards with me spinning on thin ropes wearing sparkly and colorful costumes. And like I told you before, my face had bright makeup all over. 'Thats me!' I think every time we go past one. I fell in love with all this circus buisiness. Everytime it is my turn to be on stage, though I am nervous, I try my very best, and it is absolutly worth it. When I am backstage I always say to my self, 'What am I doing?!' But after, I always say, 'That's so fun, I want to go again!'                     As I carefully and gently walked on to stage, with the bright lights shining on my face, I wasn't scared anymore because I because I believed that I could really do it as long as I try my very best. Trying my very best is hard, but once again it is absolutly woth it. Being in the circus can be tough, but it is also very enjoyable. This is what life is like  at the circus.

Item_Response: Hi my name is Alanya.  I work in a circus.  Let me tell you its not an easy task to do.  Well I love to preform and practice gymnastics to help me with my acrobatic performance in the circus.  I wake up on my tour bus at 6:00 and get ready for my day and school.  The most exciting part of my day is see all my friends and all the people at the circus watching me preform.       When it is time to preform I sometimes get scared by look out and seeing all the people just waiting for me to preform.  The my fellow people in the circus give wisdom and im ready to preform.  I do the acrobatic preforming section of the circus.       When im done everyone cheers me on and the little tiger cub comes to me and gives me a huge hug.  By then it is about midnight and I take a shower and take all of the circus make-up.  Then im ready for my next day at the circus.        I wish i could see my family and friends more, but i love prefoming and like my family always says, 'Go put yourself out there and make some huge memories!'

Item_Response: My Circus Story           Hi my name is Patricia, and i would like to discribe what happenes in the cirus. So, you have to make sure you train hard and are determined. you have to make sure that you have the right body. the good thing is we travel all over the place.we travel 20,000 miles in 7 months each year, visiting 150 cities. A typical day for me. i wake up and get dressed, and go to the pie car for bacon and pancakes. every one is getting ready for the show tonight. we have a 1 room school house that travele with us. just like any other school we have report cards, tests, and computers.                                                  Dinner time       My family and i go to the pie car to eat but we cant eat to much becauser we are performing tonight.                                                     The Shows Over                  I am wipedout. walking back to the trailer, we pass concession stands, stables, and trailers. 2 days from now we will set up another town!!

Item_Response: Hello my name is Zack and I'm going to tell you about life in the circus.  It's more harder than you think.  When you first wake up you have to eat breakfast quick because you have to get ready for the morning show.  After you eat breakfast you have to practice for your act.  My act is training lions to jump through hoops.  Hopefully it's not your turn to pick up after the elephant.  After you practice it's time for lunch. all you get is some cheese burgers and fries.                                               Show Time        Before the show the ring master will let everyone know the acts that will be happening.  Once your on your on.  first everyone goes on at once and it's a big fiasco.  You have to make sure you don't bump into anyone or they'll be very mad.  You wait anxiously until it's your turn.  First the trapeze artist are up, then the acrobats, and finally it's your turn. it's hard being a lion tamer, especially when people are watching.                                                  After The Show            After the circus is over you have to clean up.  During the clean up time you literally have to clean up everything.  After you're done cleaning up it's dinner time. you get a big dinner.                                               The Fun Times                   When you're not working you're having fun. You may think the clowns are the most fun you're wrong.  The most fun is the trainers with their animals.  It's fun riding on the unicycles when the clowns aren't around throwing water balloons at you.  The most fun though is climbing the trapeze wire.  I also like swinging on the trapeze swing.                                               Conclusion                As you can see the circus is not all fun and games.  As you have learned  it's mostly work not play I hope you know this before you join the circus.  Even though I have fun some times  it's not allways fun.

Item_Response: One day there was a mouse named Speckle. He had a big family, he had an uncle,an aunt, a sister, a friend,and of course his mom. Speckle's mom would always tell Speckle and Sam (his sister) not to come out of the mouse hole they lived in.The house they lived in was in a apartment with a women and his children. the women of course was the mom and was known as a scientist, Sam and Speckle were very curious and wanted to out to see the world, or apartment 31.              The very next morning Speckle woke up from a shower going on from a human, he remembered that he was going to sneak off in the apartment, and insisted for his sister Sam to go with him and Sam really wanted to go to and so they were off. Once Speckle took his first step out he spun around in joy and called his sister to come join him. then Speckle thought the kids room was full of toys to play with 'Sam!' he shouted 'lets look in the kids room'. Back at the old mouse house Speckle's mom woke up and she cooked because she thought they were there. soon she was searching for the kids but they weren't there.              Her panicking woke uncle and aunt mouse and tried to calm her down. Sam and Speckle had a wide grin on their faces because of all the toys. they started playing and had a joyful time.Then they heard stomping and they didn't know what to do so they ran and ran back home but then there was a big push of air and a broom was coming at them. it suddenly hit Sam. Speckle was panicking 'SAM!!' he rushed were the human couldn't see them and saw that Sam had a broken leg. he grabbed her and put her on his back and carried her back safely to the mouse hole.  the human was turning all around in confusion, she didn't know were they went. Speckle was relieved that they were okay, but mom was angry she told them not to go outside and they disobeyed. she was bursting with fury and put them both in time-out. Also Sam was hiding her leg so her mom wouldn't get more furious.                         Early in the morning Sam had woken Uncle mouse up because her leg was full of pain and was hurting real worse then yesterday.Uncle mouse got a string of material that was made out of cotton and got a cream to sooth her pain. he put the cream om and wrapped her leg very slowly and he called Speckle to get two sticks to hold her up when she stands. after that the mouse family had lived happily together for the rest of their lives.

Item_Response: Life in a circus is not as easy as you think.   Not just acrobats, clowns in small cars, and tightropes , it's even more. You work from sunup to sundown, and have nowhere to call home. You need to have balance, concentrate, and have a specific Skill.       You also need the right body. It also takes a lot of practice too! And see the audience get   so exited and happy about what they see.   See how thrilled the audience is!   Maybe life in a circus isb't that bad afterall.

One of her tricks is dancing we give her a treat if she does it right.If she ever gets mad or fierce we have to take her back to her cage out back and bring in Sharp, Sharp is Cuties brother he behaves a lot better than Cutie. Cutie is just competitive she always has to be better than everyone else. Sharp just wants to have fun he loves doing tricks but he can't do the ring of fire because got burnt before on the leg and he is just to scared to do it. At the end of their act they will both get a treat. Their treat is kind of gross though because it is a raw bird that you have to lay out in their cage for them.                 After the elephants and dancers are done I get to go out and do my trapeze tricks. I have a partner named Lewie. When it is time for our act we have to climb this 153 foot tall ladder that goes to the top. When we get up there we have to wait for Jimmy the announcer to announce us. When I get up there I just think happy thoughts, because if you don't you might not make it. It happened to me on my first show I got up there and just froze. All I was thinking about was massing up or falling or missing a flip. Since I didn't think happy thoughts I messed up so that's why I think happy thought from now on. Jimmy just announced us first I jump off the podium and flip to the first bar when I get it swinging I do a triple flip to the second bar. Now it's time for Lewie to come in. He glides to the first bar and then I flip to the third bar and he goes to the second one. Then I flip back to the second bar where Lewie is we but I dive for the net under us but we lock legs before I touch the net. Then the bar starts to swing a lot and that's when I flip back to the first bar. And that's when we both let go and fall on the mat.                    After the show when everyone leaves I got to my trailer and go to bed.

Item_Response: Hello i'm Carla S Jean, and i am a circus performer in the 'Georgia world circus'.And in that cicus i am a clown.When most people hear the word clowns, the think of paint,makeup,balloons,red noses, and all of that.But what people don't know is that clowns really aren't scarry.Why would anyone be scared of us? We make cute balloon animals, honk our big red noses,dress up in colorful costumes,and talk in a weird voice.IT'S THE BEST JOB EVER!We get to travel the world entertaining every summer.We go to China,Brazil,France,Jamaica,Mexico,Canada, and so many more!         We have over 1,000 performers!We have elephants, monkeys, birds, and a whole lot more.My father is a knife thrower.Which means he gets to throw knifes every night in the summer at inocent people.(Well actually just one person, we call him Sojo) Everyone in our circus is really nice.Well... all except for stephan.        My typical circus day is...       rise at 6:30 AM, get dressed, then have breakfast which my dad get's up super early to make for me.Then I go rehearse with half of our circus for that nights show.We only rehearse with half because we don't need all of the circus in one tent.After that we have lunch.Lunch is always curly's decision.(He won't ket us decide).It's usually fried chicken or something like that.We have 2 hours of free time right after lunch.I'm 14 years old so I can walk around and don't need to ask.That's what i do for those 2 hours.After that i have my tutor teach me my math,scisnce,social studies,and literature.Finally we have dinner at 6:00 PM.That's always a suprise.I have a curfew of 9:00.Our show is always at 7:00 to 9:00.That is my day.        My life is the best life anyone could ever wish for!

Item_Response: I Joined a Circus                                                         Day 1           Once upon a time there was a girl named Isabella. Isabella was a smart and nice girl that rarely even got a B so she had a lot of time on her hands when she wasn't studying. Her friends always called her izzy. One day izzy woke up and said she wanted to do something exiting with her life so she got up and went to school.                                                          6 Hours Later            Ring! Ring! 'ok students this is our last day before summer break and your report cards are in your daily envelope.' Says mrs. Goldilocks izzy's teacher. Izzy rushed home and looked at her daily envelope. Yes she got all A+'s but that didn't suprise her but what did suprise her was a bright blue paper that said ' Are you bored sitting at home at reading these papers? Are you 10 or older?' Well izzy was bored and she was 12. so she kept reading the paper, 'Then join a Circus sign up here first class free!' so izzy ran to her mom and asked, 'Mom can I join the circus?'                                                             5 minutes later              'Well honey you can join the circus if you promise you can keep your grades up and be careful' her mother said. Izzy replied 'ok I prromise' so izzy signed up to be in the circus and went to bed.

Item_Response: Hi I'am max and I work at a circis and I do alot of dangeres thing that you cant do . I work with animals like tigers, elefents, seals, jarafs, horeses.I travel on road with 100 people who are like circus family to me, who are with me the whole time.When you're young, it's the time to do it.It's the time to travel, the time to grow and experience your life.what many people think,the life of a circus performer isnt all high-flying fun and gamesand clowning around.It's more glamorous than being an accountant, but there are some drawbacks. circus performer  work  long day and spend a lot of time away from home. On tour,you dont really have anywhere to call home and you're always thinking about that night shows,'' says philippa.''I miss my home and garden and i dont see my family.                                                                                                      You have to work a lot of hours and weekends as well.Thats a life of a performer  from a circus its fun to be a performer because you get to travle around the world.Anyone who thinks circus life is nonstop play is crazy.I max know different, i live in big trailer with my family. We travel 20,000 miles in seven months each year, visiting 150 cities.I work from sunup to sundown.I also get a thrill from performing in front of a live audience.''I get to play and have fun every night.its great to see the faces of the audience just jump alive when when i make eye contact with them during a performance.You can see the audience being transported to another world.''You need to have a specific talent, the right body type and be very determined. Philippa,sroad to circus stardom started when she was five years old.I did musical theatre and balletand all kinds of music, singing,acting and everything to hone my craft who also trained in rhythmic gymnastic for years.When i was 11, i knew i wanted to be a performer,so i went for it. I gave up everything else and concentraded on my dancing and performing. there are so many people out there who want to do what you do, that you have to go for it.you have to put your heart into it and be certain that that,s what you want to do.

Item_Response: Hey, the circus is a fun place, but it is a lot of work.  As the ringmaster, it is my job to make sure that people are doing what they are supposed to be doing.  I also have to help other performers make sure that can do their act.  The lion tamer probably has the hardest   job of any performer because the lion is very dangerous.      In my downtime, I like to help the other performers practice their acts as well as my own.  The juggler is one of the ones I don't help because he sometimes juggles flaming chainsaws!  The trapeze artist also is not someone Id like to help as she flips around and does twists and twirls.  I could seriously hurt myself !  As for my own act, well, that's what this story is about.      When I first joined the circus, I had no act.  The old ringmaster, my father, was about to retire and I never even thought about becoming ringmaster.  I decided to ' try out ' for a clown. Well that was a joke! (HAH HAH!!! Get it,  joke!) Anyway, the clown didn't work out as I  previously said. Next, I thought about being a tightrope walker. That also didn't work thanks to my little slip I had that left me in the hospital for 4 weeks.  After I got out of the hospital, my dad was retired and that meant a position as ringmaster was now open.  I knew it would be imposable for a rookie to get the position as ring master.      It actually wasn't me who got the position but my older brother! (Can you believe it after how hard I've worked! )  So, I got a little angry. Wait. I shouldn't a little angry. I was VERY ANGRY.  I was so angry that I quit the circus.       I know this story is about how I got my job but it didn't happen the first year. Months later, I got married to a beautiful woman. (a.k.a The Trapeze Artist).  After I explained what happened, she encouraged me to try again. So I did.  When I got back to the circus my brother wasn't there. I was happy yet confused at the same time.  The juggler told me he had been diagnosed with spinal stinosis ( did I mention he was a dwarf ?)  The whole circus went to visit him the next day at the hospital.  He was completely paralyzed from the waist down. It was all so sudden.  Moments later, a machine started to make a constant beep and doctors rushed is and asked us to leave. I knew what this meant.   We had go back to the circus and the I was automatically ringleader. Simple as that. But that's not the end of the story. That's just the beginning. A year later we went back to the hospital not because of my brother, but because of our new born child. We named him Dillon after my brother ( who had really died.)  Dillon became the youngest member of the circus. He could ride a unicycle at the age of 3 months. Amazing isn't it.  Sometimes he fell, sometimes I fell when tried to ride to unicycle which was not a great idea by the way.   Our lives felt complete.  We needed nothing else.  That's when the scary thing happened.  Dillon started to throw up constantly.  We were very worried. We took him to the doctors office to get him looked over. The doctor said he probably had a appendicitis and that we should take him over to get an x-ray. Indeed his appendix had ruptured. They had to operate immediately.  The operation was successful but Dillon couldn't ride his unicycle for many months.  We needed another act. Clowns, jugglers, lion tamers. What else did we need? Then I had it.  We need a strongman.   We bought plane tickets all the way to Africa to find some of the strongest people in the world.  Many came to preform but we knew we could only choose one.  One man could dead lift 600 pounds! There's one possibility right there.  Another could bench 800 pounds.  The choice was hard because they both could lift the some amount of weight. We went with the second guy.  He seemed really interested about being in the circus.  He almost exceeded his maximum limit before we had to stop him. We had no choice but to take him.    He filled out his passport to America and started to travel with us.  Great news was waiting for us when we arrived.  Dillon could almost ride his unicycle again.  We were so excited that we threw a party. Everyone came and brought Dillon something. He got a golden unicycle from the juggler.  At the time he was 2 years old and still better than me on a bike.  After the party we had our first show. The next week, the circus was packed with people Everyone had been practicing their acts for weeks and still felt nervous.  We started of with the lion tamer then my wife, them the juggler.  After that we had Dillon do his routine. the crowd went wild and everyone did good.  My act was not only as a ringleader, but as a father, a husband, and a brother.  This was my family. This was my place. This was my life.

Item_Response: Life in a Circus                                             Life in a cicus is very hard work. It involves dedication and skill to be in a circus.Anyone who thinks life in a circus is easy should probably think again.If you want to find out what it is like to be in the circus then read on.          Being in the circus involves a lot of hard work. You have school,chores,practice then a show! Then by twelve o clock you are just barely getting into bed.          Being in the circus does have good things and bad thing about it. For example you do a lot of tours. So that means traveling and you dont get to see your family as much as you would like to.          As mentioned there are also good things about being in the circus. Even though you dont get to see your family as much your friend who perform with you become like you second cicus Family.Another good thing is you get to visit so many new places and that ties in with school lessons as well.         So as you can see being in the circus is hardwork. Even though there are some downer being in the circus is a wonderful expirence. It involes dedication but it si enjoyabl to go different places, meet new people, and have an enjoyable time performing with friends.

Item_Response: THE CIRCUS SURPRISE    ONE WEEK EARLIER...             MOM! What is it Sharleene? Look at this newspaper ad! What is it about? It is an employees wanted sign! For what? Being in the circus! Auditions are tomorrow (on Tuesday)!Can you please take me? Sure, this will be really fun! Have you been practicing your balance? NO!!!I forgot! Well, you better start practicing if you want to be in the circus. OK!             Finally! It is Tuesday!! MOM! What? Are you ready to go? Yes,just one second... I bought you a new leotard for good luck. Do you like it? YES I LOVE IT! IT IS PINK AND SPARKLY! Great! Lets go. How far away is it? It is 1 hour away! AWWW!!            Finally! We are here! It looks so amazing! I have never seen a circus up close before!   Mom! Look at all the circus horses! They are so amazing! ''Thank you'' said a circus trainer. Now lets go to my auditions! There were a lot of people auditioning! There were 20 people auditioning and there is only 2 slots!Sharleene was last. She did walking on a tightrope,juggled, and did an acrobatic trick! Sharleene was by far the best!            Then, the next day they came back to see who made it. First, she was scared because she saw ''BOB'' on the paper. Then she looked more down on the paper and it said ''SHARLEENE'' !!!! She made it in the circus! The next day she came back. She started working on her tricks! A COUPLE DAYS LATER...             She met many new friends including Bob. They all had a wonderful time at the circus. Sharleene was the circus's surprise!

Item_Response: As I walked into the big top I started to smell the sweet smell of buttered popcorn, and    peanuts they were feeding to the elephants.  I saw the red nosed clowns, on there unicicles.  And last but not least I heard, just as we were siting down in our seats the magi walk on stage and yell out to the oudiance. ' Welcom ladys and gentalman to the one and only Bellini Circus!'               Everyone stood up in their seats and started to cheer.  During that time, over all the ruckus, the magi yelled.  'Let the magic begin!' All the sudden a guy and a girl flew down to the ceilling from a trapiese twirling and swaying side to side.  Clowns came from everywere, and then lots of red smoke appered when it was gone.  A lion and his tamer came onto the stage while the lion let out a ferocios roar.               Everybody started to ooooooo and aaahhhhh, as the lion did lots of amazing tricks.  Until more red smoke appered and there again was the magi, and he said.  'How was that ladies and gentalmen, give a round of applause for that performance!' and we did until everybody started to file out of the big top.           I will never forget that day will I, I said as I walked out of the big top.

Item_Response: If you go for your dreams anything can happen. I think joining the circus isn't just fun and hard, maybe it can change your life.            I think the circus is an interesting and weird place to work. I've always wanted to join gymnastics, but I never did. If I join gymnastics I might persue my dreams. Being a gymnis can end up being an acrobat, so if I join gymnastics I would might end up being an acrobat.            If I do work at a circus, I know how hard it is to work at one. To work at one you would have to have a cerain talent. Your talents can lead you to a great job. Working at a circus takes a lot of practice. You'd have to practice your tricks a lot. Working at a circus is a little risky, but if you really want to work at a circus, you should go for it. Working at a circus could be risky because of all the tricks they do. Their tricks are sometimes dangerous.            There are also good things about working at a circus. You get to travel around the world. When you travel around the world you get to travel in a big trailer with your family. The best part about working at a circus is seeing the smile on kids faces when they watch you perform. Some people that work at the circus work there to inspire children.            The circus is really fun. You can play games and win prizes or you can watch the circus acts. If your feeling sad I suggest you go to the circus and turn that frown upside down. When you grow up, you should join the circus. It will be tons of fun, so what do you say, are you going to join?            Clearly, if you go for your dreams, anything can happen. Maybe, going for your dreams can lead you to work at the fun,weird, and magical circus.

Item_Response: Being in the circus is not all the fun and games as it seems, but it has many hardships. you have to work almost all day. It might seem fun because of all the cool stunts you do, but those are very hard to do.        As soon as you are done with break, You do nonstop work at the circus until the show is over and then you go to bed. The next day you wake up, it is back to work again.        You don't have any time to see friends and family. Also, you don't get free time to play things like soccer or baseball.         There are some upsides, though. People think you are really cool and people want your autograph. You get to see different places in the world like Japan and Europe. You get to meet many people, too.        As you can see, the circus life is not as easy as it seems. Such as long hours hard performances and not being able to see your family.

Item_Response: The circus is not all fun and games, you have to practice everyday until you get it right, you have to be confident, and you have to  be ready for anything.                                                First, if your going to be in the circus you have to practice everyday until you get your preforming act right. you have to put a little risk and a little fun in your act, be creative and try new things. if you finish one act try another. make sure your act is a perfect ten and you'll be great.                                         Next, you have to be confident and determind. if you are not confident in your self when you are doing your act something will go wrong. you also have to be determind and brave if you are not you would not want to do the act anymore and the show will not include you.                      Last, you have to be ready for anything. you have to be prepared for the unexpected beacuse what if you have to perform three or more times a day or what if  your performing partner gets sick and you cant perform. you have to be ready for anything and what ever happens, the show must go on.            Clearly, the circus life is not easy, you have to work hard, be confident and be prepared for anything.

Item_Response: A Circus Life         Hey, i'm Kenlee Mount I am 11 I work in a circus with my family. A circus life is not easy, yeah you get to hang out and play games but working from sunup to sundown is about how my day goes.            When we first get to place where we will have the show we set up the R.V. and get ready for the follwing day.             6:30 A.M. I wake up gp outside for some breakfast from my mom and dad we normal eat pancakes, yum!             7:00 A.M. Time to get dressed foe school even thought I am in the circus I still have to go to school.             9:30 A.M. School, I go and learn about all the things a normal kid would learn about like: math, scicene, ELA (reading), and socal studies.             4:30P.M. School is over and it's time for my afternoon snack and break!            5:00P.M. I have to do my homwork but i only have a little bit of time.           5:30 P.M. Time to get ready for the show I have to do a lot of things like practies my flips and tricks while my mom is practesing with her crazy monkey and my dad, is a clown so he is craking jokes  but after that i have to get ready and put on my make-up and do my hair and also put on my coutume.            7:00 P.M. On the side of the stage ready to go on!            10:45 P.M. Just got done now i get to eat and when I go outside I see my family is grilling hot dogs my favorit!            1:00 A.M. Time to gp to bed it has been a long day and I am pooped.            That is how a normal day would be like in the circus it is hard but fun I love doung it but I miss my home a lot and I miss the rest of my family , the one good thing about being in the circus is you get to meet new people and see new things!

Item_Response: ?When I was in the circus my sister and I had a very fun experience.It was hard but we kept on going to continue our dreams.We had to learn gymnastics,acting,dancing,and singing before we get to become circus performers.When we learned all those steps we were finally a circus performer.That is when our dreams came true.                   When our dreams came true we had to learn acrobatics.We had to do sommersaults which made us dizzy.Then we walked on tight ropes which almost made us fall.My sister and I also got launched from cannons and we got a little frightened.Then we learned something new.                   Training animals.We thought it would be very fun but it wasn't.One of the snakes had bit me while teaching him to play ringtoss but at least it didn't have poison.When my sister was teaching the monkey to swing on a vine,it accidently flopped on her head and ruined her hair.My sister and I were learning how to jump on top of the horses,we jumped on top of them,then they ran through the tent.Then we did something scary.                   Juggling.Well thats not really scary but you have to juggle chainsaws that are on fire.Now thats scary.We also had to juggle balls which were ok and we had to juggle swords which was scary because they could cause a minor injury.Then we juggled torches which also could burn my hand but I finally did.                   When we practice everything it was time for the show to start.When we went to our positions and started they were amazed.A few people got creeped out but gave lots of tips to the usher.When we finished we were wiped out.Then we realized that it is a very tiring job and hard work.Also we learned our lessons on being a circus performer.

It was Noahwennie's time to shine.                               He got Harry and cut him apart,but put him back together.There he was Harry was behind the stage while the body was cut open. Everyone was clapping! Noahweenie got teary he was so happy! He was in headlines everywhere!                              He went to Italy, France ,and the U.S. .                               Noahwennie had his own clothes line ,he was popular than Houdini. Then he got married , had 2 kids and lived in  Sacremento and sadly died in car crash.

Item_Response: I      Beep! Beep! Beep! Groaning, I slam down the off button of my alarm. I stretch, yawn, get dressed into my overalls and head over to the pie car for breakfast.           Oh! What am I thinking? I need to introduce myself! Hi, my name is Ariana Lasnier. I'm not your average 12 year old. I have spent most of my last 5 years touring the world with my family in the circus. I know what you're probably thinking... I'm a freak that can bend into a pretzel on a tightrope. Well, I'm not. Being in the circus is so much different than that. I'm part of the acrobats section. Not to brag, but we do A-MA-ZING tricks while hanging from ropes and so on. Anyways...          You get the point. Now, back to the story. On my way to the pie cart, I realize something. It's abnormally quiet. That's odd...  At the pie car, I sit down at a table and wait. And wait. And wait. Where is everyone? After what seemed like ages, Michelle, our cook arrives.    'Finally...' I mumble, my stomach growling.   'I'm sorry dear, I was in the back helping your mother. She's coughing up a storm!' Michelle apologizes, clanking the pans on the stove.   'W-what do you mean? I mean, she'll be okay for the show tonight won't she?' I ask worried.   'Your guess is as good as mine!' She laughs.         I fake a nervous laugh to cover my anxiety. We can't go on without her! We need her to tame the lion! After a while my eggs and bacon are ready.   'Eat up or you'll be late for school!' Michelle commands.         Well of course I can't go to just one school due to the moving for 7 months each year. Instead us younger performers get home schooled. My mom teaches, of course she would if she wasn't sick.         I rush over to the schooling car. Class has just started.   'So today- *cough cough*- we are going to revise evaluating expres- *cough cough* expressions! Goodness sakes! I'm sorry for the cough!'   My mom exclaims.     'Gee mom, you're really sick! You could rest. We'll just do tomorrows test so you don't have to talk.' I suggest.   'Well, I guess...' She says unsure.         So we take our test then read a book. Finally.... Class is over and I head to the stalls for some chores. All I have to do is feed and groom the horses and clean the stalls. After that I have to practice my routine and then I'm done until the show. This would be easy but my mom can't help. Great. So I decide to do the parts I can, by myself. Like flips, twirls on the rope and so on.         When I finally finish I head over to my moms parlor. There she is coughing and coughing and coughing!    ' You really are sick aren't you...' I say in a hushed voice.   She groans. I'll take that as a yes.   'Who's gonna take your place then?' I question   'Well, *cough* I think maybe we could postpone the show.'    'No! We can't! We are already booked for at least a show per day!' I exclaim. What are we going to do? I thought. Then, it came to me!   'Mom! I could tame the lion!' I say. I regret what came out of my mouth right away, that thing could kill me!   My mom thinks, coughs, groans and finally says 'I need to rest.'         As I head towards the door I think. I guess I could at least try to tame the lion. I just need to suck it up and learn. I turn back to my mother one last time. 'Mom, I'm going to tame the lion.' Then, I leave.         At the lion cage I find Simba- the lion- sleeping in the corner.   'Simba... Simba...' I coo. He growls. Ok. Where is the food?  I scan the room and stop. Over in the opposite corner is raw fish. Yuck!   I quietly shuffle over to the corner. I slowly stick my hand in the bucket. Of course being myself, I fully extend my arm in front of my face and hold it by the tail like a pair of dirty socks. I throw it to the lion. Out of nowhere it pounces over to the fish and rips it apart. Ok I can do this...         After about 2 or 3 hours, I'm finally done with my 'training'. Fingers crossed I don't die tonight. Time to get ready for the show!          I scurry over to the makeup parlor. All they do is powder my face a put on some mascara, lipstick and eyeshadow. Now, my costume is not exactly the most comfortable outfit on earth. It's a short dress with hanging, itchy fabric at my waist. Then, of course, is my tights. Now I look circus ready.         As I jog over to the main tent, I pass my biggest horror of the night. The lion being pushed, in its cage of course, over to the tent. Can you say death sentence? My head is spinning. This isn't right. I shouldn't be doing this, that lion will rip me apart! My knees feel weak. I feel dizzy. It's too much! Suddenly, everything goes black.         'Ariana...' The darkness calls.   'Ariana.' Closer, louder this time...   'Ariana!' Out of nowhere I'm snapped back into reality and being shaken by Joshua ( my acrobat partner). My eyes flutter open.   'Oh thank god your awake! We're on in 10 minutes!' He sighs of relief.   'W-what happened?' I mutter.   'I don't know. We found you passed out on the ground a few yards outside the entrance.' He explains.   'Is my mother okay? What about the lion?'    'She's still sick. But we have a substitute performer. Duh!' He laughs.   ' Sub-substitute!? I spent hours training with that lion!' I complain.   'Its fine... Anyways the audience came in and they-' he was cut of.   'It's show time!' My father exclaims in his announcer voice.         We take the ladder up to our ropes. Hanging there we wait for our signal. The lights go out.   'Ladies and gentleman... Welcome, to the Balabam Circus. Pleeeaaaassseeee, put your hands together for our first act of the night, the acrobats!' The announcers voice booms over the loud speakers.   The audience cheers.          I look down at the dirt floor far below us. I take a deep breath and let go of my rope. Swinging by the the rope attached to my feet I twirl over to Joshua who grabbed my arms and flipped us both. Slowly we put our arms out to show my rope is unattached and we are both just hanging by his rope, and we are only attached by a chain in our mouths. I open my mouth to release the chain. The sensation of dropping washes over me, only to be stopped by the swinging bar a hook onto. The crowd goes wild. Around me I see all the girls hanging by silk, twirling endlessly with so much grace. I pull up to position myself to sit on the swing. Only to leap through the air while Joshua swings on his swing to catch me. Again the crowd goes bonkers.          After a moment of them cheering I jump and plunge through the air, flipping over and over again. After a few seconds I blindly spin around. Trying to aim towards the landing mat. I realize I'm off by a foot or two and won't make it to the mat. Suddenly, something slams into me from behind. Joshua. He Had noticed my mistake and altered his path to help me.          I tumble onto the mat trying not to look dazed. And stand with my toes pointed and arms out. The crowd claps and we exit to the back section.         The crowd becomes muffled as a sit backstage.    'Hey uh, thanks for helping me out.' I mutter awkwardly.   'No problem. Hey wanna go get some popcorn?' He asks   'Sure!' I say relieved to get away from the quiet room.         After an hour and a half or so we get ready for our final bow. Oh duh! My mom! She came out and helped with the lion. Anyways, at the final bow I notice someone. Danielle Stone. My heart leaps up my throat. She waved her hand for me to come over after the bow.         I scurry over to her after explaining to my dad a friend was here. Danielle is, well was, my best friend before I started the circus.    'Oh my god! Hi! I haven't seen you in ages!' I shout over the noise hugging her.   'I know! You did awesome! So, how you been?what are you up to?' She smiles.   'Oh nothing. Just, you know, touring the world and such...' I joke.   ' Well about that... I'm joining the circus!Im going to be an acrobat like you!' She exclaims throwing her arms up.   'Really that's great! Well, as much as I'd love to talk I have to go. See you soon.' I hug her once more and walk away. Time for the meeting. I head to the back of the tent         Joshua waves me over to sit by him at our performance meeting. I blush and sit down. I mean, he is kind of cute... Moving on! The meeting is basically reviewing how we did and stuff. While they talk I rest my head on my arm. Although there we some bumps, today was a pretty great day!

Item_Response: I've always wanted to try out for the circus through out my life. I just found out that I got hired to try out at the circus! The things that I'm going to do at the circus are to train the show animals. I'm also going to be able to make up my own trick, and preform it on an aniaml!       First, I have to make my own trick and then practice it on an animal. The animal I will choose would be a tiger. I've been practicing this trick for about a week. Now I get to finally get to present it in front of everybody! My trick is to jump really high off of a trampoline. While I'm in the air I will do a back flip right onto a tiger!       Next, I have to practice a few more times before the show. 1, 2, 3 and jump, flip and land. Then, my boss wanted me to make the tiger sprint and go upsidown on a big loop. So then I had to wait one more day to present my trick. 1, 2, 3 and jump, flip, land, sprint and loop.        Finally, today is the day, preformance day! As I go out I here the aduince cheering as the spotlight is blazing into my face. I feel presured, but I know that I can do this. I get on the trampoline and warm up. I finally get high enough to flip. As I land on the tiger I yell 'RUN!' At first I was very scared to go on the loop. Then after the loop I wanted to do it again. So I went back to the trampoline. Jump, flip, land, run and LOOP!        My first preformance wasn't so scary after all. I can't wait to do another preformance next time. I wonder if I get to do something crazy next time?

Item_Response: My name is Jim. I am a circuis performer. The others call me Slash because I perform with a sword. Now that I'm on the circuis topic the craziest thing happend at practice yesterday.       I was practicing my routine when I heard a chain snap and the sound of large feet heading my way. 'LOOK OUT JIM!!' My friend Mike yelled. I turned around sword at the ready and to my suprise, it was only our trained gorilla Curious Gorge.       'AAHHH HAHAH!' Mike laughed out loud. 'I got you good.' 'Don't do that, you know I'm in the moment when I'm practicing.'  At that moment, Gorge started to literally go ape. After he threw a fit he went to the door and pointed outside. I went to investagate and saw that one of the lion cages were empty.          'Good boy,' I said and got him a box of cookies. he went back to his cage and started to work on his cookies. I noticed that the lock had been broken and tracks lead into the main tent. I opened it up there was no lion just one big banner that read HAPPY BIRTHDAY JIM! After I read it out loud, other people started to crowd the tent. 'What's the matter, forgot your own birthday Slash?' Mike asked. 'Guess so.'

Item_Response: Hi my name is Gwen I am 13 years old and have been in the circus for 9 years. My father died from getting eaten by an animal while training them when I was 6. The performance that I do is acrobating, my mother is an animal walker and she sometimes trains the animals too. Also I have a small 2 year old sister named Mitsy.The circus I preform in is called Le Circe De Lune which means the circus of the moon in French.         A normal day in my life is that I get up around 5:00 A.M so then I can get some practice in before the school. Then at 6:00 I rush to the Pie cart to get a tasty Nuttella crep, which is technically a flat pancake, after that I rush to the school, which is a red wagon. My best friend Enzo waits for me at the door. In school we have tests and homework and weekends and all, but instead it's moving. Usually we learn about the places that we preform at, like right now we're in France.         After 6 hrs. of school I go home to feed my sister, because my mother is working. Then I go and practice for 3 hrs. before the show. After I put on my sparkly leotard and dress Mitsy in her puffy pink dress, and even though she is to young to really preform the clowns use her to do there show. Then I head down to the tent, the people painted my face.         Then as usual I have an awesome preformance and am totally wiped out. After I eat dinner and go to sleep around 11:00 p.m and wait for the day to start again.

Item_Response: The Great Circus!                   This is a story of how I, Isabell Castini, got in the circus! It started out one summer morning. I was getting ready to go to the park when suddenly my dad says, 'Isabell. Do you want to go to the circus instead?' I called back, 'Sure!' So I got ready to go to the circus! I was in the car when my dad asked me, 'Isabell, what would you be if you were in the circus?' I replied, 'Well, I guess I would be an acrobat!' My dad kept driving and said,'Well, Isabell, how about I get you lessons to be an acrobat? This is the perfect age to start!' He says that because im about 11 years old so he wants me to learn how to be something I want to be.                      We got to the circus at exactly 12:00 o'clock. We were just in time! The first act was clowns! I watched the clowns as they happily threw pie in each other's faces! It was so funny! The next act was the acrobats! I was so excited! They did flips and twirls and whirls! I was so amazed! Then after the show was over I told my dad, 'Yes. I would love to take acrobat lessons!' So the next day my dad called the city's office. 'Hello? Do you have any gymnastic lessons or acrobat lessons? I am not sure what they are called.' Asked my dad. 'Yes, all you have to pay is $20 a month.' said the phone lady. 'Okay. When do the next lessons start?' asked my dad. 'Next Tuesday? Okay we will be there!' 'Well?' I asked. 'You may come next Tuesday ok? Do NOT let me forget! This is very important!'                   A week had passed and my dad woke me up super early! 'The early worm catches the bird!' My dad cheerfully said. 'Um...dad? Isn't it supposed to be the early bird catches the worm?' 'Oh. Right.' said my dad as he laughs. 'Well anyways. Today is the day!' 'What?' I asked while yawning. 'You are supposed to go to your lessons!' my dad replied. 'At 7:00 in the MORNING?' I asked. 'No!' my dad says, 'You are supposed to be getting up early if you want to be in the circus like your big sister.' 'Okay. I will try to be more responsible.' I replied.                  Finally after what had seemed like an hour to me (which had only been about thirty minutes.) we were there! I entered the building and the counter lady was standing right there like she had been waiting for me. I asked her what time it was so I would know that she wasn't some kind if robot or something. She said it was 8:00 A.M. 'Okay, so maybe it was an hour.' I said to myself. 'Go right in there.' said the counter lady. As I went inside I saw girls who were probably up since 5:00 in the morning doing flips and really cool tricks! 'Wow! I wish I could do that!' I said out loud. Then a lady came up to me and said, 'Hello there, My name is Mrs. Belini. Are you one of our newcomers?' 'Um, yes.' I replied shyly. 'It's fine we are all family here! you don't need to be shy.' she said. she led me to a balance beam and held my hand. She told me to climb up the balance beam. It wasn't very high and she said she would hold my hand so I climbed up on the balance beam. She told me to try to jump off and spin 360 degrees. So I jumped off and tried to spin and I did! She said that was beginner stuff. I was so happy that I got off to a good start!                  A couple of years passed and I was doing AWESOME! I was now 15 and I knew a ton of stuff about the circus and the Belini Brothers! I was thinking about joining them. Then I knew something was going on. My circus/gymnastics teacher's name was Mrs. Belini! She is their SISTER?! I ran to my dad and told him, and he said he already knew. 'Isabell, she is going to try and get you into Belini Brothers!' screamed my dad. 'What?! I barely know anything about circuses and-,' my dad cut me off. 'It's fine! Do you think that she just wants to do that just because?' 'No.' I replied quietly. 'Then you are fine. She told me that you will be able to see them on Friday. Ok?' my dad told me. I started to stutter, 'Um, but, when? How? Whe-' 'Stop stuttering. you will be fine.'                 A week passed and I was ready! I got up REALLY early and my dad wasn't even up yet. I took a shower and got dressed, and I sat in the living room waiting for my toaster waffle to be done. My dad walked in the room thinking nobody was up yet. He almost screamed, 'INTRUDER! INTRUDER!' 'I woke up early dad just like youi said. Right?' He started to laugh. 'Ok what is the big occasion?' he asked. I gasped. 'You mean you don't remember?! The Belini Brothers? We are going there, remember? So i can audition?' 'Oh yeah!' He yelled. 'Hurry! Get dressed! Take a shower!' 'It's ok dad I already did all that.' 'Ok.' he said.  3 hours had passed and finally we got to the car and started driving.                 We finally got there and one of the Belini brothers told me to go on the stage and audition. I was so scared I could barely feel my feet! So I got on the balance beam and did a bunch of cool trips and flips. Mrs. Belini also taught me how to do the acrobat tricks in the air. I climbed the ladder. Everything looked so small but I saw my dad and Mrs. Belini Cheering me on. So I jumped and did one flip. I grabbed the bar and did flips. I was so amazed that I could do all this stuff! Then the Belini Brothers spoke. 'Isabell Castini!' I thought they were going to kick me out but they just started to laugh and dance. 'We want YOU to be in our circus!' I panicked and screamed, 'AHHHH! I am so happy!' My dad told me 'CONGRATULATIONS!' I packed my things up and said, 'Thank you dad.' I got on the train and left. And that is the story of how I got into the circus!                                                                             The End

Item_Response: The day at the Circus!                                          By: Grace Miculian                                      My shaggy long brown hair  touched my skin lightly as if it was scarred of me. My name is Scarlette Defox and i'm an acrobat in the circus. But enough aboust me i have to tell you a day at a circus for me.     I was laying in bed awake starring at the crumbling white paint on the ceiling. I was waiting for Koney Non , a clown, who woke me up to eat at the pie car.     I was wiped out , though i got used to being tired. Today we had a matinee show at 3:00.                      Knock , Knock , knock.      The sound echoed at the door flung open.                                       Koney Non was in the opening of the door already wearing wis make up and clothes plus his red velvet wig.                                   'Sorry , I forgot to wake you up early!' Koney chuckled as we went in my van.                                       ' What time is it?' I asked cunfused.                                        ' Oh its 2:49' Koney whispered.                                 'WHAT!!!!' I screamed juming up off my blue sparkly bed.                         ' Why did'nt you wake me up!' i yelled as i ran to my make up desk.                I grabbed my yellow worn out brush and brush out all my tangles. My hair was done by the time he answered.                                    ' Well they had extra buritos at the pie shop and I ran to get my fair share and then i forgot, then time passed by then i remembered you and got you some snacks' Koney laughed as he took out some crackers.     I jumped up and grabbed the crackers and shoved them in my mouth not caring what the flavor was.    i chewed it all up and it tasted like white cheddar.                   ' I hate you but i gotta say thank you so much I love you!!!!!' I screamed as i went to sit back down to put on my glittery make up.                Koney smiled and walked out my van and closed the door.      I put on my blue eye shadow and then but on eye liner.           I went as fast as I could wlile i put maskera on.\\   It was 2:50 by the time I finished.     On my make desk was a curling iron , but i had no time to spare. I put my hair in a bun and ran into my bathroom.     I looked in the mirror and I did'nt look have bad.      My brown hair looked perfect. But at that moment i knew i could'nt brush my teeth becuase i heard the clock go ding ,ding ,ding ,dong.    Meaning it was 2:59.              Luckily my outfit had been ironed and next to the sink.   I quickly slipped on the dress and tights and ran outside.     It seemed as if the Circus house area was a desert and i was the only one there.      I walked passed the vans and cars then started to run in to the building that we did our preformances.          Why was everybody practiceing I mean we had a show to do but nobody was in the audience.    The ring tosser was ring tossing, the lion tamer was taming and everybody acted as if there was no rush!                        I felt a tight pinch on my back.    It was Koney the Clown.                  ' You know that the show doesnt start till tomorrow!Right' Koney chuckled as he walked to his post.                 ' What!!!!!' I whispered as i walked where the acrobats trained.             So maybe the life in the Circus is crazy , but it is my dream to do it so I will do it. No matter what.                           The End

Jeff ran to the circus.                                                   Jeff asked,' what do I do to get in to the circus.                                    The clown said,'you need to....'                                                   Jeff yelled,' what do I have to do.           The clown said,' you need to act like a clown.' Later when Jeff came home he told his parents he joined the circus.           Jeff's mom said,' good for you. But are you sure your not going to miss us.'            Jeff said,' yes.'            The next morning Jeff said by to everyone goodby and then he was off. The circus was that night and Jeff's family was there. Jeff's acted was right after the lion tamer. Jeff went on with the clowns. Jeff and the clowns stared sparing water at each other, throwing pies, and throwing water balloons. Everyone was laughing. Jeff went all around the world. Jeff went to see his family on holidays. Jeff was happy with his life. The End

Item_Response: In the Circus           Welcome to the morning of the Circus. My name is Kenzi, I am   an acrobat in the Circus.   I don't always work alone. I have a partner and her name is   Morgan,she is a really good acrobat. Morgan is a really good partner,she is very kind. She will brighten up your day no mater what.   We have a very busy schedule.       7:30- We wake up at seven thirty and go get breakfast at the Eat and Meet bus.       8:00-At eight we go back to our bus and get dressed in our warmup clothes.       8:30- We go to our stations, there are about five stations, our station is acrobats.We practice all sorts of flips.       10:15- We go to the harness to practice acrobats in the air.       11:30- At eleven thirty we eat lunch at the Eat and Meet bus.       12:45- When we are back at the bus we get to just relax and take naps or play with the animals.       2:15- At two fifteen we practice acrobats in the air and acrobats on the ground for the last time before the show.       4:15- When we are all done we go back to are buses and take showers and do our hair.       5:30-At five thirty we go to the circus tent and watch the finale touches being made.       6:00- Then finale the doors open people take their seats and we get started.       8:30- The circus is over we had a wonderful day.           We do the same routine almost every week. Also we have a   show almost everyday.I do miss going home to my family and friends,  but over all I LOVE the CIRCUS!!!

Item_Response: The Clown              Once upon a time in a small town in Ireland, a 9 year old boy was watching a circus. He thought 'I wish I was in the circus.' Then he saw it, an advertisement for an opening at a circus. The boy jumped down from the bleachers and ran away from his parents, that he did not like.         When he got to the car, he asked a man if he could join. The man said yes and handed him a form. He wrote his name, Kingsley Bowton. He then wrote down 'his age'(13). Last, his signature.         Kingsley handed the man the form. He was now in the circus!! But it's not all he thought it was.         The next day Kingsley awoke and went to what is called the pie car, which is where circus members eat, for breakfast. Then he had to go to school. Half the kids there didn't even speak English. The school was a lot like his, surprisingly for him.         After school he played with his new friend, Rudy, then did chores with him, too. Now Kingsley headed to the pie car for dinner. The director told him that he won't be perform since he's new. He was okay with watching.         That night he watched the most amazing circus ever. Tomorrow he would be in it!

Item_Response: Some people think life is easy in the circus. I, Rachel Tatley,   know better. I'm an acrobat in the circus, and believe me, it's not as easy as you think. We have to wake up very early in the morning to do our jobs, and we go to sleep very late. We do several shows in over 150 different cities in a year! I travel with my family, and all the circus performers live in one big trailer. My mother is an animal trainer, and my father is a clown.                 Even though we live in a trailer, we still go to school. The   school just travels with us. Believe it or not, our school is just like yours! We have our regular lessons, along with tests. We also use computers. But because circus performers come from all over the world, a lot of my classmates speak different languages. I have always wanted to play an instrument or do a sport, but we never have enough free time to do other things.                  When school is over, we have do to chores and practice our circus tricks. Being an actrobat takes a lot of agility and perseverance. I took gymnastics when I was smaller, so I know how to do a lot of the flips and other things in the job of being a circus performer. In the circus, I still have a lot of friends even though we're not in our real home. We try to adapt to different temperatures, but it's hard because we move around so much.                   Sometimes life is hard for us circus performers, but I know I will always enjoy being an acrobat in the circus.

Item_Response: The Amazing Bella   By Isabella Woodhouse             Hello my name is Bella and I have story to tell you about my experience in the circus. It all started on May 4, 2010, my birthday, I was at my car getting ready for the next trip to Nevada. Then all of a sudden my car started moving. I looked out the window and to my relief we were just leaving early, but noticed my cat was gone. My cat was sitting on top of another car. I hit the emergency button that made all the cars stop,'Screeeech!' I grabbed my cat and we were off again. I thought all the crazy stuff was all done for the day, but I was wrong, very wrong.             Finally we stopped in Nevada for the week and we started to set up for the night. Then suddenly I heard a,'BOOOOMMM' I shot out of my car and ran to the tent. I looked around and saw that part of the stands were lose and fell of. I grabbed a wrench and ran to the stands and started tightening the loose screws. I guess I set an example because then everyone in the circus pitch in. Like I said before there was more in store for me that day.             The show started in ten minutes and everyone was filling the stands. I used to be nevous, but I've been doing this for a while so I was exited. Especially since I learned a new tightrope dance. The show has begun, but something was wrong I could feel it. 'ROOAARR!' everyone screamed in terror. Luckily I learned how to tame a lion in circus school. I finally got the lion back in it's cage and everything was fine. The show was canceled that night,but that is fine because it was a wild day anyway.               Wow what a day. This was probaly the weirdest, wildest,and most wonderful birthday ever.

Item_Response: The Cheetah and the Stage Manager                 When many people weren't coming to the circus, the acrobats   decided getting a new animal might work. They decided to go and find and animal. The problem was that the circus had every animal known to be in the circus. They didn't know what to do. They went to Australia to find a kangaroo. The problem was the kangaroo just kept trying to hop away. Another problem was that the next performance was three days away. This was going to be their biggest crowd yet because they had advertised saying they had a new animal.                  The crew decided to go to Africa to find an animal. With one day left. When they brought the cheetah back from Africa, he wouldn't listen to anyone. Every performer tried to tame the cheetah.   During dinner time, our stage manager said that maybe he should try taming the cheetah. He hadn't tamed any animals before but we decided we should let him try. The cheetah was going to our grand finally. When we looked through the curtains, we saw that the crowd was huge. As usual, all the performers and the animals went. Then, it was the cheetah's turn.                   When the cheetah and the stage manager went into the place where the performers perform, everybody was cheering. All of us were peaking through the curtain trying to look. The cheetah was amazing. It jumped through flaming hoops, and walked on three legs. It was the best animal we trained ever. After the spectacular performance, we decided to let the stage manager also be the cheetah trainer.                                                         The End

Item_Response: Monique was devastating. I had known that she would never be the best in our circus, but I never knew that she truly had no talent. Already a half of the crowd was shouting angrily to Manny, our ringleader, and Monique. Shocked by the audience's response to her part in the show, Monique fled the stage and burst into tears as she ran to her trailer. I couldn't blame her for the audience's reaction. Many times the audience quality changed. In Atlanta, there were many happy people while in Salem, there were many grumpy people. Although most of the angry responses were because of the audience quality, I knew that part of it was because of her act.               Dandrum Circus was a very successful circus until Pansy Lynn quit. Pansy was about the best horseback rider in history. She was the one who wowed the crowd with her amazing horse tricks. To the public, she was known as 'Pansy the Horse Whisperer.' Sometimes Pansy would go to the audience and answer their questions and sign autographs. She loved the publicity. And her horse, Kay. Pansy loved that horse. He was proud, handsome, and Pansy would die for him. Actually, he died first.               Pansy cried her eyes out the day that the doctors declared Kay dead after he died of a disease. At first she refused to work with any other horse and stayed inside her trailer for weeks. Manny talked to Pansy and even sent her to a therapist to help settle her feelings. Pansy came back fresh and happy. It seemed like she had forgotten about Kay. I followed her to the stable when she was picking out a horse to practice with. I saw her come towards a beautiful tan horse like Kay, except it wasn't. 'You look so beautiful,' Pansy said as she stroked his mane,'like Kay.' She paused, making a shocked and puzzeled face. 'Where is Kay?' she said to herself. As if remembering, she sadly walked back to her trailer.                The next day, I heard that she quit. Jose, the circus manager, looked as red as a beet when he came out of the office trailer after his talk with Pansy. I didn't have a glimpse of Pansy that day and never saw her ever since.                We moved to Seattle. I helped post flyers for job openings in our circus. One of the jobs was Pansy's part with horses. Jose sat in his office interviewing many people who wanted a job. I had peeked through the window and had seen Jose's tired face after the interviews were done. It was after dinner and he was about to flip the sign that said 'Interviews in Session' to 'No Interviews' until a teenage girl with purple hair and bright blue eyes ran up to Jose. 'Are the interviews done already?' she asked. Jose looked around. No one else was in line. 'I guess one more is fine,' he said. When both of them went inside the trailer, I slipped back to my own trailer and had a good night sleep.                She got Pansy's part. Jose introduced her to everyone in the circus while we were eating breakfast. 'Her name is Monique and she claims that she is the 'horse whisperer' of this town.' We all clapped. At practice that day, I saw that she was not very good, but I didn't let that worry me. At least until showtime.                Monique ruined her part. She drove the horses too close to each other so that they were practically hitting each other. Then she fell off the horses and tripped herself and got herself stuck in the hay while the horses were chewing her hair. At least there was my part.                After Monique were my friends and me. We're called the 'Birds of the Trapeze.' I jumped and Ellen swang towards me. We caught eachother and danced around our course. Maylee and Lucy joined us. The crowd loved us. Now it was time for the finale. We all grabbed ropes that were in a circle and were somersaulting and changing spots. I've seen YouTube videos of us, and we were really good. Then Aimee jumped in the middle and we became tropical birds in paradise. We landed perfectly on our posts and posed. The crowd cheered wildly and we took a bow. They seemed to forget Monique.                Later that day, Manny told us that we saved the show. Monique had quit. 'If we find another bad performer, I'm not gonna put horse tricks on the show,' he said. We only had a day in Seattle. I wasn't sure he was going to find a replacement. That is, until I saw the long line of people outside the office trailer.
