Item_Response: THE  CIRCUS FLIER                   The first day of school my teacher handed out fliers about a circus contest.'LET THE BEST STORY'S WIN'.It has to have 2 main characters I thought to myself 'I can win this'.Then my teacher said and there's one more thing.The people who write the story, and the 5 lucky winners will get to win front row seats and they get to bring their family!I got so excited I grabbed pencil,paper and my pencil and started writing.The story needed serious work.   The next day at school I was thinking of some things for the contest and then it hit me.I should make a good story by having a good plot and beginning,middle and end.That night I started my story about the circus.                                     THE  CIRCUS   The day I was born my mom told me that I wanted to be in the circus I don't no why but when i was 4 they put me in Gymnastics they said it would help my balance on the tightrope.I don't no why they did but i'm glad now because I am a tightrope walker now all thanks to my parents I travel all around the world seeing different sights and beautiful places that I never thought I would see before.       When we reached our destination I saw a bear riding a unicycle wasn't that a sight.When we were practicing I got nervous and almost fell because i've never performed in front of a live audience before.I got so nervous on the tight rope my legs just froze and my legs locked but i caught myself and got back on the platform and got down because i was scared to death that could've put me to my death if i would of not kept my balance.       That night in front of the audience was packed and I saw this little kid about in the 5th grade or so and he was in the front row of the circus.He smiled at me I smiled back and waved he looked like he admired me and that got me across that tight rope.The night when that boy gave me a smile changed my life if that boy wouldn't of smiled I wouldn't be telling this story right now.That circus was about ten years ago and if I could have the opportunity to meet that boy again I would shake his hand that was the circus man's dream now and his goal.           10 years later he made his dream come true and shook the boy's hand for the first time.           15 years later the man died of a heart attack in his basement.   The boy went to his funereal and gave his heart to the old man because the boy looked up to him.       20 years later the boy gave the old man a grave that no one could give him and he buried him in a circus and when the boy died of a disease he got buried right beside his idol.

Item_Response: This is a story about a girl named Charlotte, she worked with the circus and so did her family.She woke up with a loud BANG it was circus time she had to practice the type rope. Item_Response: The winning storys                I was at school and before we left the teacher handed out red and white papers. I quickly scanned though the paper. Right when I got in my moms car I started talking so fast telling her what I hade just read.Finally she told me to stop and slow dwon and start agin. So I did. She asked when it was due and I  probable should get started on it.    Right when I got home I got a big stack of papers, a couple of pencils and I got right to work. Finally my dad and my big brother got home. I asked where they have been all afternoon . My dad sayed he and had to do some cleaning up in his classroom and my big brother said nothing as usally. Then I told my dad about the circus thing. He said that was awsome and asked what my story was going to be about. I said that I really didnt know. The next day at school half of the kids where saying that they all ready had they story done.That night I got my story done and writen the why I whated it. So the next day I tured it in.    The teacher said that torrom they would be telling you won and you would get your ticket and stuff. The next day I dressed a little nicer than what I usally wear.When I walked in for school and went in the gym to sit dwon I saw a lady and a man and are princable. she asked all the kids if she could have are atenten. we obeyed  her commed.Then the man said I will now tell you the winers of the copatenten. Frist from my class was  just a couple of people and me. I was so shocked when they said my name. I think so was ever one else. The man took are picture and said see you to night ladys and gentlmen .    That night I saw lots of people I knew. The same man came out and said please injoy the show .The show was awsome.Frist they had a bear in a twoto dance on a ball , then they had a women walk and ran on a tite rope luckily she did not fall.They also had a women jumb on a hourse backwards and clowns did lots of funny things they also had a lady and a man swing on diffent fabic that hung from the clealing and they would swing to one to the other .They also would hung on each other. Someday I wish I could do some of the things the people did.I wish that the night would have never ended.

Item_Response: The circus kayos.                                                                                   Once, there was a circus performer named Chicken Yumyum.  She was a person who was not afraid of any type of snake, so she decided to join the circus.  Back then, people use to dance with constrictors in the circus.  It was all her talent.  So she decided to join the circus.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        She was entered in a circus in Tokyo.  There was many trains to pull stuff with help of trucks and ships.  Chicken was the last performer.  Her job was to stand on the horse while sprinting and dance with mean constrictor about 7 feet long.  It was a success!  She then went to Florida to do a huge practice.                                                                                                                                                                                                        While practicing Chicken thought she was going to be the best and most wealthy performer in the world.  However on the newspaper it said that a clown called the floating spirit could juggle on a very thin rope while bouncing on a ball with a monster unicycle.  Chicken got mad and said to herself,'that clown should try a constrictor till he falls of his rope and dies.'She practiced more and more and was going to preform much more better than the last one.  This time she was going to a lot better than her last preform.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     There were a lot more trains and ships and trucks.  Again she was last which was good.  The Floating Spirit was there that time.  He was on a rope that almost looked like a spider web with a unicycle and a ball while juggling 6 balls.  This time in his preferment he said,'THROW THE RATTLESNAKE.'Someone shot a rattlesnake in the air and he started dancing with it in one hand while the other hand was juggling the balls!  Chicken saw that the rattlesnake was weird and how he juggled and how he unicycles was weird.  Chicken didn't know how to juggle, but she did know she was not afraid of snakes.  She asked somebody who was in charge of the circus materials,'where are the rattlesnakes?'We don't have any rattlesnakes,'said the guy,'but we have corral snakes.'Chicken was confused, but she didn't care that much.  This time she got a 8 and a half constrictor with 2 corral snakes.  She put a unicycle on a horse that was much faster than the other horse.  She was a great success but more people cheered for The Floating Spirit than Chicken.  They through money and roses at The Floating Spirit.                                                                                                                                                                             All night Chicken thought about all the strange things that happened that night.  Then it hit Chicken that the clown was a fake!  There were strings on  the balls and on the clown!  He was also attached to the unicycle!  And there was no rattlesnakes in the circus and the rattlesnake was fake or dead because it never moved! 'Nobody would believe me,'she thought,'but he can ruin my career!'She was doing nothing for 5 minutes and then she had brilliant idea.  She dressed like an untalented person and asked somebody,'when and where is The Floating Spirit's next preferment?'The guy replied.' America, Main, Tuesday April 21, 9:30 pm.'That is where and when Chicken left.                                                                                                                                                                Chicken borrowed a spot light and went into the tent.  While 'The Great Floating spirit' was doing his fake moves Chicken aimed the spot light above the clowns head and turned it on.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       It showed the lines above his head and then everybody started shouting BOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOO! and started shouting CHICKEN YUMYUM!                                                                                                                                                                       In conclusion, Chicken Yumyum died after a corral snake bit her and fell of a tight rope and was constricted by an anaconda about 16 feet long.  However, she was the most famous circus performer in history.

Item_Response: My crazy Circus life                                              by Alenne Mojica             Anyone who's a circus performer knows its crazy, but difficult being in a circus.   My name is Lola Hoptree and this my life in a circus.I live in a big trailer with my family , and some circus performs.Every day different for me, because I travel to different places every day.                  A typical day for me is not like yours. I wake up at 5:25 A.M, get dressed, brush my teeth, and I go eat some food.Later, the performers and my family get ready for the big show.I put on my neon costume, and practice my tightrope walking for tonight.Am trying to walk on my hands, but my dad said it's to dangerous.Also, I have been learning gymnastics.My mom does acrobats with my dad.And my sister is a juggler.We all practice are talents in the circus sometimes even play around.me and my sister love to play around.            Sometimes it's fun being in a circus and all,but sometimes i miss my old school, and my old friends.I like being in the circus, but I miss my old house, and my old dog.I mean we travel everywhere and sometimes if were lucky we get to go back to California and visit my grandma and grandpa.Me and my little brother love to go to my grandma's house ,because it brings back so many memories.Also it's like the first time i can go outside without people asking me to take pictures with them.I can play with my cousins and see my uncles.               I love performing in front of people. One, because I get smiles, and people laughing at our performances, and two when I perform i see people amazed of what i did.I love performing in front of hundredthsof people.Also when I see their faces it makes want to do this more.I never want to stop performing its somthing i love and always want to do.And, I'm sure my family members feel the same way to.                                                                                                                                                                                                     As you can see, being in a circus is hard, but fun at the same time. And I always want keep on doing it.

Item_Response: Hi my name is Joshua I'm thirteen years old and I work as a clown in the circus. I'm still not a real clown I'm being trained by Bobo the clown. One day Bobo tells me to get Momo his pet monkey, but when I go to the cages all the animals are gone. The circus master thinks that I did it so he told me if all the animals aren't back by midnight he's going to kick me out of the circus.         First I try to find all the small animals, but when I thought I got all of them I founded out I was missing Momo. I decided to find Momo later and go for the bigger animals. The bigger animals were easyier then I thought they were. It all came up to Momo to decide if I can stay. It was five minutes before midnight and I didn't know what to do. Item_Response: CIRCUS TIME                  Have you ever thought about one day being in a circus? A circus can look like lots of fun but can be a little hard to work in because you have to wake up early to get dressed. Circus's can be fun to  watch but can be a little stressful for you to work in. One day a girl named Karen thought it might be interesting s she went to search for a circus she can join.               Karen was a curios girl.  So she set off to Massachusetts because she heard their was going to be a circus there soon. She saw the magical circus and looked at everyone do their magical talents. Se was impressed about the way they did their tricks. She said out loud ''I WISH I WAS IN A CIRCUS. She asked them if she can be in the circus. They said sure you may be able to be in the circus.               She decided she wanted to be in the acrobatics because she had been in gymnastics before and knew how to do tricks and flips. Karen was not used to waking up at 7:00 A.M. so that was a big change for her. She loved school, but she did not like how it was taught in the circus classes. She knew two languages very well. Soon they made Karen learn another language she was very happy she got to learn another language. Not long before she realized that she had to go to bed at 10;30 P.M. after her show was over.               Ever since she entered the circus she gets to talk to her family once a week. She was not very happy with her new schedule. One fact she did love about the circus was the deliciouse food trucks. Each day they had a different kind of food. She had her own dance studio where she practiced from 3:30 to 6:30.               At last she realized she really didn't want to be in a circus. Sje loved the way her life was, she really missed the times she spent with her family and friends. Yea she loved the food at the circus but she missed her moms delicious home made food. Now Karen is going back to practicing gymnastics.

Item_Response: The Missing Circus Horse         'The worst possible event happened!' screamed Laura running into her trailer and throwing herself into her Moma's arms.  'What happened?' Moma asked. 'Papa's favorite horse, Lust, is missing!' Laura cried. 'Oh! That's just terrible! There is no show without Lust. He's the star of our circus you know.' Mama said, pulling Laura close. Suddenly, one of the circus clowns burst into  the trailer. 'The show is about to start Mrs. Cinders. We're all waiting on you.' the clown spoke in a goofy voice. 'Have you no idea that Lust is missing!' Moma practicly screamed.     'Lust is missing!' the clown said, his eyes bulging. ' That's right, and we're not doing the show without him.' Laura snapped. 'I don't know Laura. Not doing the show means losing a lot of money.' Moma said shaking her head. ' What are we waiting for then? On with the show!' the clown smiled, and waddled out of the trailer. 'Sorry sweetie.' Moma sighed as she walked out of the trailer and closed the door behind her.     'Don't worry Lust. I'll find you.' Laura exclaimed confidently. With that said, she grabed her flash light and snuck out of the trailer. The moment she got out she heard rustling in he underbrush. Instinctively she filcked on her flash light and pointed it tward the underbrush.All of a sudden, somebody put a hand over Laura's mouth and draged her into the prickly bushes.     Laura looked up and saw that it was her dad and Lust. 'Papa aren't you suppost to be at the circus, and how did you find Lust?' Laura asked. ' The circus life is so busy that I decided to run away with Lust.' Papa frowned. 'Papa, you could have just told us and we could have stopped our tour. Nobody would mind. All we want is for you to be happy.' Laura said, and hugged her dad. 'Really?' Papa asked. 'Really.' Laura said. With that said, Papa grabbed Lust's reins, took Laura's hand, and walked back to the circus.

Item_Response: The ringmaster has just introduced the dancing elephants. Good. I have seven more acts before my own. I do the math in my head. That leaves 84 minutes before my performance. Eighty-four minutes before I have to step out in front of the thousand-member audience. This is my first performance in front of an audience and yet I am performing the closing act.               My name is Anastasia Ludovic, but I am known simply by my stage name, Minnie. I am a flame swallower and a lion tamer. Since both my parents are acrobats, I was taught circus skills from a young age. I developed an interest in flame swallowing when I was nine-years old. My parents were reluctant to allow me to practice this act, but now, seven years later, I am a professional flame swallower and lion tamer. I learned how to swallow flame while standing upon a running lion's  back. But I had never done this in front of an audience. And, I get stage fright!               But it is too late now. I hear the ringmaster call out my name. 'Now presenting MINNIE!' he yells. I take a deep breath and step out onto the stage.         Twenty Minutes Later        My act has finished. The crowd is cheering louder than a lion' s roar. 'Encore!' they shout. 'Bravo!' I bow and then after several moments more of cheering, I go backstage where the rest of the crew piles on top of me in a big bear hug. I have never been happier.

Item_Response: I work in a circus.   Everbody has their special talent. Whether you have a way with animals or you can put your head between your feet. What ever  talent you have the circus needs you. My talent is the way with animals. I look after all he animals and train them. Claws and fangs are no fear to me. The tigers, leopards and lions all trust me. I can ride the horses and the wind sends a gentle breeze to my face. I reward them with apples and oats. The elephants are easily startled and can be soothed with a touch of silk.       Of course the education is provided for all the children. This is the one time I feel like a normal kid. How boring! No pie in the face, no shows ,no animals. No animals.... . At school we lean what every other kid would learn. Math, English,Science,Forgien languges.       After school, I'm am wecomed back by all my animal friends. i practice my skillls. For example, I practice taming the lions. They roar and swipe at me, but become gentle an timid when I throw them a piece of meat.       At the show, hundreds of people sit waiting for the time of their lifes. The show starts and all I remember is an array of  colours and laughter. It makes me smile.

Item_Response: Have ever seen a circus poster on a billboard? The circus is a great show to watch with your family.Want to go?   But first write a story and win  free tickets. Good luck!                                                                      The circus life         One morning I woke up and got the newspaper.   I saw a ad that said circus auditions today ,so I went to audition. I won and traveled around the world.I even  acted in front of the president. The circus is like my new home.  I have new friends there like the clowns.                We went to Miami we practiced there for a month then the show was tonight.They all did their acts then it was my turn.My act was to walk on a tightrope and land on a horse.Luckily i didn't fall and hurt myself.The show was over and we went back to the trailers.                                            Next,we acted in L.A,SAN FRANCISCO,N.Y.C. It was a lot of fun . We won a world record for most pins juggled.Then we went to Paris.The people there were very amazed.         Then we went home after the tour , and I  enjoyed time with my family.I played with my dog,peanut, he is very playful.The tour was very fun.I hope there's  another tour.

Item_Response: One thing that happens in a circus is acobatics. I think that is the most hardest thing to do because when you are flipping you also have to have balance. Once when I went to a circus when I was little thae lead acroabat had to walk on a tight rope and then jump into a pool of water. When he jumped off of the tight rope he slipped and broke his leg. The fall was like thirty feet into the air. thats why i say it is the hardest.                Anoher thing that is hard to do in the circus is twisting your body. When i went recentlly to a circus with my mom this one group of boys from ages 9 to 17came out. Their names were 'The Bone Crusher Boys. ' They call themselves that becuse they had to twist their bodys around in fuoll curcules while keepin their heads still. On boy came out when it was his turn and he could dislocating his shoulder to twist his arm around and with his hands tied behind his back. his arms went around like 5 times and it didn't even hut him. when their act was over, he showed us how he moved id arms around like that and i was because he could his inner armpit bone pop in and out whithout him hurting himself.                Lastly, the most hardest thing to do is walk on stilts. I say that because the same day I saw the Bone Crusher Boys I saw the people who walk on stilts. One guy had french braids in his hair and he was like 35 years old. He could walk up the stairs with the stilts on and he could jump up and down with their stilts on. Lastly he said you have to have a lot of balance to be on these because the bottoms of the stilts are really small. And that is why I think the Circus is a hard job.

Item_Response: Hi my name is Jessica, I'm 12 years old and my whole family's in the circus and we're all acrobats. Most people think that our life is just fun and no school, no homework just traveling and games in the circus, but no that's nothing like my life at all. I still have a normal life even if I am in the circus.       First of all, I do have school there are other kids on the circus train with me and we have one teacher. between circus acts we have school and homework. Even though I do live on a train I still have lots of responsibility, including taking care of my dog Fluffy and doing my chores.       The circus takes a lot of work including practicing for 8 hours everyday.I have to stretch a lot especially since I'm an acrobat we're the most flexible in the circus. I almost never get any sleep for example, one time we had a circus that went all the way from 4:00 to 11:55 P.M. and I didn't get to bed until 3:00 A.M. Most kids my age have to go to bed at 9:30 P.M. on the school week.       Being in the circus is also very dangerous sometimes. My best friend Meranda is also an acrobat but her parents work with lions. One time Merandas dad was practicing with the lions and one lion jumped back and scratched Merandas dad it wasn't pretty. But luckily he was trained not to be scared so he didn't panic at all, he acted very calm.       Sometimes I get super home sick, I'm from California but I'm only home for about 2 months and im in the circus train for 10 months. I've been everywhere in America on this train. I've never been out of the country for a circus act but my parents said maybe next year the circus will take us to france. My parents and Merandas parents and some other people are on the circus committee.They make all the decisions for us like which state where going next, and they help set up all the circus stuff.       On the train sometimes if we're bored all the kids on train come and we play different games.some of my favorite games that we play are hide & go seek tag. its super fun escpecially since the trains really long we have many places to hide and run.       Now you can see how my life is, its not easy and all fun and games at all. well actually being in the circus is lots of fun but you know what I mean.It takes lots of work, responsibility,  time and trust but its all worth it!

Item_Response: How The Circus Life of Jonny Burrito Started                         Hi, I'm Jonny Burrito and I will explain to you about how my circus life started.                         It all started 27 years ago in a small village called Burritoville. There were circus auditions to join the renown travelling circus called The Burrito Brothers. At the time I was only 7 years old. No person has ever made it into The Burrito Brothers at my age. My special talent was that I could walk on a tightrope.                        I was number 54 to audition. I nervously watched as people were being denied into The Burrito Brothers. My friend Barney was doing an acrobatic performance when he fell of the rope that he was holding on to and came crashing to the ground. He went into a coma.   That injury made me even more nervous.                        34,35,36,37,38,......54.                                     It was my turn. I did not want to go into a coma and i did not want to be denied. I wanted to be the youngest person to ever join The Burrito Brothers. The problem was that The Burrito Brothers did not want very young people to join their circus.                         'Well, are you coming or not 54?' Yelled the director.                          'Y-yes sir.' I stammered.                             As I climbed on to the tightrope I suddenly got butterflies in my stomach as I thought about poor Barney who went into a coma. I put my right foot on the rope and then my left foot and so on.                              I had 3 more steps...2......1.... I made it!!!!! All of the judges were clapping. The director announced, 'Congrats, Jonny. You are the youngest person to ever join The Burrito Brothers!!                                     That was how my career started.

Item_Response: Anyone who thinks circus life is nonstop play is crazy!I,Bella know different now. i live in a big trailer with my family. we travel 20,000 miles in 7 months each year,visiting 150 cities. i work from sunup to sundown. heres a typical day for me                7:00 AM i wake up,get dressed and go to the pie car for pancakes and bacon. the crews are setting up tents,lights, and music for tonight's show.                  9:00AM school time. our one room classroom schoolhouse travels with us. like any school ours has computers, tests and report cards. because the circus preformers are from all over the world, many of my classmates speak italian,french and other languages like my othr family. as we travel around the country, our geography lessons come alive.                   3:30 PM chores and practice i feed,water and groom the horses we use in our horseback acts.           Today, my dad practices somersaulting off a riding horse. im working on leaping on to a horse's back. It takes balance and concentration. Other kids are practicing jubbling or acrobatics. Our neibor walks baby leapords on a leash. Trainers are working with elephants, lions, and chimpanzees.                      6:30 PM Dinnertime! My family and I go to the pie car to eat, but we dont have much time because were preforming tonight. we do 10 shows a week. one each weekday, and a matinee on Wednesday, two on saturday and two on sunday.                 the show is over. Im wiped out. Walking back o our trailer, we passed the circus offices, concession stands, stables, and trailers. two days from now, we will be all set up in another town.                        12:00 AM in bed. Im thinking about the end of our touring season. It will be nice to go back to our real home in Florida. When I grow up, will I stand infront of an audience as a circus peformer like my parents? who knows ? The circus is fun, but its a busy and tough life.

Item_Response: I woke up at the sound of my alarm clcok at 7:00 A.M. I got up and picked out my normal clothing. I changed from my pajamas to my day clothes and went into the pie car for breakfast. I finish my breakfast and rush to the bathroom and brush my teeth. I go and watch the crew set up the tents, lights, and music for tonights show.       'Melanie, shouldn't you be getting ready for school?', Tony, a crew member asks me. I look at the time, and see that it's 8:30.           'Woops! Thanks Tony.', I say rushing to my room and start brushing my hair.       30 Minutes later, it's 9:00 A.M. I rush out of my room getting ready for school. You see our one-room schoolhouse travels with us. Like any normal school, ours has computers, report cards, and tests. Many of my classmates speak languages such as: French, Russian, and Italian. This is because in the circus life, you travel all around the world. As we travel the world, it's like our geography lessons come to life.        Once school is over, at 3:00 P.M. it's a quick break for me. The clowns let me play with their unicycles and juggling balls. I also play with my tiny dog, Noodle. Our trailer is to large for a small pet. I wish I could join after school activities (soccer, football, cheerleading, etc.) But we never stay in one place long enough.         At 3:30 p.m. It's chores and practice. I feed, water, and groom the horses. Tody my dad is practicing somersaulting off a horse. I'm practing spinning off a rope 300 ft. in the air. Everyone says I had guts to agree with doing that trick. (This trick was being postponed until two days from now.) Trainers are working with elephants, lions, and chimpanzees. Our neighbor walks baby cheetas on a leash. Other kids my age are practicing juggling and acrobatics.          6:30 P.M is dinner time! My family and I go to the pie car to eat. We don't eat much because we have shows every night after dinner. We do 10 shows a week. We have one each weekday; plus a matinee on Wednesday, two on Sunday, and two on Saturday.           10:30 P.M. The show is over. I'm tired and need some sleep. In two days from now we'll be in another country. I was hoping we'd go to Las Vegas, in Nevada. But I highly doubt that'll ever happen. I hopped under my covers and drifted to sleep. That night I had a strange dream about my spinning on a rope 300 ft. in the air, trick.                                                    THE DREAM        My palms were sweaty and I turned to face all the people counting on me, to do this trick. My hands gripped the rope. I climbed the rope, to the top and I felt the rope begin to spin. I gripped the rope even tighter with my sweaty hands. I plastered a fake smile on my face to cover up the fright. I saw the crowd cheering me on and my parents, the crew, and the other performers cheering me on aswell. Without thinking one of my hands let go of the rope. My smile was swept off when this happened. The crowds cheers got louder but everyone elses stopped. Everyone but the crowd had nervousness on their faces. I tried to put my hand back on the rope but the rope was spinning to fast. I finally got a grip of the rope with my other hand. I took a deep breath and my palms got sweaty again. I looked down, and that was the moment I realized I was afraid of heights. My breathes were quicker and my heart literally stopped. My hands slipped on the rope and when as I was falling I heard gasps and 'oh no's!' from the audience. The crew, my family, and other performers rushed to the rope. I closed my eyes tight and was waiting for impact. I slammed onto the floor, with a 'THUNK!' then I  blacked out.                                                 REALITY   I woke up sweating. I saw that my family was surounding me. They all looked worried, I noticed that I was crying. I wiped the tears off my cheeks and rubbed my eyes.        'What happened?', I asked, looking up to my family.          'You were crying and sweating. You were screaming in your sleep.', my sister, Alyssa, said still with a worried look on her face, 'What were you dreaming about?'          'I was dreaming about the rope trick. I was dreaming I fell off and I slammed into the floor.', I said, laying back down.           It was Saturday and my family gave me 'It's going to be okay, nothing will happens' before leaving the bedroom. I rubbed my eyes and got out of bed and headed to the pie car. I ate breakfast and went to go look at the rope.       I looked up at the rope and took a deep breath. I climbed the rope up to 300 ft. I looked down and it wasn't so scary.                            ON MONDAY AT THE SHOW           I looked at the people counting on me. This wasn't a dream at all. I sighed and climbed up the rope. I looked down and felt the rope begin to spin. I gripped the rope tighter and felt goosebumps go up my arms. I didn't realize my eyes were closed until I opened them and the crowd was cheering. I did it. I acomplished this trick nobody else would do. Im proud  of myself.

Item_Response: Big change               'Moooooooo.' I grew up on my grandmas farm with cows, pigs, chickens, horses, and cats. Her farm was blue and she had a gray silow about 15 ft. tall next to it. She lived in a big yellow house with a nice big porch for summer days. Being on the farm isn't easy, their are lot and lots of chores to do and you still have to go to school all at the same time. I live alone with my grandma because my parents didn't love me or want me so my grandparents took me in and two days after I got there my grandpa died of a heart attack.                Sometimes when I would have to feed the chickens, I would really swing around on the rope, and do cool acrobatics. I loved doing that kind of stuff, it would cheer me up and remind me of my dream to be in the circus.               One day when I was in my room at 6:30 right before I had to feed the chickens, I heard on the radio from my grandmas room that there was an open auditon to be in the circus. I wrote down all of the information I needed and thought of a plan to get there. My grandma doesn't like the circus, so my plan was to say I was going to just watch, when I would really tryout. I practiced my flips and tricks over and over again till they were perfect.              Finally it was the day, the day of the circus auditions. I asked my grandma if I could go and I was right my plan worked! When I got there, so many people were there I couldn't believe it! My turn was up, I was about to burst into tears and run off stage but I kept my cool.             'Ana dear, the phone is for you and I will allow it since well, you can find out for your self.'             'Coming, and o...k?'             I came to the phone and figured out why my grandma said what she did, I won! Out of 3,789 people, they liked me the best! We packed my stuff because I have to move in with the circus I can't just live at home. For my last day with grandma she didn't make me do any chores, the whole day was just fun and games on the farm. I am really going to miss my grandma, she was the only one who ever cared for me and that really means a lot.             It's my first day at the circus and boy what a busy day I have. First at 7:00 A.M. I have to get up and eat in the pie car (food truck for circus people). Then at 9:00 A.M. I go to school, just because I am in the circus doesn't mean I get to skip school. Inbetween 3:00 P.M. and 3:30 P.M. I get to have a break and play arouond with the circus acts and my friends from school. After that when it is 3:30 P.M. I have to practice my act and do chores. Right before the show I eat dinner in the pie car but not much because we have a show after. When my show is over I am wiped out and ready to go to bed. Finally at 12:00 P.M. I get to go to the trailer and plop down on the bed to fall asleep.            The circus is my dream but I miss my grandma more that anything. Life is really hard without anyone to take care of you and love you. I can't wait for the end of our touring season so I can go home to my grandma and spend time with her.

Item_Response: Its 7:15 at night the moon and the stars are out, and Daphne, Velma, and Jenavee are all still at the circus practicing for their show in three days. Daphne was getting tired so they all started walking home together. 'Bye, see you all tomorrow.' Said Jenavee. ' Bye', said Velma and Daphne. About 5 minutes later Daphne and Velma bumped into a boy named Fred. Fred wanted to be a part of the circus, and since he has been to one of their shows he asked Daphne and Velma if he could join the circus Velma asked Fred if he could come to the circus tomorrow to show them what he could do in the circus. ' Ya, I can.', said Fred.' Great,' said Daphne.           The next day it was bright and sunny outside. Daphne picked up Velma and they started walking to the circus. Fred was there waiting for them.As soon as Daphne and Velma got there they went to the show tent. Daphne asked Fred what he wanted to do in the circus, Fred said that he wanted to be an acrobat. Before Fred started Daphne called the rest of the group over. Right when Shaggy, Zachary, and Jenavee got there Fred showed them what he could do and the group was amazed, so they told Fred that he could be a part of this circus.           The next night at 6:00 they had to perform. First it was Shaggy the clown, second it was Daphne and Fred the acrobats, third Zachery the juggler, fourth  Velma the tightrope walker, and lastly Jenavee with the circus horses Lucky and Corbus. Every one started clapping.           As you can see being in the circus is a lot of fun but being in the circus is also a lot of hard work.

Item_Response: One day I woke up in my trailer, and got up. I made my bed, and got some breakfast. I felt like an anchor was tied to my neck, dragging me down. I had blueberry pancakes, and bacon. I'm always starving when I wake up. The bacon, crunchy, and greasy. The pancakes, letting out the warm smell of berrry.         I got dressed for school, brushed my teeth, tied my shoes, and walked out the door.  Im always moving from place to place because of my scedual.  There are a lot of many kids I have met in my past.  Most of them are different compared to me. Im pale, and others are dark skined.         I went to school stressed because I was always wondering when Iwas going to move to another school because of my shows.  Today we learned a math lesson and it was pretty hard.         I got home, did my chores, took a shower, did my homework, and got ready for the show.  i was really nervous this time.  It's really weird because I've been doing this for 7 years, and I never ever get nervous.  I tried to get somone or something to destract me so i could get my mind off of it.         I got dressed in this ruby red sparkly dress. My mom gave it to me just a few years ago. I put it on, and went on our way to the circus.  I was waiting untill they set it up.  It was my turn to go. I was super nervous. untill I thought to myself, ' I can do this. Iv'e been doing this for 7 years. I can do it .' I got up on the high rope, and did my trick. everybody clapping in enjoyment. I got off the rope when I was done. ' I did it!' I said aloud. ' I did it'

Item_Response: One foggy Summer day, I was at the circus, well because my family owns this circus but, I was getting ready for circus school when I realized that I was late for breakfast. It was 7:45 I was supposed to get up and be ready by 7:30. So I dashed over to the front door and quickly put on my shoes.                    Once I got to the pie cart my food was still steaming hot the way I like it. I ate my food kinda a fast but, then I slowed down because I started to choke.               I walked over to where that beautiful tent was supposed to get put up, and sure enough the crew was right on task. They were setting up the tent, bright shinning lights and some pretty cool music for tonight's show. Soon it was 9:00 it was time for school, so I said my goodbyes and went on my on way.                     When I got to school the fog was starting to clear up I was so happy that the fog was clearing. The school that I go to is a one room school house but the view that we see is just gorgeous. But, like any other school we have assessments report cards, but there is one thing that is different languages but, not me I speak English.          After school my parents lets me go play with my friends. My parents say that I'm in their hair to much, more like their in my hair too much. After I'm done hanging out with my friends I have to do chores. For my chores I have to clean the horses stables and clean them for tonight's show.             When I am done with that my mom and I make the most delicious supper in the whole wide world. After dinner I get my costume on and do my beautiful makeup. And then it is time for the show.                When I get out there I see over one million eyes.              The show is over and I'm going to go hit the the hay!                                                                      THE END

Item_Response: ?A Day at the Circus       'Hello! I am a circus performer who works with horses. Here is a story about the average day at the circus       I wake up today in Tennessee. We traveled there after yesterday's performance. I get dressed and go over to the pie car for my breakfast.We're having bacon and pancakes, which is good, because I like pancakes.       Once we all get our fill, we have to set up the stage with lights and equipment. Then, we work on our training while the kids go to their small-sized school. We also have to take care of the elephants, horses, and all the other animals, along with making sure the equipment is clean enough to use.       We also have lunch in between there, but right now we are having supper. I go back to the pie car for my meal. We only have a little bit for supper because we will be performing afterwards.       When we all finish (which didn't take long, due to our meal size) , we go on stage for the big act. After a couple acts, I come on with the horses. I have them dance around and then I feed them some apples and carrots. Then some riders hop on their backs and I have the horses run around in a circle. My act is done. Me and the horses more off stage and let the other actors perform.       After we're all finished, the audience leaves and we go to sleep. Once I get into my bed, I wish I could tell my family and friends about my great act. I can't do that, though. We don't get to see home very much, so I just go to sleep in my trailer. . . .

I have a couple friends: a clown, another clown, and an elephant. We all play games together. hopscotch, bingo, and dragracing. Yeah we all like t hang out at the pie car.  We all talk about our dream preformer.....THE TIGHT ROPE WALKER! We all want the huge veiw and everything, but the sad thing is... only one of us will get the job... probably the elephant. Than elephant says,'we should practice and the best one will win!.' So that was what we did, practice practice practice. the thing is none of us could do it. So clown #1 got a stick says here so I grab it. Then, I realized it, never trust a clow. all of the sudden it sprays water all over me. and it only felt like water. It was pink paint. Ao thats why I'm in this here tub with pink paint all over my face, not cotton candy from the circus ma'.

Item_Response: Life's a Circus    Source #1      Bella Castini is a circus performer. She travels 20,000 miles in seven months a year. She works from day to night. Here's what she does when she wakes up: 7:00 A.M. she wakes up, gets dressed, and goes to the pie car for pancakes and bacon. The rest of the crews are setting up the lights, and music for their next show for the night. 9:00 A.M. Is school time. A one-room schoolhouse travels with them while they are on tour. Like any other school, this one has computers, tests, and report cards. Many of Bella's classmates can speak different languages like: French, Russian, and Italian. 3:00 P.M. After school, the clowns let Bella play with their unicycles and with their juggling balls. Then, she starts to play with her dog, Noodle. Bella has always wanted to be on a soccer team, but they dont stay at one place long enough. 3:30 P.M. After she plays with Noodles, she feeds, grooms, and waters the horses that are in the show with them.          Bella is working on leaping from a trampoline onto a horse's back. The other children are practicing to juggle and do acrobatics. 6:30 P.M. Bella and her family go to the pie car and eat dinner when their done practicing. They have to do 10 shows a week. 10:30 P.M. The show is over and everyone is tired.  Two more days and then they will set off to another town. 12:00 A.M. Bella is thinking about the end of the tour session. She wants to go home already but the tour isn't over. Bella doesn't really know if she still wants to be a circus performer when she grows up.                                                                       Becoming a Circus Performer            Source #2      Kidzworld spoke with one of the performer about how it felt being in a circus. Her name was Philippa Hayball. She is an acrobat and dancer with Cirque du Soleil's circus show, Quidam. Not just anyone can join the circus, you have to have a special kind of talent. When Philippa was five years old, she was in circus acts already. She did musical theatre and ballet. When Philippa was 11, she knew she just wanted to be a circus performer, so she gave up on everything else and concentrated on her dancing and performing. Philippa has worked all over the planet including, Australia and Japan and all over North America. Circus performers have to travel ont eh road with 100 more people who are in the circus.            Philippa always gets a thrill from performing in front of an audience. She says you can see the audience being transported to another world. There are some drawbacks in being in the circus. Circus performers dont spend a lot of time at home, and they have to work for very long days. When they're on tour, they can't really call anywhere home because they go to a lot of different places. Circus performers are always thinking about the next show. Philippa says that she misses her home and she doesn't see her family that much either. She says that when you're a circus performer, you have to work very long hours and they have to work weekends too.

Item_Response: Living in a Circus                Has your mom ever said to you, 'We live in a circus?' Well my friend Rose knows that a real circus is harder that you think.            On stage, circuses may look like all fun and games, but Rose knows it's not! Her day begins when she wakes up at seven o' clock. She gets dreasses and heads out to the pie care for breakfeast.            She often has typical food for breafeast. She might have bacon, or cereal. At around nine she goes to school. She has a traveling school with kids that don't speak just one language. Since Rose travels to perform at so many countries and speaks many languages. Her school still has tests, computers, and report cards, but its way more fun!            Three o' clock school is over, and she has a short break. She plays with the clowns, then she trys riding their unicycles. Three forty five is when she practrices for the show. She goes over her routine and then wait.            Six thirty. Dinner time! Rose hasn't eaten all day and is starving. However, she can't eat much because she has to perform.            Seven is show time. She does her stunts, and once again, she was nervous for nothing. Ten thirty show's over. And she has to clean up. At twelve shes in bed, fast asleep.                 Rose has a hard circus life, but it must be fun. I wish we could stay together, but she had her crazy, circus life, and I have my normal, life life.

Item_Response: Gustav has wanted to be a trapeze artist ever since he was 5 years old  he practiced by using a pull up bar and lifting weights and by the time he was eleven he could do fifty chin ups in one minute. His mother and father encouraged him to be a trapeze and worked hard always working and swinging.          But when he was seventeen he got his first job as a janitor in the circus each day he would watch the trapeze artists practice gliding through the air.?? But one night after cleaning he climbed up the trapeze ladder and there he was gliding through the air he felt so free and alive. From that point on he did that every night but one night Rita one of the Italian trapezes saw him she thought he was amazing that she told her boss about him she explained how graceful he was and how amazing he looked and from there her boss said to bring him in.           As Gustav walked in he was tense and nervous he knew what he had been doing all these nights after cleaning but he didn't think that his boss knew. He started to sweat so he spit it out and told his boss everything. His boss told him that it was okay and he wanted to see him do it again so Gustav went and did trapeze his boss saw him and hired him right on the spot. Gustav did this every night for 3 years but when he was twenty he left the circus and found a new circus called circus circus h was hired there to. He was working harder each day and then finally it as his big day the day he came to new york city!           He performed his hardest there doing flips and sins and catching the other trapeze artists. That night he as tired and he slept when he woke up he saw his boss and the old circus they wanted him back but then he convinced them to come to circus circus. Now Gustav is one of the greatest trapeze artists ever and still does flips and spins with his partner Frita and he has made Circus Circus one of the greatest circuses on the planet they travel around the whole world showing of there skills such as Gustav and Frita doing flips and twirls and spins and the clowns making everyone laugh and the lions roaring and the lon tamer taming it. The whole circus works hard and they are the most determined. Some other people in the circus would also be clowns, lion tamers, and the acrobats. This is what gstavs schedule would have looked like.       7:00 A.M. Wake up eat breakast  8:00 A.M. Set up the trapeeze stand 9:00 A.M. Practice for 2 hours or so 11:00 A.M. Finish chores which wold be get my costumes ready for tonight 1:00 P.M. Lunch time go to the food truck 3:30 P.M. Pratice flips and catching Frita 6:00 P.M. Dinner time sit down with the circus and eat 6:30 P.M. Show starting get my clothes on 11:30 P.M. The show is finished 12:00 A.M. Going to sleep 1:00 A.M. Drive to the next city

Item_Response: life in a circus                                                     Have you ever wondered what life would be like in a circus? Well I have. there are circuses everywhere! In russia, italy,north america, and rome. You have to travel 20,000 miles every few monthes! That is a lot! There are also many things to do in a circus. Like acrobaticts, juggling, taming a lion, walking across a tight rope, and riding on elephants.                                                         To begin with, I will be telling you about clowns. A lot of kids think clowns are scary, but really, clowns are just there to entertain kids. They don't have to do much, but ride in a little cars which is amazing but still. Clowns are kind of funny looking. Clowns have purple hair, a red nose, a big tie, big shoes, white gloves, a really weird hat, a painted face, and a colorful suit.                               Another thing you do in a circus is acrobaticts. Acrobaticts is way more complicated than most things in a circus. what you do in acrobaticts is two people hang from a rope and swing around and around and around. that really gets the crowd going.what really interests people about acrobaticts is that they want the acrobats to fall down which is really rude. Acrobats dress in fancy clothing. They dress in white. The boys wear pants and a shirt and the girls wear a skirt and a shirt.That kind of act is personaly my favorite. It's my favorite because I like to see people from a high distance.                                The second to the last thing you can do in a circus is juggling. It takes a lot of talent to do something like that. There are many things you can juggle with. there are bowling pins, fire, chainsaws, balls, and metal rings. fire and chainsaws are really dangerous to juggle. thats why I said it takes a lot of practice to juggle amazingly. Its also embarrasing if you mess up. people don't want to see a bad show, they want to see well preformed show. Item_Response: The life of a circus clown         ''Few! What a day, that was a good show Marty. Even with the little elephant incedent.'' Zozo the clown had just finished the show of a circus. Zozo works in the Circus Talents circus. His job is being a funny entertaining clown. His best friends name is Marty, Marty was one of the acrobats. They travel together and perform for the same audiences.         ''Ya, I guess your right. Sure made the croud jump though.'' said a tired and disappointed Marty. Earlier that day in the middle of the show, one of the elephants got a little irrataded because someone stepped on her big soft feet. She had waved her head up and down in the air, and did a big circul around the stadium.          ''You know, I love all the kids and people that come and see us, but being in the circus is a lot more than just fun and games.'' said Zozo.   Zozo was right, not everyone is perfect, performers are just normal people with a dream come true. Right after he said that Marty was fast asleep. Just then Zozo recalled how he first got into the Circus Talents.           When he was a boy all his friends would call him Zozo the clown because his name was Zack. He always made his friends laugh and have a good time. That was his goal in life. Too make kids and adults laugh.   When Zozo started working in the circus, it wasen't such a great life. He had too wake up at 5 am every morning, take care of all of the animals. And worst of all he could only watch from the sides as the other performers did their show.          But afer two years of working super super hard. He was excepted in being a clown. And that was all that Zozo wanted. Too this day everyone enjoyed coming and seeing Zozo do his show and make people laugh, his dream had come true.                                                    The End.

Item_Response: Being a circus preformer sure can be a lot of work! I thought as I groomed the horses, who had just finished practicing for tonight's show.       'Cassidy!' I heard my mother calling. 'Honey, we're heading to the pie cart for dinner! The show is starting soon!'   I run after my mother and father and my sister, Amber, and soon we reach our destination.       As soon as we walk inside, Buddy the Clown greets us warmly.       'Ah, how are you, my dear Hillers? Sarah,' he turned to my mother,'how is your tightrope walking coming along? James,' now he turned to my father and clapped his enormous hand over my father's thin shoulder. 'I've seen you practicing your act where you'll juggle flames. Such perfect timing: tonight's show will be one of our best!'   My father laughed as Buddy removed his hand from his shoulder and now placed it on my head.      'Cassidy, are you excited for tonight's show? I can't wait to see you two somersault off Daisy The Elephant. That must take a lot of bravery!' He patted my head, as if I were a young child. People treat me differently just because I'm younger, but I'm twelve and very far from being the youngest one in the circus. 'Amber, your acrobatics are looking exceptional!' Amber is fourteen, only two years older than me, but she makes me feel as if she were another mom to me.        After we finish eating, we head to the main tent, called the Big Top. We are already in our costumes, and we all wait for the show to begin. My mother ties her long, fiery red hair back. The ringmaster steps out, welcomes the audience, and anounces the first act: James Hiller. Dad steps out into the spotlight and begins his act. At the end, my hands hurt from applauding. His act was fabulous!       Several more acts follow, including my mother and sister, until finally, it is my turn.      I step out into the center of the ring. The audience quiets, completely. This has never happened.      One man in the audience shouts out. 'That kid couldn't be older than nine! I came here to see a circus, not a ballet recital! She's going to get hurt!' Several others shout in agreement.       I hear my mother gasp from backstage. Out of the corner of my eye, I see my father, looking confused.       What is going on? I thought.       The ringmaster attempts calming the audience, but it is useless. 'Let's see your act, little girl! I am in the mood for some Girl Scout presentation.' The audience roared with laughter. I felt the anger boiling up inside of me. 'Ok, I will show you my act! Come on, Daisy!' I signaled for the elephant to come.       'Ok, just like we practiced.' I whispered in Daisy's ear as I climbed on her back. I rembered everything I had learned. I had to show this wild audience I was not a little kid, I was a talented young woman!          I gave Daisy a little kick, and she ran like the wind in circles around a small circular platform, where I will land. I slowly counted down. 5...4...3...2...1...       I remebered everything, even tucking in my chin. I did 6 flips and landed perfectly in the center of the platform.      The audience sat for a minute, speechless, then suddenly everyone, even the man who had called me a little girl, was clapping. I felt nothing but sheer pride and deep satisfaction. Not only had I done perfectly on my act, but I had proved everyone wrong. I was no longer a little girl. I was a confident young woman.

Item_Response: The Circus Story             Hi, my name is Abigale Bulginni and my whole life is a circus. You may think that being in a circus is spectacular, amazing kooky, tops up crazy, and a one in a life time opportunity but it's really not. Here I'll show you.            Having the opportunity of being in a circus is great but to become you have to sacrifice some of the other dreams that you might have. When I was 9 years old I always dreamed that I will become an international singer and when I was 12 I always wanted to be a nurse.            15 I went to the circus. It was amazing! Ever since I knew I had to be either a fierce lion tamer, a daredevil tight roper, or a legendary trapeze artist. When I told my mom and dad about my dream they were full on with me they paid for ballet lessons, track in field, and swimming lessons.            When I became 19 I signed up for the circus. They put me in a dark room with blue curtains and only one little hole window pouring in dim and dusty light. The employ hit a lever (which I guess was the spotlight) and a bright light the shade of lightning hit my face. Immediately I re-flexed my eyes by shading it with my arm. The employ responded ' Bright eh.' I shook my head. ' Well then wait in tell you meet the boss, he's wonderful!' said the employ sarcastically. He then left the room. I suddenly became very frightened. After 10 minutes a man with a purple, green, and orange tucks and a completely bald head came in. He had a snigger on his face making himself look completely dumb. I couldn't help but laugh a little. The man suddenly shouted out ' WHAT ER YOU LOOKING AT BOZO!' I then saw his big fat pigs belly. I couldn't help but laugh again. He began shouting for an hour strait and than he stopped and became silence. Then he said ' Dance.' I didn't do anything in the shock of how he he just suddenly became dumb. He yelled 'DANCE.' I suddenly caught my train of thought and started doing my most recent and advance ballet moves I knew. When I ended I could see he was not impressed. I suddenly thought that my dream would come to an end. ' The names Gogachi Panini kid.' I stopped thinking where have I heard that name before. I then blurted out ' Oh, you mean from The Great, The Fantisimo, Circus DE Funda!' The man shook his head.            After four years when I was 23 the boss died we a had a special funicular for him. 1,562,349 people came! I couldn't believe that that many people would come. I was the first one to bless and give the boss the gift because I was the youngest person in the circus. It was scary but it helped allot of other people lose there fear.           I then took my bosses place of training and riding the elephants and being the master of ceremonies. It was scary at first but I came very fond of it.       Finaly I became 56 when I was the only member left. Charles the acrobat died 2 years ago, Haily the seal trainer left to go on American Idol, Goggie the trapeze artist died 12 years ago, Holly the entertainer died 8 years ago

Item_Response: Hi I am Nadia Deneri and I am part of the Russian Raztac's. I am a gymnast/contortionist. I do all kinds of gymnastics and contortionist things. I love the circus but today was a scary day.       Today my best friend, Safira Exzlen, slipped off her beam and fell twenty feet down, but to my surprise the trapeze artist, Razic Caztiri, swung and caught her right before she hit the net. I ran towards her and saw that the trapeze coach, Yuri Raztac, was clapping and smiling like it was supposed to happen.       I went up to Safira after practice and asked her what she was doing. She told me that when she fell she meant to and Razic was supposed to catch her. I was a little scared for my friend and didn't want her to get hurt doing this new trick, but every time she does a new trick I worry but it always ends up perfectly fine. I said dasvidanya and left.       That night in my head I started thinking of a daring routine like Safira's. I thought and thought and wrote my thoughts down and finally came up with a greatly daring rouine. I would do a front aerial and then and front walkover and the out of the front walkover front hand spring stepout. I would then go to the end of the beam and put one foot on and one foot off the end and from there a backhandspring stepout into a back aerial.       I then thought of more. I thought, finally in the end, I would jump to a trapeze bar and hang by my knees and they would lower the trapeze and I would be about 15 feet off the ground (which would be a trampoline) and I would do a double backflip and land gracefully and bounce off the trampoline and do a front layout bounce back layout bounce front aerial land in a split finnish.       The next day I planned to tell my coach the next day. I told Tariza Raztac, my coach, the next day about the routine and she loved it. She made me practice every detail on every level of the beam. I practiced it on the line, low, mid, and finally high. I then perfected every thing on the trapeze and trampoline. I was doing grand in the eyes of Tariza by the time of the show. When the mattinee comes in four days I'll be ready to perform it. I am so happy I joined the circus!

Item_Response: LIFE IN A CIRCUS          Hi my name is Caroline, I work at a circus. How did I get here you may ask,Well when I was a little girl about 10 years of age, I foud out that I was a brileant gymnist.I started to take gymnastics and my mother and father interduced me to the circus. To me the circus was the best place on earth.There were upsides and down sides like a few weeks into the program I started to miss my parrents alot I wanted to go home but we were to far away.A week latter i reterned home to see my mom,dad,brother,and my dog lucy.The circus is a hard place sometimes.      Some of the upsides of being a circus performer are that you get to have a whole croud of people cheering just for you!You can swing all aroun on the bars with your perfoming partner and you just feel like a little bird fliing high up in the sky.I love being a performer but it shure is a hard job you work from sunup to sundown and don't get me rong you still go to school.This would be a normal day, you wake up go to the food cart get breafast head to the one room school house, but of corse they have computers report card and everything a normal shcool would have.Then school ends and you go do your chores like grooming the performance horeses and stuff like that.A few hours latter about 8:00 the show starts and you try to look as buitiful and as strong as you can up on those ropes as a trpeese artist.Then you go back to your tent and go to bed at about 10:00.Today I am almost 14 I have been in the circus for about four years and I am realy likeing it.Goodbye!

Item_Response: To be a circus proformer you need to have a talent.                  The cirus looks for weird and wacky things, things that they have never ever seen before in their whole entire life. They look for someone who's athletic. Youneed to be athletic to pull off all of the stunts.             Another quallity that you need to have is flexability. You need to be flexable to be able to do all the hard stunts that requier posture and flexability. You need to be able to do stuff with your body that nobody else can do.            Another quallity is strength. You need to be able to big up heavy objects and people with no hustle at all, You also need to beable to hold your self up.           One more is mental strengthness. You need to be able to get up without a pout if you fall or fail a stunt. This is one of the most need quallities that you need.           As you can see, it takes time and hard work and skill and dedacatin to be in a circus.

Item_Response: My Circus Fantasy                                This is my story that never happened. It is about a circus with amazing creatures and people.I hope this caught your attention,because this story might be interesting.I wouldn't know myself,because everyone has opinions.Like my picky sister hates butterscotch,and Tavian hates snake because...wait,I'm getting off topic here!Well,this is a story about a 9 year old who goes to a circus and finds out...ARGH!!!I DID IT AGAIN!Ah,well,here's the story.          Once there was a boy named Jordan CrackleMcPickle,who was short for his age with red hair like fire,literally , red as a red crayon.His eyes were green as a green crayon,wait,why do I keep mentioning crayons?Well,I guess they were.He had no freckles,only on Tuesday ,which meant he had freckles on every day except Tuesday,otherwise he had freckles as orange as an orange crayon..I really need to stop doing this!!!He went to 4th grade in Mrs.Izmint's class.                     One day his parents told him they're going to go to Fizzychew Amusing Circus!They caught a taxi to the village of Villageville,where they got snacks,after paying the driver.The 3 walked to Avinew Avenue.There,they found the circus!!!!!It was as purple as a purple crayon [I've got a problem]with gold ribbons!             There was dragon flying acrobats with sparklers flashing colors of the rainbow!Unicorn riders jumped of in a back-flip on a trampoline,into the air and on tightropes,and then onto a trapeze set!People riding on fireworks the color of blue crayons[what is wrong with me and crayons]into the sky when the explode with the people landing on the mattress pile.Dancing trees and talking dogs!Snake that grow giant with one drop of milk!              Jordan loved the show more than crayons[ARGH]and I would too.They even ate all their snacks and took a picture with a unicorn!They took a dragon ride also!They even bought one of the sparklers!When they left,they never forgot that day.

Item_Response: My name is Katie Spillman and I am part of Bellini circus. Being an Acrobat is really hard but it is worth it. I have to work really hard every perfomances and make sure I don't mess up. Sometimes I have a partner but i usually work alone. I've probably went around the whole world! But it wasn't easy at all!       When I first joined the circus I was not good at all, I mean i could do a few tricks but still i was a rookie. one time when i went up to perform and i fell doing a hard trick. Everyone was laughing at me! I thought i was never going to be an acrobatic again but i practiced more and became way better. After that i relized how careful i had to be. now i always make sure the rope is strong so nothing bad happens.           if you ever want to join the circus you need to make sure you really like it because you are always doing work. i only see my family three times a year but the circus is also my family.You also have to be the perfect fit for your act like if you want to be a clown then you'll have to have good face expessions and don't mind getting a little embarresed.       clearly, Being in the circus is hard and you have to be careful but it is totally worth it.

Item_Response: My friend Grason.He is in the circus.H joined the circus when he was 15.Let me tell you about the time he almost lost his leg.          He once was a acrobat at the circus.The circus bissness was making a lot of money.Lots of people were coming to see the circus.Grason and his friend Josh were both acrobats.After six years of being acrobats they thought we could a dangerous but yet cool trick be they weren't ready yet.          He thought they could swing through a big hoop on fire.When it became are time to do are trick he thought he had butterflies in my stomach.He walked on the platform.When he started to swing he didn't have a tight grip on the tightrope.In the air He tried to get a grip,but his hands slipped off the tight rope and he fell onto the hoop.He tried to get off but his leg was stuck. Item_Response: People say that the circus is just for fun.Well, they are wrong.I, Chelsea Jeffcoat  know how difficult it is.You have to go to school every day but not on saturday and sunday, you have practice your acted everyday, and you have have determination.The circus has to travel 20,000 mils and travel 150 cities ach year.My family drives a van everywhere we go and it has all our stuff.Even our school!The circus has to has special and specific talent.We groom lions and tiny dogs.We ride elephants to.You must have concentration and determination if you are a acrobat or a artist.We work until sunup and sundown.When you are in the circus you have to be kind to others.One reason I love the circus is because I get to meet new people and I love when I put smiles on peoples faces it makes me feel good inside.Acrobats have to practice everyday so they can get there talent right the first time and not mess up during a performenace.One other thing I love about the circus is the clowns.And oh  yeah I forgot to tell in school we have to learn other languages like Russian,Italian,French,and Chinese.We learned about other countries culture and geography about the earth.And yes we have computers,test, and report cards to.One other thing I love to do is ride on th elephant and playing with the juggling balls and play with the tiny dogs.I would love to play sports like softall but since I am on the road and never stay in one place I can't play softball.I promise you one thing the leapords,loins,elephants,and chaimpanzees are hard work to work with must of the they don't want to cooperate at all and it is hard to clean them and give them a bath.That's why I love the circus and I would never leave it eitherand it hard work and plus you can get exsercise too.

Item_Response: The Circus Disaster!                Mary Jane was a 11 year old girl just getting ready to do her circus performance, she was going to ride on her pet lion and leap over a circle that was on fire. She was nervous every past minute as she watched Johnny Lunar do his performance. Mary had a bad feeling but she couldn't tell if she was just nervous or she thought something bad was going to happen. Mary and Johnny were friends about 3 months when Johnny became a circus performer. he was the same age as Mary that's why they were very close friends. The act that he was doing was very hard because it had a use of fire.           When he lite a match to light the rope for his act, BAM!!!! the place caught on fire. The audience were all panic and couldn't get out because the door way was on fire. Circus performers were leaving from the back door leaving the audience, as Johnny just stood frozen solid. Mary was just about to leave as she looked back and couldn't help but leave without trying to help, so she ran back. She ran around looking for anything too stop the fire as she saw a firestingursher. she took hold of it and blew out the fire from the doorway and yelled out 'run out hurry' so everyone did. Finally firefighters came.              Mary was releaved everyone was safe. As she was walking she saw Johnny and ran to him. They talked about how Mary didn't do her act because of Johnny, but all Mary said was 'as long as everyone's safe it's alright'. A few weeks later Mary got to do her performance. at the end everyone applaused for her as she waved for the crowd.

Item_Response: The circus is a fun place.You learn how to saw people in half,walk on coals,and many more things.To learn though things will take a long time of practice.If you want to join the circus you have to learn how to juggle and every thing.         When you join the circus you won't be able to do all the tricks rite away so you may just be picking up elephant poop.You also may just be able to dress up as a clown and throw pies in other clowns faces.         In the circus you have to get up like at 7 a.m every day.You have to get up early to get make up on,your hair done,and you have to get dressed.If you go to school rite after school you get like a 5 minute brake then you have to get dressed for the circus.        In the circus you get to jump off diving boards,jump through firing hoops,and more crazy things like that.A lot of people thing the circus it just all crazy stuff and playing,but you actually have to work a lot to become a expert in the circus.       People join then find out they have to do a lot of work to perform on stage.When people find out about how they have to travel a lot they may miss home,but when they are on stage they forget all about it because they are having so much fun.The circus is very hard but when you get on stage all that hard work you have done goes to work and turns all that hard work into fun.      If you are a expert in they circus you get to swing on poles and let go and some one would catch you.To become a expert only thing you have to do is practice a lot and a lot of practice.But all the practice is worth it.      Everyone likes going to the circus to see people get sawed in half,jumping through firing hopes,picking up elephant poop,and more.The circus is a fun place for the whole family to go to.Its a nice place to watch a shoe have peanuts,popcorn,and a pop.They circus is a amazing place for everyone.

Item_Response: Have you ever been to a circus with real live animals?             If you are wondering what it is like for me to be in a circus, well I will tell you straight off the bottom of my lip. It is really amazing to be around a big crowed, and seeing them smile. I think thats the best part about being in a circus! Would you ever be interested in being in the circus? Well it takes alot of effort for a person to be in a circus. You have to have strength and balance if you want to acrobat. You have to be brave to be a clown, because your in front of a bunch of people. And tons more, but I am here to tell you what I do.       First, When schools over its time for a quick break. The clowns let me play with ther little unicycles, juggling balls, and also their shoes to act like im big foot. Sometimes I even play with our snake,Cheese; but don't worry the snake won't bite! Then it is time to do the things on my list.       Next, It's time for chores. I feed the snake, groom and feed the horses we use in a act.Then check if my costume is ready for tonights show, and see if every body else has theirs too. Last I check to see if every one has their schedual for tonight. The schedual is for the time their on  and everything they need to know for tonight.        Next, Its dinner time. My friends and I eat dinner outside. We are eating chicken, vegtables, and water. We have to stay strong in our body, so no junk food. We can not eat too much, or when we preform tonight our stomach will hurt. Have you ever had cramps in your stomach after you ate alot and jumped around? I sure have, and I do not want that to happen again!       Last, The show is over. now I am in bed thinking of what is going to happen next in my future to come. Working in a circus isn't so bad, it's actually quite fun to be in. Being in a circus is a busy tough life but I know I can make it around when I am with my friends to support me. Well It's past my bedtime, I have to go. Good night!

Item_Response: Hi, my name is Abbi.I am 11 years old and I am a performer in the Amazing Circus! I just woke up and now I am eating the chefs famous  pancakes and bacon! We have it everyday for breakfast, and let me tell you it is delious! I'm one of the many acrobats in the circus and there are about 14 more! It is not a good circus without  a lot of acrobats. Anyway, circus life is hard work. When we don't have a proformance ( we don't have many of those) I practice, practice practice.        Today is another hardworking circus day. The show starts at 10:00. Then we have another one at 4:00. I don't get done working tell 8:00 or 9:00(depends how we do on the show.) I need to go get everything on for today the show starts in an hour. I have my big solo today want to look my best! Getting my costume on is a pain. It is all ichey and unconfortble. In the inside you have to be really carefull not to pull a thred or your costume is done. After your costume is done you get make up done. It is really boring sitting in that chair having them work on your face and it tickles!        Everyone is in the circus ready for the show to start! Ahhhh, i am so exited i can hardly sit still.                                                    SHOW STARTS                                                     PART   2            Welcome..... ladies and gentleman, boys and girls i give you the Amazing Circus! It is almost my part, ahh i cant wait. Got to go it is HERE!!! And now her solo she has been waiting for Abbi Sitte!! I just got on the rope and.....the lights go out i can't see anything AHHHHHHHHH,Why is everything so dissy? Then in a sec everyone in the circus is around me. The lights are on! Then the tent falls down! What are we going to do?        Wait a minite the tent is still up, the lights are on, the sun is up ok that is weird. I go to one of the other acorbats and the show is tonight! I was dreaming! So I still have my solo! I didn't fall!Yea!
