Item_Response: To be in the circus you have to have a certain talent. You have to get up at 7:00 am to get some food before school. At 9:00 am your at school doing test and getting your grades. At 3:00 pm school is over and you do all your chores. By 3:00 pm you practicing do talent. At 6:30 pm you eat dinner and get ready for the show. At 7:30 pm the people in the stands are getting amused sadly at 10:30 pm the show is over and you have to pack up to leave and wait until the next show comes around.           The next show is here and your getting ready for all the bang and roaring off the crowd. you get ready for your act tight roping your thinking to your self don't look down you made it. Here comes the lion tamer which is my dad he tames the lion. here comes my mom doing flips and twists like a string. i watch the elephants do ticks like stand up on their hind legs and have jewels all over them.its the end of the season and that's the last time will be in the circus till next year.

Item_Response: The Circus            Hi! Welcome to the circus I hope you have a great time. I am one of the tightrope walkers here along with many more different people like clowns, acrobats, jugglers, tightrope walkers, horses, and even a lion tamer.        Like I said earlier, I am a tightrope walker I walk on a thin rope that is as high as the sky. I have to walk on the tightrope without falling off of it. You have to have talent to be in the circus. You have to have skills to be in the circus.You also have to have time to be in the circus because the circus takes up a lot of your time.. But, it would be really fun to say '' I am in the circus.'' We travel 20,000 miles in seven months, each year. We also visit 150 cities. I work from sunup to sundown.        So that is the life of person in the circus. It is really fun to be able  to have this opportunity to be in the circus. You should try it someday.You will love it once you start doing it.Well I hope you enjoyed the show.

Item_Response: Loupo the Magnificent       Before the Story   Hello, my name is Loupo the magnificent, I am a leopard from South Africa, and I was brought to the circus when I was one-and-a-half weeks old. Actually, my real name is Loupo, not Loupo the magnificent, and I was actually brought here against my will. I am now two years old, and my first show is tonight.   I am supposed to jump through a sieries of rings, follow simple(and stupid) commands  and ride an elephant in circles. The trainers think that they trained a wild cat from Africa, and they think that they did it all on their own. It's actually the animal's choice to be trained. I only did it because I thought they would hurt me if I didn't. It's hard to live when you're afraid of everything. The only good thing that comes out of the circus, is the meat that you don't have to fight for...       I sat in the corner shadows of my cage, in the cart that has LOUPO THE MAGNIFICENT painted in gold all over it. The spectators stuck their hand in my cart to try and touch me. I growled at them, and they cheered. I actually wanted to just get to the show so that no one could touch me.   The trainer pushed through the crowd with a handful of meat in his hand. I groaned. He opened the little trapdoor and threw the meat inside. I sniffed it, and then licked it, then I took it in my mouth. The trainer stood beside my cage and yelled, 'Behold, LOUPO THE MAGNIFICENT!' The crowd cheered so loud that I put my ears back, crouched low to the ground and groweded fiercely at them. They cheered. Ugh.   One by one, they all dispersed. It was now the evening, and I lay down to watch the sunset. That's when the trainer came up to my cage saying, 'Hello Loupo! Who's my little leopard? Yes, you are! You are...'. One day I would run away escape this embarassing talk. He opened the door and said 'Up!' and I got up with a groan. He slipped the noose over my head and 'led' me out.   There was a long line of animals and acrobats waiting to be called into the tent for their turn. The trapeze artists were first, and as the Ring Leader called them in, they danced inside as the crowd clapped. Next were the Poodles and Jack Russel Terriers. They did their part: balancing on balls and jumping rope. Next were the acrobats, and they did tight-rope walking and flying across the cieling. I never cared much for the acrobats, they were always bragging and showing-off and telling everyone what to do and where to go. Then there were the circus horses, then the bears, then the elephants and elephant riders. Then the clowns and dancers, and then there was me.   As the dancers finish their show, the Ring Leader called: 'And now, for the show you've all been waiting for, the wild cat, wrestled from Africa, tussled and trained. The cat that has become a world-wide star! I give you, the marvelous, the magnificent, LOUPO!' That's when the trainer loosened my noose and shoved me into the ring. A clown ran up behind me hollaring, and I did what we rehearsed: Act afraid and run up onto the platform. The crowd cheered. Then the Ring Leader called, 'And now, the magnificent Loupo will perform his first trick: the hoops!' Several clowns pushed up some rings in front of me. I slumped off of the platform and walked through the hoops as they wanted me to. The crowd went wild. Then the Ring leader said, 'Now the magnificent Loupo will follow my every command!' He faced me and said, 'Sit!' So I did as he told. The audience clapped. 'Roll over!' I rolled over. The audience cheered. 'Dance!' I stood up on two legs. The  audience hollared. I felt more pathetic than I ever have been before. Then the Ring Leader said, 'And now, Loupo will achieve the impossible! Loupo will train an elephant!' Then in walked Brophy, the elephant. He did what he was told to do: act wild, act angry. I did what I was told: Growl at him, and pretend to scare him. He did what he was told: Lie down when I growled, and whimper. I did what they wanted me to do: I climbed on his back. He did what they wanted him to do: Stand up and walk in circles. I guess we both felt stupid, but the audience loved it.   When the show was over, I was led back to my cage. I was upset, and angry. About 10 seconds after I lay down, the audience had crowded around my cage. Whooping and Hollaring and sticking their hands in to touch me. This was going to be a long night.   It was about midnight, and everybody had gone back to their trailers, all except the Ring Leader and the trainer. This was their conversation:   Ring Leader: 'So, are you excited?'   Trainer: 'You bet. It's not everyday that you get to train two new leopards.' Ring Leader: 'What are their names again?'   Trainer: 'Ocapoco and Lucapaca. They're going to be in the backround of Loupo. The manager said that the show would bring in more buyers if Loupo had backup.'   Ring Leader: 'But we could barely fit these people in the tent, how are we supposed to fit another thousand?'   Trainer: 'No idea.'   Ring Leader: 'When are they arriving?'   Trainer: 'Tomorrow.'   Ring Leader: 'Oh, well. Good luck.'   Trainer: 'Thanks.' That is how their conversation ended.   Well, the next day there was a lot of buzz. I guessed it was about the two new leopards. Two other cages were attatched to the back of mine, one was painted in silver that said, LUCAPACA THE AMAZING and another blue one that said OCAPOCO THE EXOTIC. The two leopards arrived cowering and bloody.       It took two months for them to heal, they were pretty traumatized. When we first started rehearsing together, it was odd. They wouldn't cooperate and they always would cower behind me whenever someone scared them. I had much pity for them.   In the days that passed there was a lot of disorganization, and it was because of Ocapoco and Lucapaca. Ocapoco got loose, and Lucapaca would snarl at anyone who came near her. I followed their examle with going on strike. First I wouldn't follow any of the trainers commands. Then I would do a Lucapaca and growel anytime someone came near, and I even learned how to open my cage and do an Ocapoco. We went that way for weeks, not once having a show, and Ocapoco and Lucapaca were greatful for my strike. We nearly drove the trainers, acrobats, managers, and advertisers mad by going on strike. As a result, this is what happened:   It was day 47 of our strike, and the trainers were afraid to come feed us, but we just kept our strike flowing. Then one day, the trainers finally gave us some food. We ate it, only to find that there were sleeping pills inside. We slept hard, and when we woke up, we were in crates on a plane. The younger two were scared, and so was I. Then, the trainers opened up the door. They hobbled in, for it was bumpy in the back of the plane. They gave us some more meat, and we were too hungry to even consider that there might be pills inside...idiots. The second time we woke up we were in the same crates, but we were in a car, not a plane. It was hot outside, and the road was bumpy, light streamed in through the few holes in our crates. There was a weird sence of home here, though I could not put my finger on it. Then, the car stopped. Our crates were put on the ground, and they were opened, and I knew exactly where I was: South Africa. I bolted out of the crate and I just kept running, running into the warm sun, running into the long golden grasses of home. I could hear Ocapoco and Lucapoca behind me, but I kept running, I was rinning home.

Item_Response: Hi, my name is Jenna. I have a story for you. When I was young...I wanted to be in the circus, so when I was five I did ballet. I ended that when I was 10. When I got home I got out my backpack. My mom, she was coming! What am I going to do? I put my backpack under my bed, the door handel was slowly moving. My mom yelled to me 'Do your homework' I said 'Ok'. I got my backpack out I got everything I needed. At 8:00 my dad said 'bed time'. At 9:30 I got up, I was out the door in a second.       I ran away, I got to the circus tent in town. I told the people 'I want to be in the circus'. They all said 'We do need someone new'. I was in the circus! That morning we left town we were off. I loved all the nature that went bye. We were in the next town in a week. There was a leader his name was Zoco. He asked ' What do you want to be?' I said ' If I could have a job it would be to work and train the elephants and do a horesback trick'. He said ' Ok'. He put us in partners. My partner was Zoozoo. Over the years Zoozoo made me awsome.       I was 13 years old I was very sad I didn't have a family. We were going to my old town I ran once we got their, I looked for the little red house I opened the door and yelled 'Mom, Dad'. They both ran and I showed them I loved them. After that I told them the whole story. The End.        Thank you for the graet time I had. I hope you liked it.

Item_Response: My Day at the Circus       It is a busy day at the circus we have to do a lot. The circus is crazy most of the day everyone's running around trying to get everything ready.       7:00 A.M.-I wake up, get dressed , and I go to the food cart to get bacon and eggs. The crew is setting up the tents, lights, and music.       8:30 A.M.-I go to school in one of our many trailers with some of the other kids that travel with their parents. We have computers, progress reports, and tests. Some of my classmates speak foreign languages.       2:30 P.M.-I have to practice and finish my chores some of my chores are grooming, feeding, and watering our horses and our dogs too. I am practicing flipping off a horse and then jumping off a trampoline onto an elephant.           7:30 P.M.-I am eating dinner with my family we eat some chicken and vegetables. It is good, but we don't eat it all because if we do our performance won't be the best.           8:30 P.M.- The show started My dad goes on first he perfects every stunt. Now it's my turn I landed my stunt. Everyone else did great I can't believe it. Yeah!       10:00 P.M.- The day is over the performance want great. Tomorrow will be a whole different adventure. I love traveling in the circus. Then after the circus I go to my trailer after a tiring day.

Item_Response: I look out into the crowd.  There has to be over 1,000 people out there. Its my first time ever doing a circus show. I walk to my trainer and tell her im very nervous.  'You've done this correctly every time we have practiced. You wont mess up I promise.'  My act in the show was a tightrope walker. It took me over 2 months to learn how to tightrope walk wihtout falling off.        I heard my act being accounced. I was the first act.  I walked out slowly and nervously to the tightrope. I walked a little faster.  I wasn't nervous the times we practiced, but now theres an audience and i'm sure ill mess up.  I climbed the ladder leading to the tightrope and waited about 10 seconds. I knew I was going to fall off but i had to try.       I had to remember the good things about walking a tightrope.  There was a net under me so if i fell off i wouldn't get hurt.  I realized i'd been standing at the top of the ladder for about 2 minutes.  I didn't want to keep the audience waiting.  I slowly started walking along the tightrope. My heart was beating very fastly.  I started to get cold chills.       I looked at my trainer.  She looked very nervous and I really didn't want to let her down. I realized I was alittle more nervous about this than I should be.  I started walking confidently along the tight rope. I'd gotten halfway through without falling. I suddenly noticed something in the middle if the tightrope. There was a tear in the middle of the tightrope. I knew if i stepped on it the tightrope would break.       I walked carefully towards it.  I stepped over it thinking it would break. Even though the net was under it, it still kind of hurt when I fell because the net was scratchy.  I walked over the tear in the tightrope and it didn't break. I carefully made it over to the other side. Everyone started cheering and I felt very proud of myself.  I looked at my trainer and she looked very proud too.

Item_Response: Life in the Circus           Life in the circus is fun. the downside of it is that you have to always stay away from your home. that's not fun at all. In the circus you get to dress funny , like a clown. You can juggle, ride a horse , it doesn't matter just as long as you are having fun doing it.        You may have a special talent. Acrobatics is a great talent to see. people hanging from ropes , chains, even by just hands and feet. Juggling is fun once you get the hang of it. trowing up more than ten thuings in the air is an exciting scene.         Tightroping is thrilling. someone is always scared you will fall , but that generally doesn't happen at the circus.          People will train for months doing these stunts until they get them perfect. Not all stunts have to be of the ground, you can be a clown, ride a horse, be a comedian, or any of those things really.           The circus is fun to see. Don't ever be afraid to chase your dream. If you want to be a clown , be a clown . Whatever you want to be it.

Item_Response: Hello, I am Mystic Cabaret and I travel with my circus family around the world. I work from sunup to sundown and I devote myself to become a performer even though I am only 11 years old.                 Every day I wake up a 7:00 A.M. and do what everyone does: brush my teeth and get dressed. Then I go to the pie car for my breakfast of pancakes and bacon. Currently, the crews are setting up tents, lights, and music for tonight's show.                  At 9:00 A.M. I go to our circus's one-room schoolhouse to learn. It has everything a school has. For example computers, tests, and report cards. Because my circus travels around the world, I have many performers that speak different languages from me. Our geography lessons come alive when we travel.                    School is over at 3:00 P.M. and I have a short break. The clowns usually allow me to play with their unicycles and juggling balls. I want to have a large pet, but our trailer is too small. Even though I love my life as part of a circus family, I sometimes want to join the swim team. However, we don't stay at one place long enough to.                     After 30 minutes, it's 3:30 P.M. and I have to do my chores and then practice. I feed, water, and groom all the horses. Today, I plan to practicing my tricks with the horses.                     At 6:30, I eat my dinner in the pie car. However, we don't eat much because tonight we are going to perform. We usually do 15 shows in one week.                     After the circus's performance is finished, I flop on to my bed and go to sleep, dreaming about what I am going to perform next. This is my life as a circus performer, and I am proud of it.

Item_Response: Those that think that circuses are all fun and games don't know what they are talking about. I, Josh Camp, would know better. I am a lion tamer in the Kidzworld circus.       Here is my typical week.       Monday:  Wake up and go to the pie car to get breakfast. Then go to the school car. Most of the kids there are from all over the world, but we actually get to learn each other's languages. I currently know Spanish, Korean, Japanese, French, and English. After school I have a little free time, so the clowns let me play on their unicycles, as long as I don't break them. I do this part every day. Then our special Monday performance is what I like. we do our trapeze stunts, the sword-swallowing, and then I come out with Bernard and Fabia, my two lions. We do our famous human/lion totem pole.       Tuesday:  Wake up and go to the pie car for breakfast. Then I do the usual for weekdays: school, play, and practice. Tuesdays aren't my favorite days because I'm stuck with clean-up, but it's actually pretty fun.       Wednesday:  Wake up and go to the pie car for breakfast.Then I do the usual for weekdays. Wednesday is my favorite day of the week, because I get to perform for our normal performance, as well as our Wednesday matinee. Bernard, Fabia, and I do our totem pole, as well as our famous double ring jump.       Thursday:  Wake up and get breakfast. Then the weekday usual. We have one performance, and it's the trapeze performance, so I'm stuck with setup and cleanup.       Friday:  Get up and get breakfast. Then the weekday procedures. We have no performance tonight, so I just relax and enjoy the scenery.       Weekends:  Wake up and get breakfast. We finally have no school, so we get to mess around until about 4:00, when everybody performs three times each day. Once I get home, I'm wiped out and ready for bed.

Item_Response: Life in a Circus                                                                                   As an ordinary day I always need to wake up early for the show. I usually wake up earlier but on today's show not that many people are going. Its time to go eat egg,bacon, and pancakes from the food car. After, we start to set up and get ready for the show. Item_Response: Circus can be fun. People have to do certain jobs and there is a lot of  them like grooming, pie car, and matinee. I am going to talk adout how it s to work at a circus.           First, the people who uses animals in their proformence has to groom the animals. Groom means to clean and brush the animals. If they dont groom yhe animals, they would be stinky. They also have to feed the animals. If they dont feed the animals they woudlnt be able to do their performence because the food gives them the energy they need.            Also, the proformeres have to eat. They eat at the pie car. It has pie, pizza, and ect. If they dont eat a great meal they will be hungry during their proformence. The proformers needs a lot of energy, if they run out of energy they would be tired during their proformence. That is why they have to eat a good meal.             Lastly, when the proformers are done with their proformence, they are wiped out. Wiped out means to be very tired. When they are done with their proformence the go to the pie car to eat because they be so hungry and tired. They have to get up really early in the morning to get ready to go to the Circus. They barly have enough time to get some rest they need.               As you can see, beaing in a Circus is a lot of work. You have to travel 20,000 miles. Some people in the circus are use to it because they probally worked there for 20 years. They have to wake up early in the morning to get to the Circus. If the performers are using animals in their proformence, they have to groom them. If they dont groom the animals they would be stinkyand all. They have to eat  good meal so they wouldnt be hungry during their proformence. They need energy so they dont be wiped out. Circus can be very fun.

Item_Response: Have you ever thought how life is in a circus? Its really fun and not so fun at the same time.Circus performers, get to travel around the world which can be fun and tiring.Some people that work in the circus have fun while others don't.           These are reasons why some people like to work and live in the circus. They  have fun because they get to work with animals.Trainers work with elephants,lions,and chimpanzees.Some tricks they do are somersaulting off a running horse,or leaping from a trampoline onto a horses back.The kids juggle and do acrobatics.They like doing that because its entertaining.Another thing that make people like the circus is because they travel around the world.Traveling around the world gives an opportunity to meet different places and different people.            These are some reasons why some people don't like to work and live in a circus.The circus is a busy and a tough life.They have to wake up early, at seven in the morning, and sleep late.Circus performers work long days and spend a lot of time away from home.On tour, They don't have anywhere to call home.Circus performers, don't see their family that much.They have to work long hours and weekends too.Although for some people the circus is fun, for others its difficult.               As well as the circus performers like and don't like the circus, they can learn new things.When they travel to different places, they get to learn about that place.They learn the culture and the celebrations that place has.This can be an advantage for the circus performers.When the circus performers travel to different places, they can visit their family that lives there.                 Those are some reasons why circus performers like and don't like being in the circus. Just because being a circus performer might seem fun, for others its frustrating and difficult. If the circus performers don't like the circus or if they do, they get to travel and learn new things from different places that they have never seen or been before.

Item_Response: Working at the circus is both hard and easy. Some people think it is fun to work at the circus, but they don't know it is also difficult.  We asked Ally to tell us about the circus.           In the circus their are clowns, juggling, acrobats, a tightrope walker,and even horses. When you come in a circus you see all these amazing things that you think you want to be in the circus oneday, but what you don't know is that  behind those curtains people are practicing a trying to  do the best to intertain the audience. All of this starts in the morning. 'In the morning everyone gets wakes up gets dress and goes to the pie car to eat breakfast. Then the chidren go school while the parents or adults stay  and practice. In school the children go to school to learn laguages  and to learn  things about the city they are traveling to.'           ' In the afternoon the children get out of school and go to practice and do chores.   Everyone at the circus works really hard and they are trying to do their best preformance every. After practicing they go to have dinner at the pie cart. No one has a big dinner since they are going to preform.          When show time comes the preformers put their outfits on and then the show begins. Once the show begins the magic begins. Everyone  is  quite.'  Ally enjoys preforming in front of people. She always has a smile when she  faces the crowd. When the show is over  she is really tired.          ' The circus  is a very great place ,but it is sometimes hard', says Ally. The circus is always filled with excitment.

I'm here to tell you about the ways of the circus. I'm a stuntman, but that's not close to all the cool stuff    you can do at a circus. The circus is a place where dreams of some come true. There are many types of jobs as I said earlier.  For an example acrobats can be something you might like. As I was a kid, I would love to watch the circus's performances. Now I'm what I always wanted to be and anyone, even you can make your dream come true just as I did. You can be a juggler, tight rope walker, clown, animal trainer, a stuntman like me ,but that's not all there is to a circus, there's plenty more to explore!                                                                                                                                                                                 When you come into a circus, be prepared for what awaits you because it's not all that easy, you have to really want it, you have to strive. Item_Response: Hi,my name is Shambri and I am a circus performer!   I am a acrobat.I love what i do but let me tell you that it took a lot of hard work and effort to be able to be in the circus.I started when  was young and if you want to be in the circus i recommend that you start when you are young its a lot easier to start your career.   Many people think that being in the circus it all fun & games but it is not.We circus performers work very hard and practice for a very long time.Also because of all the traveling that we do while we are in the circus you don't really have time to  see our family when we have a break we enjoy and treasure it very much.I have to practice my tricks and moves everyday but it is worth it when you get out in the ring or as for me get on the bars and start to move the audience almost seems like its moving with you doing the tricks right beside you.Almost as if the audience is there to catch you if you fall.Like you will always be safe and the sense that you get when you nail a perfect new move!being in the circus is a lot of fun but hard work also.    I started as a dancer we learned lots of flips and tumbling that came in handy when i decided to start gymnastics.I found a love for gymnastics and also found that i was amazing at it i won competitions and could do many different moves.When a circus directer asked me to join i was overwhelmed with happiness,but my family didn't agree.It took a lot of hard work but i finally got them to agree.Now my family is very supportive of what i do,and i will always treasure them because if it weren't for them i wouldn't be here doing what i love and it took a lot of courage in your daughter to let her move away forever so she could fill her dreams.   I don't know if the circus is right for you because not everyone likes that lifestyle,but if your interested go for it and just remember the circus will always be there for you!

Item_Response: Circus Life                                     I am Elizabeth Mincen. Though circus life can be hard and tough, it is fun at the same time.                             A day at the circus is very tiring. I work all day with the rest of the people in the circus. Every week, I perform 10 times. Due to this, I practice and practice. One upside about working in a circus is you get to travel to many different places you have never been to before. The circus gives many people an opportunity to go to so many different places and meet so many different people. There are many good things about working in circus but there are many bad things as well.                                           Though many people think that working in a circus is easy, working in the circus is really not all fun and games. You have to work long days and you don't really spend too much time with your family. You can't call home either because it all just comes back to the fact you don't have much time. Before you join a circus you might want to think about the very fact that you will be away from your family.                                  There are many things to think about before you join a circus. It's not as easy as you think it is.  Would you like to go to school in a moving vehicle? Well, if you work in a circus you will work in a one-room schoolhouse. It's like any ordinary school, with computers, tests, and report cards, it's just that you will be in a cramped place, studying. After school, it's break time. But that's the only free time you will have for the rest of your day. Then, I usually go straight to chores and practice for the show I will do at night. Finally, it's show time for me. Though I am really scared I am happy at the same time. I tried my very best and now the show is over. I am tired and ready to go to bed.                                 I think that working in acircus can be hard but it is very fun at the same time. I put a lot of thought into joining the circus, and now I think I made a fairly wise decision. Though I sometimes feel that working in the circus is very tough, I really enjoy it.

Item_Response: We have just finished a show and we are starting to take the tents down. I am exhausted because I had to handle the animals. This is usual for me because I work in the circus and the circus life is crazy. I went back to the trailer which we live in. We are on our way to Chicago for our next show. It is 9 AM right now so it is school time. In the circus, the school is the same as any other school. Now, I have a quick break so I go to where the animals are. I play with Bubbles, our chimpanzee. I have to go and work with the animals, now that the break is over.         I went to see Bubbles but she wasn't there. I panicked, I searched everywhere but I could not find her. I had to talk to my boss but when I did I was surprised because he was not mad at me. He said that this has happened before and that he was pretty sure where she was. I followed him and he took me under the trailer where I saw a hole that I had not noticed before. When we looked into the hole she was not there. My boss was speechless, this was his prize monkey and now it was gone. He said that if I don't find out where she was he would fire me. After he went back to his office, I went to my bed and thought hard. Where could she be? I asked myself.       When I went back to the animal tent, I found a note that I hadn't noticed before in Bubble's cage. It said that I had to pay 80,000 dollars if I ever wanted to have Bubbles back. I told the manager abot this and he called the police. The police found fingerprints on  the note and found out it belonged to the former animal handler which I replaced. My boss said that the former animal handler was mean to the animals and was greedy so he fired him. Also, he wanted revenge against me because he thought of me as an enemy. When I was in the university, I was the best at everything and he was second best. He always tried to be first but I always did something creative. I kind of remember him but its been a long time.       Once the police got his address they put him in jail for theft. We had a celebration after our show to honor me for finding Bubbles, our star. Every month I went to talk to the former animal handler and soon we became friends.

Item_Response: The Circus Life            I love working in the circus. I am a circus performer and I am a tight-rope walker. People ask me wht is so fun about going to unknown lands, moving alot, and having a job where you could break your neck. I'n just about to tell you why!            One reason I like woking in the circus is becuase of everything I get to see. Since the cirus I work in travels global, I have been to nearly every part of the world. Just think about it. One week, I wake up in the Niagra falls and then next week I am in Manhattan! I have also seen all the seven wonders of the world.            Another reason why I love the circus I live in so many unique places such as Austrlia, India, China, Costa Rica, Rio de Jañero, Africa! I see new animals, places, and I meet new people. I bet you don't get to do that!            Some people ask me, ' Aren't you afraid of falling of that high tight-rope?' Well, actually, once you develope the balance, Tight-rope walking is like riding a bike. And it is super fun to walk high up and look at everybody watching me below.            Working in a circus is fun because you see new places, you live in new places and you get to take fun risks.

Item_Response: The Circus Life           Raghav was walking over the tight rope. He was really excited and encouraged to cross the rope an the other side. Everyone was cheering for me I did not want to let them down. Hi I am Raghav, but everyone calls me RAGS. Being a circus tight rope man is very exciting.                The good part about being a tight rope man is that you get to have a lot of hard tricks and you get to stay with your family. The food is your choice. You can see your neighbors and watch them do amazing tricks. No need to go all the way to a circus to see everyone. You are getting the behind the scenes look that no one else gets except the other circus people and the manager. I went to the second show and I was about to fall of the tight rope, but the people cheering me on were encouraging me. 'It is not over until the crowd stops cheering' is what I say. Item_Response: One early morning in Mexico a girl named Jackie was born.Her mom spent most of her time practicing for a circus every single day. When Jamie got older her mother started to teach her life in the circus.At school she alwase talked about circus things,like working,food,and all the stuff they have to be able to do to become an amazing circus performer.On Jackie`s seventeen Birth-day her mother took her to the family circus.Jackie`s mom said she could be in the act next week.Jackie practiced over and over.In the morning mom woke her up very early.She said 'get up its time for breakfast'.She got up and went to a little cart wear they served bacon and pancakes.Then after she rested a while she went to comb the horses she loved that job but she new there was much more than that.Then later she practiced magic and juggling.Her dad came to visit her she has not seen her dad in a long time.Then the show was about to start she could hardly wait to go out there and show her amazing talents.Jackie got her unicycle and she went out after her uncle said'Our new and talented 17 year old....JACKIE!!!         She loved to hear her name said by her relatives who love and appreciated her.She got her unicycle and ran on the stage.She was great she did a back flip of the unicycle,on top of a trampoline then she jumped on a pole and swung herself around.Everyone was amazed a 17 year old could do all those things at once.After the show the audience went wild the were crazy and they just loved her act.Then Jackie took a break and she ate dinner and she spent some time with her relatives for a few hours,then she went to bed thinking of what the audience is going to think next week`s circus.        All in all Jackie had control over the circus when she turned 21. She passed it down to her kids and her kids past it down to their kids.They all reacted the same way Jackie did,happy confedence and hard working. :)

Item_Response: I, Valina Scott have been in the circus since I was seven years old. I first started off as a baton thrower. Now in the present I am 17 and an acrobat. Life in the circus is tiring. You need to wake up really early, Then you need to start practicing for the next show. We practice from the time we wake up until lunch then, after lunch we practice more. Once its dinnertime and dinner is finished we wait until the next show. Around 7 o'clock we crowd in to the circus tent. The clowns paint there faces, the baton throwers get there batons, The acrobats do warm ups and the lion tamers get there lions. By 8 o'clock we're ready to start the show. We walk into the clearing and we look at the happy faced audience and we all smile for there gratitude.                 'ALL UP!' The lion tamers yells as all of his lions stand up. The lions gather in a circle.                 'READY!' The lions wait for the Que. The lion tamer throws a ball in and the lions bounce it to each other. One little rebel of a lion decides to sneak off. The crowd gasps in horror as the lion starts to walk the tightrope.                 'SOMEBODY SAVE THE POOR LITTLE LION!' A little girl from the crowd screams. All of us turn around to see the little lion struggling to get across. Peter our tightrope walker jumps on our super-duper-bouncy-jiggly trampoline he lands on the tightrope. He pushes the lion off of the tightrope to the trampoline. The lion is safe! Everyone sighs letting there stress be relived.                   We continue our show the tightrope walker started walking on the tightrope. The baton thrower did there skit.                  It came time for me to do my skit. I started to do the acrobats but I failed. I started to fall and I thought of a quick plan.                     'I NEED A TRAMPOLINE!' The lion tamer heard me and put a trampoline on the bottom of me. I dropped on the trampoline safely.                      By the time the show ended it was 10 o'clock and I was tired. I lay my head on my pillow and dazed off into a endless sleep. I had a dream of the show awaiting tomorrow.

Item_Response: A Beautiful Day At the Circus by Jayia Clemons                There are four siblings that live in Duarte.Their names were; Tiaunna, who had a twin named Kiauna, Daniel, and Biaunca.They had a friend named Tiffaunnie.I was their cousin. They all loved each other the same.Then one day they saw a banner that said, '' Circus in town, See it Today!''.Then they knew at once they had to see it.Then there was one problem.Biaunca was afriad of clowns!They tried to make her over come it by having a clown come to their house.She didn't come out of her room.Then when she came out they told her how nice they were by having it give Kiauna and Tiaunna a flower and it worked.I did n't sleep over because I don't like clowns.           While the others were geting dressed Tiaunna and Kiaunna and I snuck into the circus to see the training.We saw acrobats,lions,leopards,and the ringleader.We saw how tough it was to be be in a circus and went back home.While we were walking home we saw a banner that said the show wasn't until the next day..When we came back to the house they got dressed but told them the news.They just shrugged put on a movie at some candy, icecream ,and popcorn and went to sleep.           The next morning we woke up and at breakfast.The show didn't start until 5:00 P.M.We had seven hours to spare so we went shopping,bought fast food,went to the park, babysat our baby cousin Cayleigh down the street, and finally it was 4:00.At 4:30 we first dressed their baby cousin then ourselves.We were all ready at 4:50 and went to the circus. We got lemonade, hot dogs, ice cream, popcorn, and candy.           Since we were a little early they got to meet some of the people before they did their acts.They even took many pictures with them.They got to ride an elephant too.By then it was time to get our seats.Before we went offstage the teams told us to come back after the show to spend more time with them and we said 'okay'.       The acts were more than what they expected.They saw the lion do tricks,the acrobats doing things they never seen not even a gymnast do,they saw clowns on unicycles and more.At the end they did something really special they never did before.Even I Jayia saw it myself because I was there.They told us to come on stage during the show and they said it really loud!We ended up doing a magic trick that we didn't even attempt to do.At the end of the show we thanked them a lot and hoped to see them again.Then I came up with a good idea!I told them,''come to the pool with us tomorrow'' and gave them the address.The next day thay showed up and we all had fun.When we came in the house we went on the computer and saw our pictures online to the world,then we turned on the t.v and were on the news! I will never forget that time.

Item_Response: Hello my name is Adreanna Richardson and I am 12 years old in the fifth grade.I attend Baskerville elmentary.I have two siblings one is a girl and one is a boy.I have a mother and her name is Tamika and I also have a father his name is Marcus.We love each other equally and the same amount.                  I have two teachers thier names are Mrs.Kirby and Mr.Jordan.I love to go to school to get an good education so I can go to an university or college as long as I am in school while im in my teen years.                                 If I had a mother and a father that were circus people that means that would like to attend the circus and  acually took place in one or even live in one it would take practice and we propbably would never get to have family time like go to the mall and go to a fancy resurant and eat out.                                     I would not certainly want to live in a trailer either because a house is much bigger and can hold heavier things like the bed, dresser, oven, dryer and all of those good things would maybe make the tires of a trailer burst and also a some houses do and do not have wheels on them.                       At the very end of the day I would be very tired and stressed out from a long day at practice and performing and school and you have to have a specific talent the right body type in determined that you will join the circus.                       This is my whole day schedule what I do and what time I get up and I also go outsid efor a few minutes with my friends and then I go back in the house and eat dinner with my family:               5:00am-wake up,get dressed   6:00am-eat breakfast   7:00am-watch the world news   7:30am-be at the bus stop   8:00 at school   3:15pm-out of school   4:00pm-getting dropped off at home   5:00pm-do homework   6:00pm-dinnertime   7:00pm-watch alittle bit of TV   8:00pm-take a bath   9:00pm-watching a fanalie   10:00PM-in the bed wipedout                          THE END OF ADREANNA RICHARDSON                        AMAZING LIFE STORY

Item_Response: Hello, have you every even throught about becoming a circus performer because if you have maybe you should try it.But if you would try it good advice would be to start while you are young so that you can be exceollrnt at it when you get older.(if you decide to countinue)Now im going to talk about some,                                              RESPONSIBILITIES                                         ____________________         (1)BEING TO WORK ON TIME!        (2)PRACTICING WHEN YOU ARE AT WORK!        (3)FOCUSING AT WORK!         (4)DOING YOUR BEST WHILE ON STAGE!        (5)PRACTICING WHEN YOU HAVE _EXTRA_ TIME!             Now if you think you arent gonna practice because you THINK you ALREADY know the rutein well then there is a way you can get FFIIRREEDD!!!!!!!!!! because you are suppose to pracctice until it is time for you to get on that stage.       Also im gonna talk about what you do at the CIRCUS NOW DONT GET IT WRONG!!!!! you do not sit around at work and clown around all day or else ill work at the circus but you dont you may clown arown for about 30 min. then its back to work!!!!!!!!!!!!!!  But the you do while you at the  circus is practise for about 3 to 4 hous then  travel to the place you are performing then that will be your time to laugh and joke but when you get there it will be tijme to practice again. Nextr im going to tell you about the working at a circus.No you wont get to see or talk or spend time whith your family as much as you pleede. But they will not keep you away from your parents you just will see them at certain times. Last im going to tell you the fun parett about the circus. Its fun because you get to b perform in front of a a big cround and that will be fun. Also you will meet many many many diffrent people. You will travel alot.HOPE YOU DECIDE YOU WANT TO JOIN THE CIRCUS THANK YOU!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! Item_Response: Circus life can be crazy we travel all the time to different circuses it is busy my name is Catherine and i will share to you what a circus life is.       when i wake up at 6:30 A.M. We have to go to state to state to perform while we were on our private jet I talked about how mean,selfish,ugly,and tall Erin was.We have her flat and tall body for our statue so i can beat it!anyway I am sorry i may have gotten a little mad so anyway.           We just started our new show! I did a awesome magic trick where I made my assistant Erin the 2 disaper( I wish she did anyway), Kaitlyn made the animals do really cool tricks,and Brittney did awesome flips.I really love being in a circus.

Item_Response: My Life In the Circus          Hi there my name is Bonnie Blue-Bell I am from England and I want to tell you about my life in the circus. I joined the circus when I was 3 years old, I get to do acrobatics. When I first started being an acrobate I just did flips and cart-wheels but now that I am 15 years old I get to do all sorts of things, in my latest act I swung off the pole did a triple back flip and landed ontop of a matress straped to an elephant! Ok maybe it was just the net but the elephant would be way cooler. Oh and sometimes I get to help the sorwd thrower by being put on a spinning wheel and have knives thrown at me! It really gets your blood going not to mention your stumache turning! My mom and dad are the owners of the circus so I get to see them every day, unlike the other circus performers who miss their familys a lot. My best friend Lilly is in the circus too we get to do some of our acts together. But I feel bad for Lilly because she doesn't always get to see her family, but we kind of took her in as a family member.            Life in the circus is hard work, practiceing every day 12 shows a week! Not to mention still having to go to school. Sometimes I wish I just had a normal life and didn't have to work so hard. My little brother Tiger or Ty is what I call him wants to be a clown so he's always doing things to make people laugh. One advantage to living the circus life is being able to vist a these cool places like France, Rome, America, Cuba, and all sorts of places. I love the cirus life and I wouldn't give it up for anything.

Item_Response: Living in a circus can be both fun and hard. You have to go to eat. Then go to school. When you get back from school relax. Next, do the chores and practice. Now it is dinnertime. Finally the show is over and I feel so tired I also wonder if I will ever be a performer like my parents.                  In the morning I wake up and get dressed. Then I go to the pie car. We call it a pie car because clowns love pie for food and to throw at people so that is why we call it a pie car. We eat pancakes and bacon. Mean while the crew is getting ready for tonight show.                  Next, it is school time! We have a room for school in a one- room schoolhouse. Our school has  computers, tests, and report cards. The kids in the class speak all kinds of languages because they are from all around the world. Our geography lessons come alive.                   School is over. Now I take a quick break. We get to play with the materials that the clowns use. I also can play with my puppy Candy. She is a poodle because they do not allow big dogs.                     Chores and practice. I feed, water, and broom the horses. Today,  my father will practice siome somersaulting off a running horse. I am working on leaping from a trampoline onto a horse's back it takes balance and concentration. Kid are doing juggling and acrobaticts.                      The show is over.

Item_Response: LIFE WORKING IN THE CIRCUS      The life of working in a circus is hard, you have to work all day, have a small dinner every day, have a quick break, have a long pratice on your performance, do 10 shows a week, get wiped out after the show, and risk your life to entertain others. Item_Response: In a Circus it is preety hard work practing almost every single day and perfoming in front of lots of people. And if you make a mistake like a Acrobat your going to problaby hurt yourself so that is why you need lots of training. And my name is Bob Perez and i am a Acrobat in a Circus.                              You have to practice a lot in a Circus like an Acrobat. It takes a lot of work to be in a Circus. Almost every single day you have to practice being in a Circus. Like practicing how to train a lion, juggling, being on top of a elephant, and doing acrobatics. And you have to do all of that on a stage in front of a lot of people.                                 Once you practice you have to go through every step. Like first jump on a trampaling then on the pole and then the other pole. And once you perform in a Circus you have to memorize everything that you have done while practicing. And sometimes they put it on T.V. so you have to really trie your best. And sometimes you have to do more shows after that and after the first show you have to practice even more until the second show starts.                                    And in the second show you have to do a lot of different moves. So you have to try your best on both of these shows.

Item_Response: THE CIRCUS    By Logan Huffman                                                                                   Being part of a circus would be hard it would take a lot of work    you would have a lot of responsibility's like feeding the animals and   try to please the crowd.                                                                      In my opinion after the circus would be the hardest part you would have to clean up the bleachers and take down   the tent and transport it somewhere else.                                          Then set it up again then take the animals to the tent and go home. Then you would make sure the animals aren't sick and make sure there cages are clean and if they aren't well you have to clean it up. Then you would get dressed and put everything up like the bleachers the tight rope and the ladder pool beach ball and put out the rest of the equipment.Then collect the tickets and let people inside then when everybody has took there seat you would have to get the animals and have the show.                                                                                 And that why it would be like at a circus everyday.

Item_Response: The Circus         The circus is a place where you will have an amazing time. You will see things that you have never seen before. When you go to a circus there is only one thing you need to look out for. Having two much fun! I will tell you the story of how the circus is brought to life. I will tell you about the Setup, The Clowns, and what a show is like.               Our setup here at the circus is very interesting.We live in vans with about two other members of the circus. In all we have about two hundred members in all. On a normal year we have one hundred vans! Inside the van's are two bedrooms, one bathroom, a TV room and a couch, oh don't forget the kitchen. Our meals normally are things that you can put in the microwave. Sometimes if we are lucky we get to go out. The animals sleep in their cages. We have a special place for all the cages so none of the animals get taken away. When you take a overview picture you will see a place for all the vans. A huge amount of animal cages. One mini house that contains some bathrooms. Five mini food stands and then the circus. The color of the circus is red and white. The pattern is like swirls. We are known as the BIG APPLE CIRCUS.              The clowns are the main attractions. That is because we put so much time and effort in to them. When the clowns get out of bed the first thing they do is walk to the costume designing van. ?When they get here the costume designer makes sure that they get the worst clothes to mach. This makes them look really odd. Finally there bow tie with sparkles tops everything. When they have all of that they walk over to the hair designer. The hair designer gives them a very wacky wig and a very bright hat to top their head. When this is all done they have one more trip to make. The face painter! Our face painter gets all of their face red, then white, then a big red button for their nose. Finally they get to put on there gloves to show that they are ready to show off there skills.   Finally it is time for the show. Get the clowns ready, get the horses yapping and let the show begin. 'Welcome to the circus! As the lights start to dim backstage is a tsunami waiting to irrupt. Finally the irrupt explodes and the actors do what they do. The clowns are falling on their backsides and the acrobats jump all over the sky. The juggler juggles bananas on fire. Horses cantering all around. This is the BIG APPLE CIRCUS. Memories that i will always remember is the day i was in the circus. A clowns job is always to tell stories that are funny to the mind but all I want to tell you today is that great things happen even when you do not expect them to happen.         The circus is an amazing place and i hope you enjoy the experience one day two.

Item_Response: AT THE BELLINI CIRCUS           When my family and I go to the Bellini circus we walk in and the first thing I see the greeter I say hello. Next we walk into the staduim the show startes at 7:00 but it is 6:00 now so we have some time to eat and play games.Next we go to the food carts and eat a great hotdog the best I ever had. It is time for the show to start first the the clown comes out and makes my family and I laugh.Next a man is on a dirt bike and ride on a rope high in the air.Then the trapeze artist swing on a swing in the air and do flips.Last a woman comes out standing on a elephant when the elephant is standing on a block of wood.Then the show is over and i beg my mom and dad to bring me to the Bellini circus for my birthday.

Item_Response: THE CIRCUS           1. The circus looks and sounds very fun. The circus has all different kinds of cool stuff that they do. Most of the time you are always traveling to all different places about 20,000 miles apart. The circus goes to about 150 different places. You never get to have time off to be having fun.       2. If you had dreamed about going in a circus I would not say try it unless you had a very good talent to enter a really good circus team. They are always working on there trips to different places. When you never get time off and you are working 365 days a year I feel bad for the people that have to.       3. One of the upsides of being in a circus is that you get to see and travel all across the world.You get to go to so many different places. You are go to have about 100 different people that treat you like family. They are always by your side no matter what. They are always there if you are hurt so I say you could try out if you want to. But I say you should only try out if you have really have good talent. So try if you want to. If you get hurt your circus family will always be there for you. So don't worry you will be fine.

Item_Response: Life On The Road                                                  By: Eleanor Daniel                   Have you ever met a kid in your school who has or does work with a circus?   Well, Bella Castini works with a circus everyday from sunup to sundown.   When you work for a circus you must have a special talent. In this case Bella's   talent is with horses she leaps from a trampoline and onto a horses back. Now you   have to have some bravery and talent to do that!        Bella lives in a trailer with her family and goes to school in a traveling one room   school house. Bella still has a house in Florida too but she is mostly on the road.   Bella's parents are in the circus along with her being in the circus involves time,   dedication,talent,flexibility and luck.              The circus has things like...  tight rope walkers,Clowns,acrobats,Circus horse acts   and Circus animals! The Circus is where Bella works and she sees people from over   ten shows a week.Being on the road with a circus can have some downs too.You   only get to see your family outside of the Circus when you are in the city they live   in or take time off. Also you work on the weekend and train on the weekend too!                    At the end of the day you are wiped out but it is all worth it because now everyone your the person who jumped on a horses back! And you gave that thought to all   the kids who came to see the show. The circus is fun to see hard to perform  but amazing all together.

Item_Response: One day,I woke up.It felt like any other day.My name is Nicole and I live,work ,perform,and travel with the circus.I got up feeling excited as I felt the train stop.Today we were going to set camp in India.I had always wanted to visit India;it seemed like such a great place to perform and visit.There were so many beautiful plants and so many pretty little stores.Plus to make things even better ;Mauricio the circus manager said that the other circus in India were going to sell us over a tiger!!!It was going to be a white tiger with black stripes.I hopped out of bed, got changed, and made my way to the breakfast cart.Since we were traveling by train.I saw Isabel;one of the acrobats on my way.'Are you going to breakfast?'she asked me.I nodded and asked her 'You?'. 'No,actually i just finished.'Her answer didn`t surprise me;she tends to get up at 6:30 in the morning.   When I finished my breakfast,I checked the time;7:50.Just in time to see    the tiger.When the train started to come to a stop;I got up so fast I nearly tripped over my footing.I loved helping set up,but I really wanted to see the tiger.I ran outside when the train came to a final stop and caught up to Mauricio.When I opened my mouth to say something he stopped and said in his italian accent'I already told you could come,you don`t have to keep asking!'.I blushed.I knew what he was talking about; lastnight,I`d begged him halfway to death to let me come.Finally after two and a half hours of saying please,pretty please,please with a cherry on top(I have a record for holding my breath)he`d said yes right when my voice started to get sqeaky.'I was just going to say good morning but yeah that works too'I told him.'I`m just going to get my backpack and i`m ready'I told him'O.K, I`ll see you at the train stop'he replied.I nodded and ran to my train cart to get my phone(pictures),wallet(you never know when there might be something pretty on sale),and my backpack.I rode Blackjack;one of our horses(my favorite one in particular)and rode off to the train station.   When Maurico and  his assistants came I told them 'Finally!'   I had been waiting for forty-five minutes.I had been jumping from excitement,or maybe just ten cups of coffee pimps me up a little.Ross;one of Mauricio`s assistants rolled his eys at my exitement, but i just ignored him.We made our way to buy the tiger.When we got to the other circus manager him,Mauricio,and his assistants all went inside this big room to talk leaving me alone in the hallway.When Ross finally came out he told me we had to wait but the deal was done.The other assistant came out to tell us that we should go to camp,it was going to take a while.We got our horses and rode off to camp.When we got back the whole camp was set up so i just went insiide and read a book.three hours later;it was time for the show and mauricio and the tiger still weren`t back.I went backstage to get ready.         After I finished putting on my make up and changed into my circus clothes I heard Mauricio`s voice on speaker for the introduction.It was my turn.I got behind the curtain and got on Blackjack.Once we did our performance;which was riding Blackjack through flaming hoops,no biggie.we went around the back and watched from the audience.The acrobats show was amazing.Shannon and Isabel had learned new tricks.the tightrope act was kinda tricky at first but he got the hang of it.It was time for the tiger act.the white tiger galloped out there and did all these amazing stunts you couldn`t think were possible for a tiger.It did the craziest of things and listened and obeyed Mauricio`s every command             After a while we went to sleep.You would think that after seeing a tiger you couldn`t fall of sleep .I think i beat that statement easily.                                        The End.

Item_Response: The time i saved the circus                                                                                                When i was five years old i always wanted to go to the circus. I have been studying it ever sense. Whenever the circus is in town i always beg my mom i want to go but, we couldn't go because we didn't have the money. When i was six years old i started to watch videos of the circus. I started to get more and more into it.   In one video i saw people bending and twisting no other humans can bend! I was very amused.So I started to give it a try. I practiced and practiced until i can do it. One day later, i finally did it! I can be flexible.                         One day, i was watching TV then my mom came in with a big smile on her face. she said that we had enough money to go to the circus. Then, i started to have a big smile on my face. I jumped up and down, up and down, till i got dizzy. My mom said more . She said that we have tickets and our own show! The smile on my face got bigger. I also said how many people can we take? My mom said we can take the whole family. 'One ticket for me, one for you , one for your father, one for your sister , and one for your brother'. 'So i bought five tickets'. I began to do cartwheels all around the room. I don't think i can go to sleep tonight.                         I told my brother and my sister about what happened, and they got really exited too. Tomorrow is going to be the best day ever! At night, i started to do a back flip and a front flip. My mom came into the room rubbing her eyes and said 'go to sleep young lady'! I hopped into bed and pretend to go to sleep. When my mom exited the room, and i started to do flips again. In the morning, i started to get dressed and eat my breakfest. So did my brother and sister. We were all ready to go to the circus. When everyone was ready we all went to the car and drove to the circus.                                                                                                                               By the time we got there i saw a lot of people in line to go to the circus. We had to wait a long time to get in front of the line. When we got in all of the circus people were going nuts. I asked one clown what was going on and he said 'our flexible person is sick! We don't have backup'! Then i said'no the show must go on'.'But h-how are we going to do that'? the clown said. 'I saw videos of people being flexible in the circus, i started doing it and i mastered it perfectly'. The clown said 'great, we'll put you in a costume then. The show must go on'! He grabbed my arm and pulled me back stage. There were a lot of people crowding around me. They put an itchy costume on me then, they put me in line.'i don't think i can do this any more'. 'Oh relax you will be fine' the clown said. I gulped and tried to calm down.                                                                                                     Everyone was lining up behind me, then a guy was on the stage saying 'who's ready to see our amazing bender'. Everyone cheered. Then the clown said 'that's your cue'. I gulped again and walked up to the stage. I saw thousands of eyes looking at me. I pretended that i was alone, and started doing tricks that everyone couldn't do. Everyone oohed and aah-ed, then the guy came up to the stage and said 'let's give it up to the amazing bender everybody'. Everyone clapped and cheered. I walked up back stage and saw my family and the circus people smiling my mom hugged me and said that i did a great job. When the show was over the guy walked up to me and said ' hi my name is Bill, i think some day you are going to join the circus'. 'ya' i said. I looked at the stage one more time and said 'some day'.

Item_Response: My Act at the Circus                   I was on the train that was going to Chicago for one of our many famous performences. We had been on the train for five hours, so I figured we were getting close. I looked around, watching all the other acrobats and clowns practicing their tricks. I was about to get up, but my feet were so sore from walking that skinny tightrope, that I decided to just rest.          My name is Alexis Bone and I am a tightrope walker. For many kids, I have the dream job, but it is not all you think it would be. I'm talking about long days, late nights, and being away from home. I figured that it was all worth it when I got named 'Best Tightrope Walker in America' at just age eleven. I was excited for our biggest performence of the year, but nervous too. I looked out the window- we were there.         It was 5:00 P.M. The show starts at six. Our crew works on the finishing touches while I warm up. I looked at the clock- six. I started to hear the familiar voice of our ringmaster, Mr. Brian O'Haris.   ' Hello, and welcome to... Circus Sundown!!!'   His voice boomed throughout the large tent. First up was the acrobats. Next were all the clowns and animals. Finally it was the trappeze people and me.          I decided to rest my feet and watch the performences through the T.V. backstage. I watched the acrobats do their amazing stunts, I watched The clowns riding in the small car next to the huge elephants, and when I saw the trappeze people coming out, I stood just behind the entrance, waiting for my cue.         I saw my cue to start climbing up the tall ladder in the back of the tent that leades to the tightrope. When I got up to the top, I felt like I was going to be sick. My nerves went crazy as I heard my final cue.         I stepped onto my platform- the crowd went crazy! That made me feel a little better, but when the music stopped, I went back into fully terrified mode. I stepped on the wire, scrunched my feet, and began. I tried to look confident as I started to make my way across the wire. I was focusing so hard on not falling, I didn't notice that I was done. I threw my hands up and bowed. The crowd went crazy as they gave me a standing ovation.

Item_Response: Have you ever wished to join a circus? Have you ever been asked to join a circus? Well I can say yes to all of those questions! My name is Rachel Dolphie Loveer and I'm here to talk about being an acrobatic in the circus and what life is like in a circus. Just to begin let me say it is an exciting, amazing, but incredibly hard job. You have to practice, practice, practice every day. But when you get into the ring every minute you spent practicing is worth it. The crowd cheers and all you see is the smiling faces all around you.                                                                              After I wake up and eat my breakfast its all about school and acrobats for me and my family. First I learn regular things like you and then I practice. Then after a half an hour of 'backbending' work its time for a stretch-break. At  4:00 p.m its more practicing for me with multiple water breaks in between. Then at 7:30 its show time!              Everyone goes into the backstage tent as our director tells about our circus. After two hours of a light show-time practice its my turn to shine. Verso, our circus director, says, 'And now for our youngest little acrobatic! Who, at age 13, can do more than her father, Marcos! I introduce to you Rachel Dolphie Loveer!' I cartwheel out and twist and turn in the air as I jump into center stage. I lift my head to a squealing baby girl in the front row. She breaks into a wide smile as I climb into the air before twisting, turning, and swinging everywhere. I jump and spin like no other while still being the most graceful acrobatic in the ring. This is what the circus is all about to me.               Then I bow to the audience as they clap, whistle, and shout my name at me. I back bend slowly then walk out on my hands to enthusiastic applause. My family pats me on the back as soon as I'm in the backstage tent. I hear everyone telling me how amazing I was as I smile, hug, and high-five my family. The circus is the best place in the world for me at this moment.                I would give up everything to be right here everyday. And I am! My life is perfect in this moment right here. This is my circus life! I watch as everyone does there acts while congratulating everyone who finishes. After a few more hours the circus is finished. I settle into bed at 12:00 a.m. but that's alright. I did amazing at the show and that's all that matters. Tomorrow it will start again until I'm to old to bend so well. But that doesn't matter right now. Because I'm in the circus, and this is my life.

Item_Response: Life in a Circus                                                                                                        By Kaitlyn Danielle Pasillas                       Living in the circus can be crazy but also has the points of living a normal life.  As said from Bella Castini and Philippa Hayball, the circus life is difficult and can't be done by just anyone.  There's many things to do like practice or fit in a good meal, and then there's getting started with it all.                 When ever you feel like joining the circus, you must remember some important things first.    The circus is not just a huge playground with an audience all the time.  You've got to travel very far distances from home all over the world, sometimes even 20,000 miles in seven months each and every year could be your life.  Hopefully you know different languages.  The day is work from when the sun goes up to when the sun sets down.  There's also the getting in part of the circus.  You must have a specific talent to join, and you must be good at it.  When you get in, the day seems very long, if you are a child, don't think you've just avoided school for the rest of your life.  It may not be exactly the same, but you still have tests, report cards, computers and everything a regular school needs.  When you're ready, it's time for the show, remember, you have at least until late in the night for relaxation, practice, and food.  The way the circus works is tough so you should be ready for a whole different turn in your life.                                          Now, the life of a carney in the circus is insane.  You wake up early then head to get breakfast.  For the kids, it's school time right after.  You must be able to memorize languages from all over the world.  The classmates you have could be from France or Italy and still not speak your language.  Even though you have a busy day, you still get tests and report cards.  As soon as the school is over you might have time for a short break, but then it's off to practice.  Oh, and don't think yo have no chores any longer!  You then get dinner and then it's off to the show.  As soon as the show is over you may just want to crawl into bed.  You get about 7 hours of sleep, maybe that is.  Your usual bed time is around 12:00 A.M. The life of a carney is crazy and tiring.                                 The talents you need must be very different and unusual.  There's singing, dancing, and being amazingly flexible.  You could be an acrobat or perhaps a trapeze artist, maybe a clown or a juggler, there's the job of a tightrope walker as well.  You may have wanted to be a performer your entire life or you have just gotten sick of your regular life and wanted to do more.  Some people have been doing performing for years.  Like doing gymnastics, music, or acting as a starter.  Philippa Hayball said, 'When I was 11, I knew I wanted to be a performer, so I went for it.'  One talent that every carney should have is concentration.  You need to put your heart in it throughout everything.  As a carney, you have the priorities of being in the circus.  You need to have the talent they have every day to be in the circus.                     If you ask anybody who lives in the circus, they will tell you their is and upside and a downside to the package of the circus.  The upside includes the chance to travel around the world.  You may be able to make new friends too.  Everyone you meet can become your family.  The thrill itself of performing for a live audience is amazing.  Their job is to play and have fun every night.  They see it as a pleasure to have our faces be filled with such joy that is so unexplainable to anyone.  The audience is almost taken to whole different world.  Sadly, there is a downside to the job of a circus performer.  The fun and games has an end at some point.  Even though it's a glamorous lifestyle, there are drawbacks.  There's nowhere you can really call home and that can really enter the mind during a night's show.  Some miss their own gardens and pets and family.  Truly but sadly, they don't often see their family.  Plus, the work is so tiring during the long hours of the days, even weekends.  The upsides can be great, but the downside can be most unpleasant with the life of a carney.                      The life of a circus performer is like living in a, well, circus.  Crazy, wild, fun, but also sad.  Philippa Haybal and Bella Castini have their experiences with the circus.  It can't be easy all the time and there is the day when you just can't do a thing.  They have said that when you're in the circus, your whole life begins to change.

Item_Response: Circus Life   On March tenth  at the circus there was a group of people who decided to look around the circus and everywhere they went they were amazed on what was happened. Jumping over rings of fire to clowns juggling on a unicycles it made them look bewildered. So one of the people in the group decided that they should join the circus. They ended up becoming performers and were sent straight to work.       First, One of the people in the group loved animals and signed up to be a animal trainer. So when she got to her area she realized she saw a sign labeled Lions  and on a little table there was a whip and some meat for the lion. She crept inside feeling very terrified that there was one large lion just sitting there looking very hungry. As the girl crept up to the lion it began to growl  and then roar. Quickly the girl whipped the lion and it crawled to the corner looking very angered because he was  whipped and it stared at the meat for a long time until the girl gave him some. after that they started doing a lot of tricks.       Next, the tallest of the group and he oldest decided he wanted to tightrope walk. All he had to do was cross the tightrope and he would be done for the day.when he got on he made it thirteen steps until he fell then the next was fourteen steps and then fifteen steps and then he finally did it he passed the twenty step tightrope and collapsed on the ground do to him being extremely tired and after he climbed down the ladder he rested on the ground.       Then, the next person who was the youngest in the group joined acrobatics when he jumped he missed the rope and broke his arm. After the ambulance came for and put on his cast he came back because he didn't want to miss the matinee and once it was his turn to jump he sprinted and then jumped but this time he didn't miss the jump and he started becoming known as 'one arm'.       Finally, The group walked back to the pie car after the show and talked about what they did. The girl talked about the lion and the oldest talked about the tightrope and the youngest talked about his acrobatic accident. After they thought about they realized that they all faced their fears.       When the whent to sleep they all thought of their journeys and what they did not realizing that they had another big day ahead but none of them cared they only wanted rest.

Item_Response: Thirteen-year-old Daniel sat in the pie car eating pancakes, and drinking orange juice, while looking out the window at the circus tent,'Another day of being in the circus,' he said. He went inside the tent, and felt exhausted just by looking at his father practicing his performing skills. He then saw his older sister, Kathryn getting ready for the show, and his mother helping performers plan their outfit.            Daniel went to the dressing room, and put on his costume.He put a robe around his costume. Then, the make up artist made his face look like a clown. He was ready for the show! The other performers went outside to the pie car and ate pancakes, bacon, and hashbrowns, while drinking apple juice. He joined his father and practiced his juggling while standing on one foot, and his tightrope walking acts. He went backstage, and got his sister. He asked her if she wanted to do a very special performance with her. Excitedly, she said,'YES,'.             So they practiced and and practiced and practiced until they got it right. 'I can't do this anymore!' said Kathryn. Daniel kept encouraging her to keep trying, and said,'c'mon it's already planned, and we have a special time performing towards the end of the show for everyone.' But Kathryn didn't listen and ran away.             At the end of the show, Kathryn didn't show up. Daniel didn't want to cancel, so he went with the plan. As he introduced himself to the crowd, Kathryn came out! Daniel was surprised, and proud of his sister. They did their special performance, standing on top of horses! Then their career of being in the circus was happily ever after.
