Item_Response: Jenifer was an acrobat who was practicing for her most important performance.4 years ago she would've thought the circus was all about flipping and jumping and hugging tigers,but now that she has been in the circus business for...a while she knows that even though there is flipping and jumping, there is much more to a circus to reveal.She was in her trailer with some jugglers and the lion tamer.It was only 3:00 PM and she was already tired.'Don't worry Jennifer.Now is not the time for worrying,we still have much more to do'the lion tamer said to her while she took out a broom.'Yeah, well right now what I have to worry about is helping to clean up the tent or James will chew my''-JENNIFER!''sorry! i forgot that there are...erm...'children''here''.The lion tamer nodded approvingly and combed his baby leopards fur.The lion tamer(whose name was Carl)never liked it when others swore in front of his leopard,Charlie.Said it was a bad example on him.'he was a beast before and i don't want him like that now!'' he would say.''Hurry up Jennifer!''one of the acrobats hollered.'i'm coming''Jennifer muttered under her breath.She heading outside and was delighted to see the sun shining.They were in New Jersey and it rained alot.Jennifer realized the other acrobats were staring at her.'okay,What prank did you guys pull off now?Jennifer asked.She walked in a circle and stared at the ground.'It's not you Jennifer it's just that...well...isn't that gate usually locked? the sparkly acrobat pointed behind her.Jennifer whipped her dark hair around and noticed that it was usually locked.'hey guy's!' James came in.'What's...''he began but then went dead silent.''OH NO!''James ran away and started screaming 'CARL!CARL! YOUR NEEDED!''.All but suddenly reality smacked her face.It was the lions cage that was opened.Jennifer almost fainted.She raced back to her trailer and saw that Carl was gone.He left a note however.It read''Jennifer, i went out for a moment to walk Charlie.Don't worry, i haven't disappeared this timeJennifer would've giggled if she weren't absolutely terrified.The last time Carl left everyone thought he ran away from the circus.Okay Jennifer calm down now I think James has got this all under control, she thought to herself.She then remembered James's panic in finding Carl.So maybe NOT under control.She heard a low rumbling sound coming from the showers.Jennifer got up the courage to walk up to the shower.With her shaky hand she whipped open the shower.There,Sitting in the shower,was a six foot tall, carnivorous,lion.Jennifer tried to scream but it came out all Squeaky.At the sound of that,the lion slightly turned it's head.Jennifer saw it's ferocious brown eyes.He roared so loudly that the lamp broke.Jennifer stepped backwards and tripped.Thud!She hit her head. Her vision was blurry but she could see the lion clearly.She stumbled to get uo then hit the floor again.She opened the mini fridge and saw a huge piece of raw steak.Jennifer stood up and retrived the meat. The lion roared again and he pounced.Jennifer dodged it and ran out.'JAMES!'' James stopped screaming and his eyes widened when he saw the lion.He ran to the gate and opened it.Jennifer stopped in the entrance of the gate and stood.She didn't know what she was doing.JENNIFER MOVE!''James screamed.The lion was coming right at her.She did an ariel leap over the tiger and James slammed the cage shut.Jennifer was sweating and was out of breath.Carl then walked up to them.''What did i miss?''he asked.'Nothing Carl,Nothing at all.'Jennifer replied smiling.That night was her biggest night of the year.Jennifer got a strange feeling.That feeling was confidence

Item_Response: Days at the Circus       It is crazy around here during the day, people running around practicing juggling and washing animals.       Here's a typical day for me:         7:00 A.M.-Get up, get dressed and go to the trailer for chocolate chip pancakes. The crew is setting up tents, lights, and music for tonight's show.             9:00 A.M.-go to school in a trailer and study on the computer until lunch. After lunch we do another lesson and back to the trailer.             2:15 P.M.- school's over, get a little snack and play with the horses.              2:45 P.M.- chores and practice. some of my chores are grooming the horses, scrub all the saddes.                6:15 P.M.- dinner, food smella really good but we don't eat much because the show is soon.              10:30 P.M.- the show starts and its really good. Mydad goes out first and he is amazing! the reast of us did great too..               12:00 P.M.-loved the show, in bed now thanking fior a great day.

Item_Response: If you  are thinking about working at the circus  you are thinking just like me Deaujha Battle.The circus is very fun to go to you get to see many things and have the experience to do those things when your older.       Heres my daily schedule:           6:30 am I get up brush my teeth wash my face take a wash up or shower and get dreesed. Next I go in the living room turn on tv, go get my socks and shoes,and put my socks and shoes on and get ready for school.       7:30 am im in the car heading to school for a good wonderful beautiful day because after school i will be going to the circus to do my job which is a acrobatic.           8:00 am get in school we have a reading test today and that is about the circus about what we know about the circus and how did we find out this information about the circus so of course i know i am going to pass the test because i work at the circus so i know almost everything about the circus.           9:00 am it is time for our special and today we have P.E. and today in P.E. we are going to be playing this game called circus clowns and i was so excited because today we were mostly doing everything about clowns.           11:00 am we have lunch and today the luch lady said we were going to have what clowns have so when she said that I knew something had to be up someone must knew I worked at the circus or something           11:30 It was time to have recess so today for recess we are pretending to be clowns and after that we will do some acrobatics our teacher had said so then I was very happy because at the circus I am a acrobatic.           12:00 pm it is time for dismissal so when they called my name to be dismissed I jumped up very fast because I was ready to go to the circus           12:30 pm I get to the ciscus which is where i work at and when i get their i see all my classmates and i ask what are you guys doing here they all said we knew you worked here so i said but i didnt tell you i worked here and they all said your manager called and told us to do clown things today and come watch you do your acrobatic thing.           1:00 pm i am performing my acrobatic thing and i here my friends cheeering me on and saying positive things about me.               6:00 pm it is time for dinner and when i get home my mom says guess what we are having tonight i say what she says clown food.               9:00 pm i am in bed resting good and i wae up and say i cant wait for tomorrow wonder what we are having for breakfast and lunch.           THANK YOU BY: DEAUJHABATTLE

Item_Response: Life at The CIRCUS              Life at the circus is sometimes very difficult,it pretty much seems fun but not really.A circus is a very fascinating place,it has many interesting things like for example there's elephants,clowns,horses,acrobatics,leopards,juggling,lions,horseback acts,chimpanzees,and many more.So,join me and lets talk about working in the circus.                  In the circus they have to travel all over the world just to fascinate and amaze many different people.you need to set up evrything so people can get amazed and go to your circus,like for example big posters that say ''Circus circus come and enjoy our fun loving circus now!evrysingle day your probably going to have many different people come and enjoy the circus,but evry single day your going to need to clean up after them.It's pretty much true you are going to need to clean up after them because the audience does make a big mess evry time they go to the circus,like litterally all the popcorn and soda spills all over the floor.                 Many circus's have a special place where performers from the circus go to eat,they call it the ''Pie car'',and no they don't eat and buy pure pie right there,only becauase it's called a Pie car doesn't mean they sell and eat pure pie there.you can't eat too mch though because you still have to do some more performances!many performers enjoy the food there.                Circus workers need to travel evry where almost around the world,and this is all just so people can come to the circus.It is very difficult to travel sometimes because the workers may get sick.Even if they get sick they still decide to travel.they all ways travel no matter if it's near or far.they travel evrywhere evry single day.                As you can see working at the circus is easy and hard at the same time.You get to do many different things at the circus but some thing include lots of training.They also travel alot and you might get sick on the way to your destination!Your always going to need to clean up after the audience leaves because if you don't it's going to be a mess.remember their your adience let them be proud and enjoy the performances!

Item_Response: One nice morning at the circus, a boy and girl orphan were on the run because they ran away from the orphanage. Now, these two kids have names, the boy was named Oliver and the girls was named Astroria. Thay left the orphanage because they where called runts (ironic, right?) and always left them out. Impressively, they managed to get out of there and decided to live their life as two performers to get away from the orphanage and the bullies. The day they made it to the circus it was ,of course, a nice morning. Let's start this story, shall we?'Finally, were here!' shouted Oliver, that had his mouth covered quickly. 'Shhh!' said Astroria, 'you'll wake the performers' she continued.They had to wait for the gates to open before going in.  Eventually they waited until the gate was opened and quickly scampered in. Once in they met the owner of the circus.'Mister Tillman!' Oliver called out.'Who's there?' Tillman answered. Tillman was a strong man and also is a performer, but only for the beginning.'We'd like to be in your circus!' Astroria replied. 'Where are your parents?' Tillman asked. 'W-were orphans and we'd like to be performers!' stutered Astroria. 'Are you two related?', Tillman asked. 'We think not...' said Astroria. 'Well it's okay if I let you two be performers if you guys promise me your acts could be chosen.'Tillman asks. 'Of course' both reply. Many months past and the two perfectly fit in with the others, but one day. 'Okay todays act for you two is......acrobatics!' said Tillman. Over the time, both kids have became more skillful at the circus and acrobatics were their favorite act. Before the act starts Oliver ask Tillman for fire effects at the end and Tillman agreed. Durring their show, everyone was amazed by their moves and tricks. 'Okay this is it , try to do as many frontflips as you can!' reminded Astoria to Oliver. 'I got this' replies Oliver. Oliver springs off aboard, does a few flips and perfectly lands in the safety net. At the same time Astroria, still standing on the board falls off because of a shining light hitting her eyes. Oliver notices and (by pure luck) finds a trampoline, bounces on it, catches Astroria, does another flip, and perfectly lands as the fire effects go off. Everything is silent but out of nowhere  the crowd chants,shouts, and whistles. Later that night everyone treated them with even more respect than they did before. They still performed but they chose their permanent act would be acrobatics. The End.

Item_Response: The Circus: The Show of a Life Time                                                                By: Trinity Smallwood           One, fine-no. One Beautiful morning, I was going down to the market, when I saw almost the entire townspeople looking at the 'HELP WANTED' wall. Well, I was not going to just stand there staring like a buffoon, so I went down there, to see what the hullabaloo was about. The hullabaloo was that there was a 'HELP WANTED' sign for the Circus!! Now, I don't know about you, but if there's a Circus, they make MONEY! If you saw them you would pay them for just being there, I mean they, like, radiate money. Well, me and my folks could use some of that money, so I hurried up with my tasks and went home to tell my folks about the chance we had. They were ECSTATIC about doing it. They wanted all of us (Lewis, Sarah, Miles, and I) to try out for it. 'It'll give this family a better chance of getting in!!' My mama said. 'And which ever one of you gets in-you go for it!!' On the 'Try-outs' we were so exited! when we (individually) tried out, me and Sarah got in, but the boys didn't. Lewis was fuming! He was so mad, he almost broke his computer!! 'I SHOULD'VE GOTTEN IN THERE!! NOT SARAH AND LEIA!!' He shouted.   I'll bet you're wondering how my first day went. Well, on the first day we had a lot of fun. First, I walked in to the tent they had put up. Then, I saw all of the Circus! All of whom I saw was: the Clowns: the Acrobats; and-OH, MY, GOD!!! The Tight Rope Walkers!!! I walked right over there, and they welcomed me as if I had been their friend forever. They helped me do their routines, and they even let me do one on my own!!! They were so kind, they let me use their ropes (since I didn't have on yet) and made me feel right at home. I was so happy, that I forgot I had a performance that morning, AND that I was dreaming about the first time I walked in and met every one!! 'That was the best show yet!!' Sarah said. I had told my sister about my dream and she thought I was re-imagining how I had felt because I was nervous. The fact is, I am nervous. But I don't dream things when I'm nervous. So, I don't know what to think of it. 'Well, wish me luck!' I said. She and I said 'See ya' and I went to the 'Performance Tent' to rehearse.   I was the BEST out there. When the crowd cheered, I just stood in the finished position and just Smiled. That was the best day of my life!!

Item_Response: My name is Andy Pho and I will tell you about circus life! Being a circus performer isn't all fun and games, I still have to do homework like any other kid, and practice preforming. An advantage for me, is that you get to travel all over the world and meet different people. It's really cool because making people from different countries laugh and amazed is a really good feeling.                      My family and I usually have to sleep in a big trailer and have to spend a lot of time from home, but I'm cool about it. I sometimes think if I'll ever to actually live in our house, but I guess it's just one of the backslides you get as a circus performer. I do get homesick sometimes, but I try that not to stop me from preforming.                   People usually think that preforming is really easy but it's really not! We may make it look easy, but those moves takes a lot of training and talent. I joined the circus 2 years ago when I was 8. I started with gymnastics and then started wanting to become a performer. I knew it it would require patience and talent, so I tried my best. My parents were kind of worried about me not being home all the time, but I told them I would be OK.                 As you can see being a circus performer has it's advantages and non-advantages. I still love being a performer in front of people, but people should make sure to think about it first. My name is Andy and I see you next time!

Item_Response: Fight Cheaters with Genius                My name is Lilly Smith a 14 year old highschooler. My mom and dad pushed me in to being a circus performer when I was 4. I was very flexible for my age. That made my dad very happy because he was a  tightrope walker so I can be a acrobat. When I was 6 my dad went to go do something and left me next to the rope. When he came back  I was doing handstands on the rope. He was flabbergasted when he saw me. He said you are two in one and there is no way they won't exept her. When I was 8 my dad toke me to the owner of the of the circus and he was happy too but then he said that he already had a girl like her and only had two men but only one of them was like her too. I met the girl the next day she seemed nice until I talked to her she was tring to put presure on me so I will mess up and she gave me a pair of shoes that were so slippery that i fell every time i spun around. She wasn't going to play fair she was going to cheat.        This is the first show and to told her to get the my new shoes and I lnew she was going to get the ones that were slippery so I fell and blamed it on her. The nexted show I won because he said that I was fresh, eligant, and graceful. My dad was right there nexted to me after that show he was so proud of me. Then I got wrried if I don't do something new I could go home. My dad was tring to think of something to do and it reminded me of me childhood. Then I forgot that my mom was going to be there. Item_Response: life in the circus isn't all just fun and games, its hard work.       have you ever gone to the circus? what is your favorite thing to see, the daring acts, or the glimmering lights that introduce your favorite act, or is it just everything about the circus that you like. the setting the acts the animals or the clowns?       My favorite thing to do is tight roping. Tight roping is where you are about 50 feet in the air with a 12 foot long stick to balance you for walking across a 1foot wide rope thats 30 feet long that you have to walk across. sounds crazy right,thats what  i do every show.       When i put my feet on the rope, it sinks down from my weight and i start walking, thats when my head starts spinning but i just keep on walking. If you've ever stood on one foot this is nothing like this, this is one foot in front of the other and is much harder than balancing on one foot, walking on that tiny rope feels walking on air , really really  high in the air with a stick for balance. But once you get on the rope you can't go to fast and you can't go to slow,you cannot make any mistakes when tight roping, it's all about timing.

Item_Response: There is a girl named Alexis, and she is making up her mind if she wants to join the circus or not. 'I don't know Hunter' said Alexis talking to her brother. 'Why not!' exclaimed Hunter. 'You are in shape, have good balance, and you get to travel the world!' Alexis was walking around her house trying to decide. Then, Alexis said she would join the circus tomorrow. Her parents said it was ok, and they went to bed.       The next morning Alexis and her family went to the circus sign-ups. Alexis was really nervous. Then her mother said 'Hello my daughter would like to join the circus. Is this where we sign in?' There was a big man in a white shirt and he nodded. The man lead Alexis and her family to a tent that was filled with people all over the world lining up to sign in for the circus. 'Are you sure you want to join the circus?' asked Alexis's father. 'Yes. I want to perform in the circus.' said Alexis.       A man blew his whistle and everybody went to him. 'Anybody who is joining the circus go in that corner.' Everybody went over there inclouding Alexis. He pointed to Alexis and said 'Whats your talent?' He asked. 'Ummm umm' Alexis didn't really have a talent so she blurted out 'Walking on the tightrope' she said. 'Ok you go over there' he said.       She walked on the tightrope very well. She didn't fall once.' Ok we will be leaving for our first tour tomorrow.' He said. 'TOMORROW!!!' Alexis screamed. They all ran back to their places to practice more. Alexis said goodbye to her parents. Then she went to practice. She was sad that she wouldn't see her parents for a while, but she was happy she was joining the circus.

Item_Response: Facts about the Circus   What is it like to be a circus preformer? Well, it contains hard work and a lot of dedication and you must have the right body type. You need a lot of fexlibility and training to be a circus preformer. There are many ups and downs of being a circus preformer too, it isnt just perfect there are many hardships that you will face along the way. Bella ( a circus preformer) traveled 20,000 miles in ONE YEAR!  You will probably also be wiped out from the practices and the show that you will do. You also have to STILL do school but, in a one roomed school house! The ups of being in the circus is you can practice stunts and flexibility. You also get to see all the different kinds of animals that are in the circus which are mostly wild ( but tamed) animals.                                                   Story about the circus By: Hallie Solie                                                                                                                                                                                           People probably could look at me and think that I was not a circus preformer. I don't ike the cold stares people give my mom when we go out in public with our face paint on. I don't want to be in the circus, but it is seomthing that I love and can't quit! I first joined the circus when I was 4. My parents wanted to keep me at a reasonable age to join the circus because there were so many different stunts involved. I first started meeting with a dance and gymnastics teacher every day, every week. We practiced keeping the beat and ometimes even different stunts. Soon when I was 8 I could do any gymnastics trick that anyone asked me. I was a terrific gymnast/ dancer and I officially joimed the circus after that. The first time I did a stunt it was revolting and unrealistic. I swung from bar to bar until I reached the end of the fish net. it was so scary yet so fun that I wanted to keep on doing it until I died. When I fell I just got right back up. My mom called me Wonder Women. Now, its different.       I get to have my own part in the show! I will be doing gymnastics AND dance! It will be so much fun! It was totally worth 10 years of waiting! I guess since I am 14 I am old enough to run the show! My first dance was a major hit! People loved it and applaud me loudly! It was the most beautiful clap I have ever heard in my entire preforming life. I would have to do a gymnastics act later tonight. My gymnastics act was even better! The claps were louder and more real. Back tucks and Front tucks were the main idea of what I was doing. People wistled and screamed my name! If I could do this all my life I would. Our next tour is in Boston ( I read my bosses planner  ) I hope they liked our act as much as Florida did!         Boston tour wasn't any different accept for my routine! The crowds applaud me like Florida did and they also screamed my name! Finally, people decided it was my time to do something that I wouln't do in a million years, I ran through the ring of fire! Johnny Cash blared through the radio and I looked at that small ring and jumped with all my  might. The fire burned me but it was something I could fit through. I guess I found my new circus act out.

Item_Response: Circus Life                                                               By Teagan           I like being in the circus but it is very difficult. It is very fun but I never can call a place home or join a sports team. I will tell you how fun and difficult a circus life can be.           6:30 am  I wake up and get dressed in my acrobat suit and go into the food car and eat pancakes with the clowns. The clowns are fun to eat with but they always want to play with their food. A lot of times the human cannonball man makes the pancakes.         7:15 am I start practicing my acrobat routine with my brother. After I finish practicing for the night show I play with the clowns. I love to ride their unicycles. Happy the clown showed me how to ride one. Happy is my favorite clown because he always wants to play boardgames with me.         8:45 am School starts I usually learn about math, science,geography and reading. Some times we have a lot of homework and if I need help I usually ask my mom, dad or Happy.Whats really fun is that for recess we get to play with the monkeys. My favorite monkey in named Ty, he is the smallest of all the monkeys.         2:30 pm Schools over and I have to start doing my chores. My chores are to feed all of the animals and practice with them so they are ready for the 5:45 and 9:30 show. I practice with the tigers to jump through a ring of fire. I don't really have to practice with the elephants because they don't really do anything people just do tricks on them. Last I practice with the monkeys, they do acrobatic and tightrope acts. It is actually kind of fun to practice with the monkeys.          3:00 pm I have my meal before the show. I eat with the clowns and my brother, mom and dad. My mom is an animal trainer and my dad is a tight rope walker. I have to eat my supper at 3:00 pm because if would eat right before I do my acrobatic act I might get sick during the 5:45 show.         4:30 pm  We start setting up the stage. It is horrible setting up the stage for every show because when we tour the world  we have to set up each time we move cities. It is really hard for me to carry the big safety net for my acrobat performance. It must way 100 pounds!         5:45 pm We start the show. That's my favorite part because all of the hard training will pay off. It is very exciting being an acrobat because it fells like you are flying through the air and just when you are going to hit the ground I get swooped up by my brother.             8:30 pm We just finished the show. It was super fun, I love performing in front of people. All of the performers get a quick break before we all have to do the 9:30 show. I've always thought the 9:30 show was to late at night but I still have to do it anyway.         9:30 pm We have to start the 9:30 show. I know I said I love doing my acrobatic show but I hate doing it all over again. I'm really tired after the first show but I still have to do everything again! It is horrible.         12:00 am All of the shows are over for the day and I am pooped. Everything I do is super tiring And I have to do it all twice! It is super fun to be in the circus but it also has a lot of down sides.

Item_Response: Margo Marasigan lives in a  big trailer with her family.Margo and her family travels around the world,and performs night shows in cities,like Las Vegas,Manila,Santa Maria.Margo always has a typical day just like her circus performer friends.She has to do work everyday with her family.Margo misses her home in the Philippines and wishes to go back.                            Here is a typical day for Margo:                 8:00 A.M. Margo wakes up gets dressed and eats breakfast with her friends at a trailer where circus performers eat.Some days they eat pancakes,and bacon,but most of the time they mostly eat rice,sausages,and spam.                    9:00 A.M. School time.They have a one-room schoolhouse that travels with them.The schoolhouse has things that a regular school has,like computers,textbooks,and report cards.Everyday they learn new things in Math,English,and Social Studies.Sometimes when they have some extra time they learn French,Russian,or maybe Italian languages.           2:00 P.M. School is over.The clowns let Margo play with their unicycles.And sometimes she juggles balls,or maybe bowling pins.Margo also have a puppy named Etho,which she plays and walks him in the nearby park.           2:39 P.M.Chores and practice.Margo feeds the horses,waters the plants,and cleans her room if it's messy.Her dad practices horse back acts.She is practices somersaulting off a running horse.She is also working on leaping from a trampoline onto the horse's back.          5:30 P.M.Dinner time.Tonight Margo ate Hamburgers for dinner.She didn't ended up finishing the hamburger because shows about in an hour and they need to get ready.               6:30 P.M. Showtime.Margo loves doing tricks while she was at horseback.She loves how everytime when Margo makes eye contact to them the jump up from their seats to cheer them on.Margo is always used to performing at night and performing a matinee on Wednesdays.           10:00 P.M.Show's over.Margo is exhausted.As she was walking back to the trailer,she passes the circus office.Two Days from now,they will set up in another state.

Item_Response: Hello, my name is Leilani.I'm 11 years old. Tommorrow I am trying out for the circus. I'm excited, scared, and happy at the same time. I really hope I make it in, if I don't I don't know what I will do with my life. If I make it in , I'm planning to be an acrobat. I have been training for 4 years. Before that I was in gymnastics. Now, here I am trying out for the circus. Well I think I should be heading to bed now, I don't want to miss my big day!             Awww! Good morning. OH NO! I forgot, I'm trying out today. I need to get ready. Right now I'm half asleep and my tryouts start in 30 minutes! I'm just going to throw on some clothes and head out the door.                       Finally, I'm here just in time. All of a sudden I here my name. '' LEILANI! '' Someone yells. Oh, that's for me. I better go in to the room for tryouts. AAW. I can't believe this is happening. I'm walking in to the room. WOW! It's awesome in here. Theres ropes and bars everywhere. Then I here a booming vioce say, '' You may start now! '' Then I reply, ''Ok.'' So then I start my routine. I climb up on to the rope and do all kinds of tricks.Then I end and then the booming vioce came back again and said,'' Terriffic!'' Then I finally look around the room and see him. It is a clown! Then he says, '' Hello, my name is Balto, what is yours?'' I then say loud and clear, ''Leilani.'' Then he replied, ''Well,guess what you made it in the circus!'' Then I run all around the room saying thank you. I finally settle down and he says, ''The first show is tommorrw morning at 11:00, thank you.'' Then I walk out the room, head to the car, and my mom drives me home.                         Oh, yay. Today is my show and I'm already at the circus trailer.I practice a little then everyone starts to get here. Finally the show starts. Balto gives a nice start, now it's my time. I head out excited do a flip then jump on to the rope I do my part then head back stage again,as I walk away I here everyone cheering for me. I actully have to say that might have been the best moment of my life.

Item_Response: What happens in the circus? Well some people will never know, but I do. Me and my friend Rily want to the Amozon Circus for the inside scoop. Of what they do, me and rily want to find out what happens in the circus like, how many people perform, how they fly on the silks, and how they teach the animals to do cool tricks.       So me and Rily went to talk with the main cheif of the circus Mr. Hoeny. He said that each night they perform they have 60 people perform exact. He also said that 10 people do one trick on the animal they have been training but they each go one by one. Then the next groop will perform what they have to do. Until they are done the people who are not performing they will help run the show. So that what me and Rily got about how many people are in the circus.       Next we went to the flying silk tent and me and Rliy had to find someone to help us. So we found Madam Kishca the famous Silk person. So I was talking to her and she said the flying silks are really hard to master it anly took me 2 years to learn how to use the silks because I wanted to be in the circus and wene they had tryouts i was only 5 and i made it to the circus the gudges were impress about how well I did. So back on the report well on the flying silks we have to be flexible so we have to do gymnastics wich is easy if you have been doing it since you were 1 years old which i have been doing said Angelina the reporter. Next you have to  have good grips on the silks because it will hurt you if you dont have a tight grip.       The last thing is how do people train the animals. whaqt they do is that they use treats to help them understand what to do like counting painting and other stuff. that all you really need to know about the story.

Item_Response: Date: April 25,2013                     Name:Shannon Bullock                                                                                                                             Circus Days!          Intro:  Hello, my name is Katie Johnson. I am 11 years old. In this story we are going to be talking all about the circus.                           Let's Join The Circus!        One day while I was sitting on my bed, I wanted to go for a walk. When I was outside I saw some flyers that said' JOIN THE CIRCUS TODAY!' Then I said to myself 'I want to join the circus now.' When I had got home I had asked my mom could we join the circus, surprisingly she said 'yes'. So we got Evey thing that we were taking.Then we had go plane tickets to go to our destination which was Africa.When we had arrived at Africa's airport we saw a big white and red tent. My mom and I had went inside the tent and signed a white sign up sheet. We interred the big tent and we got taught many of tricks. When everyone got their together we had a show. There were thousands of people there just to see us perform. Soon as the circus crew saw the audience they knew what they had been practicing.                             The performers!      The first performer was Andy, he was a lion tamer.  Andy had brown lions, and white lions. After Andy there was a gymnastics girl names Kate. Kate did back flips, jumps, and she cartwheeled off a moving horse.Finally, it was my turn I was the one who controls the elephants,  that had to be the best job of all of them. I made the elephants stand up.Also made the elephants hold up one hand. The whole crowed cheered and screamed.The circus did the same act everyday of one week . After the week was over we would make up new acts.The circus is like school you would go for a few months and then you would have a few months for a break.                                      After the shows I would help the other kids groom the animals. There  was two people there that I was really close to  her name is Madison and My mom. Madison is my best friend.When the tour around the world was over everyone went home. My best friend Madison moved next door to me ,so now I can see her everyday.We go to school together and we are in the same class.After school we go outside and practice some old circus acts. I all ways wished to be  in the circus and my wish came true.   Madison and I said when we grow up we would be awesome circus actors.That was my time in the circus.

Item_Response: ''Oh shoot!''thought Joseph. His parents had just told him that they were going to go to the circus that Joseph worked at to watch him perform!Joseph has been working for the Alveni circus for two months, just enough to get the hang of it, but now that his parents were coming he felt like he had learned nothing.         There was only one thing to do. Practice, Practice, Practice.So Joseph left with an alarming,''By!'', hopped on his bike, and started pedaling. He checked his watch, 9:34 a.m., when he looked up, all he saw was the red and blue of the circus tent.On his way in he waved to Matt, his best friend out everyone at the circus. He quickly climbed up the ladder, and hung on to the trapeze. Before starting he took a big, deep, slow, breath. While he swayed he did amazing flips, alternating as if time didn't even exist anymore. This is how he always felt on the trapeze, but while he swung he saw his parents along with all of the fans. He was still looking when he plummeted into the net.          Oh no! He had forgotten he had a performance this morning!          When he woke up he heard,''And now, Joseph  Kelleman!''What the heck was going on!He looked down and saw Matt giving him two thumbs up, and managing a slight smile. Ohhh, Matt had brought him up here. Well, now or never. He grabbed on, and he did it!While he swayed back and forth he saw his parents smiling. Well, he saw them smiling upsidedown, but either way, it was success.

Item_Response: I live in the circus, just about all my life Ive been here, its hard but it can be very fun. Every morning its get up, get dressed, clean up after the animals, do your chores, eat breakfast, do some school work, practice, eat lunch, get ready for show, practice more for show and do the show.            I have to live like this everyday, it can get annoying, but you can't quit my family is in the circus with me. They can tell you how hard it is too, the clowns when I have time will sometimes let me ride their unicycles, its hard luckily I don't have to do that for a show, then I have to care for the animals more.             You will be surprised by how much you have to do shows, every few days you put on a new show. I have to help put up the tents, bring the animals in, fed the animals, get everything to the places they need to be and always be prepared for the worst in the circus life.             There are many animals we have to take care of, leopards, lions, tigers, elephants, chimpanzees and more but there are a lot of them. We have special trainers for the animals to do their acts with, I take care of the horses and elephants mostly, the elephants are the smelliest animal I'll ever meet!               My act is standing on two running horses, and then when they start getting farther apart I do the splits with my feet on different horse backs. Many of my family members travel with us, and other people I know come with us. Many of the people in the circus are either from my family, or my neighborhood I lived in.              Back when I lived in my neighborhood I went to sleep at 8 p.m. but here, I don't get to sleep till 12 in the morning. Living in the circus is hard, and it takes forever to get used to, but when you do get used to it, you won't ever go back.             Bad part is, if you wan to be an acrobat, you have to be right body shape and have determination. Some people join for fun, some wanting to see the world while having a fun job, many come by themselves and have no family with them. When you come by yourself, it feels like you are a stranger in a world of people knowing each other.            Life in the circus can be hard, after awhile of living with it you will start to like it. Being i the circus isn't just doing fun things all the time, it has to do hard work, determination and many chores and jobs you need to do, so don't think its all merry good time here, think and study what you do before you join.

The super-sonic boom is were you swing on a thin vine  then onto a trampoline, then a summer-sault  and land on a horse. I saw the man do this and I left.             I walked into Markus's training room and watched him juggle the knifes. 'Hey he yelled 'Hey I yelled back ' Do you wanna try?' he asked 'no thanks' I smiled and left. We were all getting ready for our last show this year,  this would be the 40th year. I'm 11 so this is my fifth year.          I walked into my training room and went to the ropes. A woman yelled across the room. ' I hurt my leg really badly'          The circus got cancelled and we are preforming tonight.I felt really bad that it got cancelled, HONK HONK! Item_Response: Circus Tragedy              I Walk in, so many lights! It's Huge! I sit down in aisle 5, section 3, just about inbetween the entrance and the performers! as the first Performer comes through he looks crazy with a red nose and rainbow hair and he is juggling! it is amazing it looks like hes juggling five knives!                As the clown walks out I look up and see a man with one foot on a very small tightrope,  I wish I could do that! Suddenly he falls but the circus has not set up the net! He bangs his head on the ground and his brain splatters everywhere! I rush down with the rest of the crowd to take some of his brain home as a souvenier!              As the circus medics come they tell everyone to put his brain down so they might have a chance to put it back in.   When I home I ask all my friends to give me some money so they all give me $1000 then I take all that money and donate it to the man who's brain splattered all over the floor. I still have some of his brain as a memory from that circus.                                               Circus Tragedy By Sean Brogan

Item_Response: Life in the circus isn't as easy as most think it is. Learning the circus routines is hard because you need to be on time when you are doing tricks and need to be confident in how you are doing. Circus performers do 10 shows a week and travel 20,000 miles in seven months just to do performances. All you do is work from sunup to sundown and after that, they still have to perform. Most circus performers are wiped out after they are done performing. They even cant go to bed until 12:00. Imagine riding a unicycle and doing a trick at the same time. Well that is what they do. They are always away from home and I cant even imagine being that home sick.           When you are in the circus, you live in a trailor. You sleep and groom yourself in there too. When circus performers wake up, they eat breakfast in a pie car which is where performers eat their breakfast, lunch, and dinner. Can you imagine that?! Since performers perform at night, they dont eat much dinner before they go out on stage or else they will puke. They perform weekly plus a matinee which is an afternoon show. When most performers have nothibng to do, they are practicing. Kids practice juggling and scrobatics while adults practice flying up in the air and balancing on wires.            Now you know how hard it is in life in the circus. If you want to join the circus, make sure you are confident and ready for any expectations coming your way because you are in for a ride. Also be strong and practice practice practice. Remember, practice makes perfect.

Item_Response: One day I Was walking down the street and I saw a poster that said that anyone who wanted to be in the circus to come to 972 Light road. I really wanted to be in the circus so I took home the poster and showed it to my parents. At first they thought I was just kiding. I kept on telling them that I wanted to be in the circuc. Later on they got tired of me asking so they said yes and took me. It took us some time to get to the adress on the paper but we finally got there                  When we were signing up the owner said that I needed an adult to come both of my parents decided to come with me.After we signed in the gave us a room and told us that they would find out what we were good at tomorrow. Tomorrow comes and they come and get us to find out what we are good at. They find out that I'm good at tight rope walkink, my dad is good at doing stunts and that my mom is good at training animals                    When they tell us that they are not haveing shows until next week everybody is sad at first. Then we realize that this gives us extra time to practice our acts. Next week comes and we are all ready. As we are getting ready to put on the show we start to see people comming through the doors. By the time all the seats were filled with people we were all ready to put on a show.

The crowd starts 'booing' at him. He feels ashamed of himself. Sammy, a friend of his who is in the circus saw it all. Sammy in his point of view it was a simple mistake that any one could have done. Manny felt horrible about this incident others were just laughing at him.                                                                                                                                                                                                               Sammy tried to make Manny feel better, but he didn't succeed. Manny then got so mad that he didn't want to talk to anyone now. He was angry and mean now. Sammy from his point of view saw Manny acting weird like never before.                                                                                                                                                                                         Manny went again and came out performing and he fell again and he was okay with it and he started laughing at himself. Sammy now saw him in his point of view very happy and he was being himself.                                                                                                                                                                                                                               Manny went back onstage and performed better. He didn't fall and he did other stuff as well while he was riding on the unicycle . Sammy saw him in his point of view as him back again  as normal.                                                                               THE END

Item_Response: Life At The Circus                    Do you think working at the circus is fun?Well your mostly WRONG!  I Christopher T will tell you what I do at the circus.       Circus workers work all day with very little brakes.   It can also be dangerous.Like if you fall of the tightrope during performance then your messed up big time!  One time a guy was doing a triple backflip off a elephant and he got all stomped on and died.  Thats why the circus doesnt like to hire people who will most likely do that these days.       Not everything at the circus is boring.The circus is dangerous doesnt   mean it isn fun.  It is fun because were risking to do stuff like that.  A very risky and my favorite is the human canon.  Its a canon used to launch performers through the air.       I live in South Carolina.Well at lease thats were I used to live there   before I became part of the circus.  Lets just say for now that I live everywere the circus goes to perform.  The reason why we can't live in a house is because we only stay for a week in one place and thene pack our bags and go somewere else to perform.       Wait,  I forgot to tell you guys about the things we do when were   not performing or practicing.  We still have to work no matter what.  I do chores (yep, we do chores still) like feed the animals.  We eat at a cart called a pie cart which doesnt have pies there sadly.  And we clean our own trailers.           Well thats all I do at the circus so that means I told you everything   that I do there so this case is closed.

Item_Response: Life at the Circus            One one day, Bob asked hs parents if he can be a performer at the circus. First, his parents denied his request and  said,' The circus  is too dangerous for you to join. Your father and I both love you so much so we don't want to see you at a young age.'           'Well, I am an adult now so I have my own decisions of what I want to be. So, no matter you agree or not I am going to join the circus.            A few days later, Bob went to his room and packed up his clothes and everything else he needed.Since Bob had his own car, he took off driving to the Bellini Circus. When he arrived, he applied to join the circus. The manager said,' If you want to be in the circus, you'll need years of practice,'           ' Sure, I am all ready. I don't care if I have to practice for years, being a circus performer is my dream.', replied Bob.            The manager took  Bob to the room where all the newcomers belong. ' Bob, this will be the room that you practice in. If you need any help you can ask the teacher here, Jimmy.' Bob wanted to learn how to juggle so he took three balls and tried to juggle. He failed like 300  times but he did't give up. He walked up to Jimmy and asked,' Hey, Jimmy I need help on juggling balls.'            ' Jimmy took two balls and started juggling. See, Bob the trick is that you always keep your eyes on the balls so you won't loose control. Start just with two balls, learn from the basics.'             After two years of practice, Bob finally became a professional circus performer. He began juggling rings and walking on tightropes. He performed at the Bellini circus for five years. In the sixth year, he missed home. In the circus, there are no phones or any devices that can contact your relatives.  He started crying, whining that he wants to go home. He tried to sneek out of circus but got caught for about ten times.             At the performance in San Francisco, where his home is. He was performing walking on tightropes. He felt homesick when he was walking on the rope and he fell off. The manager annouced ' Sorry, one of our professional performer fell off the rope, named Bob.              A woman from the audience got out of her seat and walked to the performance area. It was Bob's mom. She looked at the performer named Bob and there it was, her son, laying down on the floor moaning in pain. ' Oh, poor Bob, if you had listened to me, you wouldn't be in a mess like this.            She dialed 911 and the ambulance came. They carefully put Bob in the ambulance and brought him to the hospital. The doctor said that he had his bones fractured in his right leg. When Bob woke up, he saw his mother. ' Oh, mom. Am I glad to see you. I was crying almost everyday because I missed home. Well, here I am, home in San Francisco. Oh by the way, thank you, mom for rescuing me from the circus. It was a nightmare! There are no phones to call home and barely any free time. All you do there is just practice, practice, and pactice.If I had just listened to you I wouldn't be here, in a hospital bed where my leg is fractured.'             When Bob's leg healed he went home and apologized to his mother and father for not listening to them. Later on, when Bob wanted a new job, he will always ask his parent if they agree or not.

Item_Response: CIRCUS                                                 BY:Kenna Sanchez                                                             Joining the Circus                                              Before you start joining the circus, you need to show us                     some tricks that you have. After you show us some of your                    tricks we give you a contract for it. When you're approved                     for being a circus member we show you all of our tricks.                     We first start with juggling! Then there are different levels                    when you get even better at it!                                                                    Schedule                                               First, you wake up and get dressed. Then you eat breakfast.                     all of the circus crew get together and start practicing for the                     big show. We usually practice Monday, Tuesday, Wednesday,                                      and Friday. On Thursday we have a break and on Saturday                     that's when we perform! Before we perform on Saturday we                     cool off and wait till we get called on the stage.

Item_Response: Being in the circus might be a little scary because you have to go and see about 1000 people in the the seats and fun because you may have many adventures.The first thing i will do is wake up in the mo ring and dress up in my cloths and go to school and study when i get out from school at 2:00.And then go to the circus and practice.The first thing I will see is people training animals and people training. What am gonna do is doing jokes for the London show in 5 days and we people and kids have to get ready for the big show.For now we are practicing.The people in the show is Tom the lion trainer, Rick is going to be the motorcycle in the cage, Joe the clown like me,elephants,monkeys,tigers,and lions are going to be in it.we are done practicing and going home.I wake up and do the process.We have 4 days left and we have to get our show on today not London but in Chicago. I  wake up i don't go too school and i get in the plane with my family and we go to London.The circus is big and we can stay in a hotel.I get every thing ready and i gave a water gun and a horn and my friend Joe and we made all the kids laugh. it was fun.

Item_Response: The Circus                                                                                                                                                                                                                      I  went to the circus one time and i was pretty nervous but it was cool when I walked the circus all i saw was a lot of performers like acrobats and clowns that scared me but i just went to go sit down in the seats then the show was about to start and i was excited then the show started i saw flashing lights  then the acrobats came out swinging  but i thought it graceful then the clowns came that was scary to me but one clown wasn't that scary he was nice and gave me a balloon that was a poodle.Then the acrobats came out again which i thought was nice but then something terrible had happened when the acrobats were doing their performance they were swinging and that's when something bad happened what happened is the girl accidentally let go of the swing and fell into the net they keep there so if they fall they won't get hurt but she did get hurt and the sad and weird thing is the net wasn't there and she took a hard fall and everybody was shocked and they screamed and screamed and they called 911 we all had to leave. My experience at the circus wasn't that great and i did feel bad for the girl at the circus when she fell and for me that circus experience wasn't the greatest but at least i got to go to the circus and that was my experience at the circus.

Item_Response: Life in a Circus                             Life as a circus fun but its hard its fun becuase  you get to do tricks and have a good time but its hard becuase sometimes you can't do some of the tricks. I have to wake up early so I could eat then  I have to go to school next I come  back from school and  we get ready to do the show at night. Sometimes it's hard becuase you have to dedicate yourself to go to the next level and you have to work day and night. After you have to practice doing tricks like doing flips summer-salting and that gets you exsuasted but you have to keep going and going. Then you have to dance and practice you acts. Next you have to travel all around the world and its hard because you have to live in the trailer.                               The you have to clean up and my clown friends help me clean up after the show then we all go to bed. Next we go to different country's and preform and sometimes we make friends with the people and the give use high fives and say good job. Next we pack up and we go to the next state and we preform. Then some of our tricks is that we walk on lines and try not to fall down. Next we ride  motocycles in a circle cage. All these tricks we do are hard so we have to practice and practice. After we make the animals do somet tricks too.                        All the things in the circus we do take lots of  practice and hard work. The circus is fun becuase you get to hang with your friends and in the show to. Next its kind of fun traviling around the world. Then its amazing when you see your friends preform and  there tricks. We do fun things with the animals like make them jump over things. It's really fun working in the circus you could have lots of fun with all of your friends and family. Then you could be proud of  your family to suporrt you. So thats how it is in the circus.

Item_Response: Life In the Circus         Life in the circus is fun but difficult at the same time. It also takes a lot of hard work and heart. As a circus performer, you also have to dedicate yourself. It's fun at the same time because you get to learn tricks like the somersault or a back-flip. Life in the circus is fun but difficult at the same time. Here are some details on living a circus life.          To get into the circus you must train very hard. You must do flexibility for an acrobat. You must be brave for dealing with the lions. You also must have funny jokes if you want to be a clown. Training is very important to join the circus.          Lastly you must do these following things:   You must get up get, dressed, eat breakfast, and then go to school like a normal child. You must finish school, come to the trailer, eat a snack, and then do your chores again like a normal child. Then you have to go practice for the circus when your done with your chores. After your practice, you eat dinner, and you must get ready for your show. Lastly, after your show you take a shower, brush your teeth, wash your face and get ready for bed. Then you have to repaet that routine every day.           That is how life in the circus is difficult and fun.

Item_Response: Today I should pratice why? Well I for the first time get to tame a lion. Now you must be wondering why im doing this. This isn't for me to just goof around its because I join the circus.Most of the kids are going to juggle or do acrobatics. I am finnaly old enough to tame a lion and its a shocking surprise. This is not for me its for the audience. The tent is sent up and all the kids and adults are  ready!                                      We are in New York praticing at our big red tent for tonight. Taming a lion was normal one hand with a chair and the other with a whip. When I was done with that I went to see the others.I saw some clowns going inside a little car which was amazing how they all fit. Then I went to see some circus acrobats. One of them fell off luckily there was a net underneath so the acrobat got off and climbed back up. I saw cirus jugglers tightrope walkers and circus horses.        I went back and groomed the horses. Some people were sent to put up posters everywhere. I looked out of the tent and noticed the sun going down. I also noticed alot of people buying some tickets. I know you must think if you did it you would get stage fright but once you get use to it it actully pretty fun. When everyone was seated and the sun went down a man yelled in a mircrophone, 'LETS BEGIN!' and so we did.Circus music played and I saw the tightrope walker walk slowly then fast, then a man threw a cane at the tight rope walker. The tight rope walker caught it almost falling off. I noticed a lot of shocked faces everywhere this shock was a surprised shock. There were some circus acro bats swinging and tossing each other. It was amazing how they dont fall its like there a feather when they get thrown in the air then they grab on amazing!        It was later my turn to do my trick I was thinking to my self i can do this and so i went on the stage with a whip on one hand and a chair on the other. I whipped the lion and the lion roared. I put my chair up quickly so I won't get attacked. The lion was sitting there doing nothing. I had to finish quickly or the audience will get bored. I added some things i whipped the lion hard and the lion got up fast. I yelled, 'ha! ha!' the lion was walking back into its cage. Everyone cheered a I noticed a scratch on my cheek. I bowed and went off stage. I watched some clowns get in a small car and drive around. I heard some people whispering and clapping.        I yawned as we were done. We took down the tent and we got in the pie car to travel to another place. Its fun but yet busy. Dangerous but normal. I grabbed some banges and put on my cheek. For my opinion its dangerous and hard. I would need more pratice. I wish i could tell more but im wiped out.

Item_Response: Life in a circus can be really fun, but can be tough and busy.You'll have to peform or practice everyday.Take care of the animals and still go to school.It evens takes skills to entertain the audience.         Skills are one of the most important things to peform.You need to have a skill to be an acrobat or a trapeze artist.Even a clown because you need to have skills of entertaining or have sense of humor.If you want to do something people can notice you need to have skills.Having skills can impress the people.         Being in a circus can be really fun.It also helps you excercise instead of sitting and watching tv.You can also travel around the world.You can also get to know more about the people travling with you.They are very impressive and skillful.You might get your fear over clowns by being with them if you are.         Even though being in a circus is fun, it's also busy and hard.You might get old of the people your with.You'll might not be able to make more friends.It's hard to keep track of school and the circus.You might miss home,friends, and your family.There might not be a place to call home and you are probably tired peforming all day.You might not like the uniform if you have one because they might be icthy and you have to wear them all day.         Being in circus can  really be busy and fun.It can aslo be dangerous or easy.The circus it's mostly for entertaining people.It's not games it's about the circus' hardwork.

Item_Response: Circus Life by Maxwell Lee Warren   If you think you can go to join a circus with any kind of talent, your right. If you could be any kind of person in a circus what would you be? A lion tamer, type-rope walker, or a trapeze artist?   If you chose trapeze artist that was the same thing I chose. One of the upsides of being in the circus is that you get the chance to travel the world. Maxwell has worked all over the planet, including Australia, Japan and all over North America. 'The circus has given me the opportunity to go to so many different places and meet so many different people. I travel on the road with 100 people who are like a circus family to me, who are with me the whole time. When you're young, it's the time to do it. It's the time to travel, the time to grow and experience your life.'

Item_Response: The circus By: Anna V. Roth                                                                                                                   There was a girl named Anna she was part of a circus she was about 11 years old. Anna's dad owed a circus  when Anna was born she was naturally acrobat and so was her little sister named Gwyn.                   Anna and Gwyn were as graceful as birds flying threw the sky when they were practicing. One day Anna and Gwyn's dad said, 'girls how about you practice a very special trick for Saturday.' Anna asked her dad why an extra special trick is some one really important going to come to their show? The girls father said yes the president was coming to their show and is going to bring his daughter and it is her birth day.               When Saturday came around Anna and Gwyn were both so nerves to preform in front of the president. when Anna got up on the bar and swung and did 3 somersaults and a pike then Gwyn grabed her hands. Then jumped back on to the plat form the crowed went wild. The president's daughter told her dad 'This is the best birthday i have ever had' her dad almost started to cry.

Item_Response: Every day at the circus I wake up  early, to begin for a hard day. I have to go to school, do chores, practice, and perform. First, I go to school. Then, I do my chores and practice. After that, I eat, and after that I perform. The long show is finally over at ten thirty, and I am so tired! I am finally in bed at twelve A.M., which might seem late, but it's not when you get up at nine.     To get into the circus, we all had to have some sort of special talent that we were really good at. The rooms we stay in are small, so we can't really have any big animals as pets.     We move around a lot. There are bad things and good thing about being able to move around. The good things are getting to travel the world. It makes geography class a lot easier. Another good thing is getting to see and meet new people every week. A few bad things are not really staying in one place for long. Also, not being able to stay and enjoy being in the presents of one place for a long time. Last, we are away from home a lot.     We work with many different people from all across the world. Some speak different languages, but it if they seem nice we still figure out ways to be friends.

Item_Response: Last year I had ran away from family to join a circus. At first I thought it would be fun, but now that I'm in a circus I see that it is very challenging. Since I once worked at zoo, I agreed I would take care of the animals and train them. Its VERY hard work!!      Every morning I feed the horses, lions, seals, and chimpanzees. Next I go get somthing to eat at the pie car. Then I help set up the tents, lights, and music for tonights show.  A few other trainers and I work with the animals. Yesterday we got a new animal, a cheetah I named Namarah. I got to work with Namarah on jumping through a ring of fire. She did really good!!!!      That night people came through the tent talking, laughing and guessing what show we might put on for them. We were all nervous for the big show. We had planned to do things we had never done before! As Seth, the director of our circus walked out in front of the big crowed and started anouncing some things that we might do tonight, I help Namarah into her outfit.      The first to go out was Zan, our chimpanzee, and his trainer, Bob. As Zan juggled bowling pins and rode a unicycle I ran out with Namarah. Namarah jumped over obsticles and through tunnels. I heard some of the audiance go 'OOOHHH' and 'AAAHHH'. Namarah stopped where she was supposed to, to start getting ready to jump through the Ring of Fire. I set the tiny ring a couple yards away from Namarah and set it on fire. She stared at me, fear in her eyes. I mouthed ' Do it just like we been practicing.' She seemed to understand. I saw her load back and fire herself right and the ring. Then she leaped, I held my breath and closed my eyes.       All of a sudden I heard screams of joy and clapping. I open my eyes to see Namarah standing right next to me, rubbing her head against my leg. I bend down and look her right in the eyes and say 'You did great!!!!!!.' Then I kiss her on top of the head, and she licks me in the face. I stand back up again and take a bow, I see Namarahs eyes sparkle with joy.     I learned that a circus life is tough but Namarah always makes it fun.

Item_Response: One day there was a boy and his mother.   The boys name was Frank.   It was his first time ever going to the Circus.   They were in the car when they finaly got there all he saw was lots of red and white stripes on tents.   He said it was 'Amazing.'   he told his mom to park already,so she did.   He ran as fast as he can to go buy food and drinks so he can get in the tents fast and get front row seats.                  After waiting for thirty minutes the lights when off and the other shining lights turned on.   All Frank was focus on was the animals.   Frank loved animals and was so excided he saw them on stage.   The host came out with a stick and cards on his hand then said, 'Lady`s and Gentlemen, put your hands together for the Jugglers.'  Frank saw many Jugglers some of them even had sticks with fire and some juggling rings.   Frank was so amazed he couldn`t keep an eye off the show.   Until he saw the Lion Tammer.             The Lion Tammer was herting the poor lion than he got so sad he didn`t even want to see that part.   Thankfully that part was over and Frank was able to enjoy the show know.   Frank was ready to see the Acrobats.   He likes how they swing up into the air.   'It looks like they are flying, he says.   Frank likes how the Acrobats work together to swing up in the the air.   The Acrobats bowed  and it was time for the clowns.          'The entrance was funny ', said Frank. They came out of the curtains in a tiny  car and when the clowns came out there was about seven clowns that came out of the tiny car.   Frank was wondering how they all fit in the tiny car it was the size of his dog`s house.    'The clowns were really funny ', said Frank.  It was the end of there act and everyone was clapping.    Frank was still wondering how all seven clowns fit in one tiny car.             The show ended about two hours later.    It was so great.   Frank was sad that they were leaving home but he hopes his mom would lethim come next year with his freinds.

Item_Response: My Grand Performance                     This was it. This was my last circus act for the rest of my life. I had been training for this one for months. It was the biggest performance we had done yet. It was called the The Shining Star. I was waiting at the end of the tight rope, waiting for the signal that let me on. I was extremely nervous, but excited at the same time. I was supposed to be on a unicycle, and juggling five balls across the tight rope. The horses and the elephants were out. It was my turn. I mounted my unicycle. I made sure that I had the five balls in my hand, and started out on the rope. I wobbled at first but I don't think anyone noticed.                              I Smiled at the crowd and started to juggle. I started out with three, then four, (I was doing great!) then......... I was falling.....spinning forward,and sideways, I landed on the trampoling with a SMACK!!!, and fell off of it. I luckily landed on my feet. I wasn't badly hurt, on the outside. The inside of me was what hurt the most. I had let my whole team down. I just smiled, and ran out. Back stage, everyone crowded aruond me. They all asked me if I was okay. I told them all that I was sorry, and I had let them down. We were sure to lose the contest now.                         At the end of the show, the announcer told the winner. It was us!!!! Everyone cheered! It was great!! I had no idea how though... I mean.. I fell. The other team did perfect. Later I talked to the announcer and asked him how we won. He told me that I did absolutely wonderful, and the way that I had jumped off the rope, spun in the air, landed on the trampoline, and bounced off with a perfect landing on the feet! I was amazed! Did he really think that I had done that on purpose?! I started to tell him what had really happened, but the crew came in and told me I was late to celebrate! I guess falling wasn't so bad after all.

Item_Response: I opened my eyes. Just another average Monday in circus life, or so I thought at that time. I sighed, and started to slide out of my bed on a circus trailer. I looked at the clock on the wall-6:51 A.M. I decided that, since I normally got out of bed at 7:00 A.M., nine more minutes of sleep wouldn't hurt. I plopped back down onto my bed and started to close my eyes.        I was awoken again by a light knock on my door. I bolted out of bed and looked at the clock again-7:16 A.M. I had overslept for the first time! I quickly got dressed and went to the pie car. There, I found that most of the performers were already done with breakfast. The ringmaster noticed me and said, 'Is this the first or second time you overslept, Emily?' I sighed once more when the ringmaster had gone. The day was already starting out badly.         I quickly finished breakfast and went to the schoolhouse. Fortunately, that went well, unlike when I got up and, as I would soon find out, my practice and performance time.        At 3:30 P.M., school was over, and it was break time. I saw that we had arrived in our destination-Kansas City. I played a short while with my teacup chihuahua, Teacup, and started practice early, thinking that would make up for me oversleeping. Unfortunately, that was not true.       I began my practice as normal. I started to jump from a trampoline onto a horse's back. After several times of doing this, I began to relax and daydreamed that nobody had noticed me oversleep. My daydreams eventually evolved into a dream of seeing my family and living back in Miami, Florida. Oh, how I missed that time. But I had taken a liking to acrobatics and determinedly joined the circus when I was 11. Now I had been in the circus for five years now. I have traveled all over North and South America. Now, still daydreaming, I leaped again from the trampoline, imagining I was bouncing down the stairs. 'THUMP!' I was jolted from my daydream by pinpricks of pain shooting up my leg.       I was surprised to find myself sprawled in the dirt, wondering how I had gotten there. I had thought I was jumping down the stairs to the a kitchen. I then remembered that I was in the circus, and I was practicing jumping off a trampoline onto a horse's back. I realized I had jumped straight off a trampoline 15 feet in the air with no horse to support my fall.       Wincing, I tried to get up. I made the mistake of putting my weight on my injured right leg and collapsed. I heard other performers arriving for practice. A man leading an elephant saw me first. He ran to me and called to the others for the ringmaster. He then also left to find the ringmaster. No! I thought. I already have embarrassed myself once, but I will not be embarrassed twice! I slowly got up, and started to limp around. After a while, the pain in my leg subsided, so I decided to continue practicing as if nothing had happened. The ringmaster arrived with a worried face. I rushed up the trampoline.       Seeing me seemingly all right, the ringmaster's expression changed from worried to confusion. He then became angry. He turned to the man who was leading the elephant and started to scream something about tricking him. I just continued to practice, trying to ignore the pain in my leg.        After dinner, we all started to prepare for the show. By now, the pain in my leg had nearly gone, so I decided I could make it though the show. My mind insisted on it-performing in a circus show, having fun performing, and seeing the audience so absorbed into my performance were the reasons I joined.        I went with the others backstage. After a while, I heard the announcer announce my name. I took a deep breath. In. Out. Shakily and painfully, I got to my feet. I went in the direction of the stage. In. Out. I emerged onstage, and I heard the audience clapping. In. Out. I climbed the trampoline and waited for my horse, Creamy, who was named for the color of her fur, mane, and tail. Not yet. Not yet. NOW! I jumped off the trampoline just as my leg bent in an awkward position-the position my leg was in when I fell at practice.        I lurched in midair, and was about to slam into the ground. My life is over, I thought. I had forgotten about the safety net, and had not set it up. But just then, Creamy doubled back and, amazingly,  caught me. The audience clapped again, thinking this was part of the show. I rode Creamy back backstage while murmuring to her softly, praising her.        When the show was over, the ringmaster praised Creamy too, saying I was lucky to have such a brilliant horse. If not, I would have died that day.        Nearly a month has passed since then. My leg has long since healed, and I continue to practice and perform successfully with Creamy, my life-saving friend and companion.

Item_Response: Today, i'll be sharing some information about the circus. The circus let's you travel places you've never been before while travaling with your new family.                                    You should join the circus because you can travel to new places. Here are a few reasons why . First, you will be able to go on many adventures with your 'family.' For example, you may go to Hawaii for a performance and have fun snorkling. Next, you will be able to try new foods. You can try some exotic Chinese food that you have never tried before. Finally, you will be able to explore new cultures. You can go to India and learn about their culture and festivals like Diwali.                        Join the circus because you can make a new and supportive family. Not convinced, i'll give you a few reasons. First, you will have many people who will care for you and love you just the way you are. Some kids in school might be insulted because of their flexibility. In the circus you won't  have that problem because your family and friends all are very flexible. Next, you will h ave people who unerstand you. if you feel down or angry your family will know how to comfort you because they have probably been through this before. Finally, you will have someone to trust because in the circus, most of the people there are very well trained.                          Joining the circus made my life better. If you love gymnastics and dancing, try joining you might find your home while touring the world!
