Item_Response: About twenty years ago, I was a student in Lark Creek elementary school. My teacher clapped her hands and said, 'Students, I have an important announcement to make. Our school has won one rare ticket from the five to attend the Bellini Circus in the front row seats! That's right, one of you very lucky students will be able to win the free ticket by writing the best essay in class'.       As I walked home with my best friend we both discussed how we would write a essay. The instant I reached home, I started to write my essay:       'If anyone would think special talents were gifted to you, that is wrong. Even people in the circus must work harder than ever; often sacrificing extra time with friends and family to achieve their dream of performing in the circus. Take Philippa for example. When she was 11, she had her heart set on being a performer. She gave up everything and concentrated on her dance and performing. This is how to achieve your dreams.       Being part of a circus doesn't mean a free pass from school, in fact the one room classroom has everything a regular class has from a whiteboard to tests. Since circus performers are from around the globe, classrooms are often filled with a 'mixed bag' of students. The circus performers live in a trailer where there is a pie car (it is like a restaurant), a classroom, and of course a home for performers to live in.                                                                                                              When school is over it is time for some fun; circus style. The children get to see what the others are training and finally, kids get to try some tricks them self. People in the circus must be daring and adventurous. Tricks may include: leaping form a trampoline onto a horse's back, somersaulting from a horse's back, acrobatics, juggling, walking baby leopards on leashes, and training animals such as elephants, lions and chimpanzees.       Like all other jobs, working in a circus has ups and downs. One of the upsides is that you get to travel around the world. Performers get to meet people from around the world with interesting backgrounds. Another pleasure is the thrill of performing in front of a live audience. The downside of working in a circus is that circus performers  work for long periods of hours. In addition, performers are away from their family and home.       As you an see circus performers have a different, but somewhat hard life. If you work hard, your dream can come true'.       I looked down at my essay, and realized that I didn't care to win. Writing this essay was the gift after all. I had learned so much about the circus and realized that I might want to be there. I might want to do that. Being a glamorous star of the circus became my dream that day.       The next day, I walked to school with my essay in my hand. I told myself, 'I don't want to win, I have already won a big dose of inspiration'.       I handed in my essay in the morning as the teacher smiled. In an hour the teacher would announce the winner. As the clock ticked, it was hard for me to concentrate. Finally, the teacher announce the winner, and it was me. I had won a front seat ticket to the Bellini Circus. My career seemed to fly from then on. I got to meet Philippa, and she gave me a few words on how to succeed. I worked harder than ever at gymnastics now. I decided that I would awe the audience with my difficultly and flexibility. That is how I reached my dream and became The star of the circus. I was nicknamed Philippa #2. I tell youngsters around the world that it all started with a little dose of inspiration.

Item_Response: Life in a Circus   Hello im Ami and im going to tell you a little abouy my circus life.first i am 16 years old and i have 3 brothers. Ihave been in the circus for almost 9 years. So let get with the subject.When i am practicing it takes all you got we have to dance, jump,jugle,throw fire, and do even harder more dangerous stuff.We practice for more than 2 whole months.Then we perform in the circus.           When we get to the circus we have to set up everything then start.It is not easy,it is a very tough job.I love my job though. I think the toughest thing is the string i hate it.You have to be very balanced espeally on the one wheel bike.           When we dont put on a good show we are very disapionted,becuase we work so hard on being in the circus it really puts us downn. after we know that we just needed more practice on our work so we can do better next time.when we dont do a good job our directer will make it harder on us and in our practices.When it is so bad we can get kicked off of the whole team intill we are ready to do better and make more progress.               so that is preety much about the circus life. It can get trickey and a little to hrad but it is worth it if you just try your best and belive thaat you can make mor progress the next time.So be ready for the time of your life cause your not want to miss it.                                                                TRUST ME!!!!!!!!

Item_Response: I , Kaylin Ayers remember the first time I went to the circus. When we, my family and I, arrived there were many people there. before we went into the big tent we got some treats when we went inside we saw many performers getting ready for the show they were about to perform. We found some seats and sat down. All of the performers were getting in there positions. The show was about to start.                                                                                                                                                                                                                       First there was a man and woman holding onto ropes swinging back and forth. Then the lady let go and the gentleman caught her.  Then the man let go. The woman fell, but as she was falling she grabbed onto a laced rope that hung from the ceiling. she gracefully went down the rope. The crowd went roaring.               After that some clowns came out on unicycles. They kept falling and bumping into each other. It was very funny.  then there was a lion. It jumped and roared. It did its master told it to. There were also people on horses doing tricks. Then there was a man  that walked  across a tightrope. There was also a woman that was able to put herself in a very small box. then there was a man juggled many figure.             IT was very interesting and exciting to see all of those amazing acts. At the end of the show we were able to meet some performers and ride on the horses. It was a night I will never forget.

Item_Response: Today we had a circus performence at the collusieum.(It was at 10:00 P.M.) We needed to practice really hard so we missed school.Our whole crew ate eggs with bacon and then we got started. Some of us had to wait a little longer because we were full.When we wre done taking a break we went on the road to The Collusieum.             We arivved arrived at 7:00 A.M. because we left the house at 2:00 A.M. We unpacted and went to praqctice. My mom and I are partners at acrobatics and gymnastics.  And my brother and dad are partners at going in the cannon and getting shot out. The rest of our crew ride horses elephants, blow fire, and more! (They all picked what they are good at.)              At 5:00 P.M.we all pitch in to clean the animals but we all forgot the supplies! We didn't know what to do so we had to waste half our money to buy the supplies. (The whole crew pitched in.we were very sad those few min.)               It was 10:00 P.M. and we had to start.(The animals were spick and span.) We made a big entrance and got started. My mom and I did an amazing job in the air. In the ending of our turn my mom did a unbelievible move that no one could do it exept her!               Then it was everybodys' turn. It was incredible. Item_Response: The Burn Down             Once there was a very popular circus tent,one of the biggest tents in the world.Every day hundreads of people came to watch the performers do there stunts.In the tent,there is a hidden door under the circus walls. The door leads to were the performers get ready.A long time ago the room use to be a big gas station under it.They need to be very carful of fire because they have all kinds of machines. if there is the slightest fire the tent will explode!             One day a very thoughtful woman was getting in her costume to perform. She had to get paint on her face and gether wig and nose on.The woman had hair like a clown so she didn't need a wig.This is the first time they ever saw hair like that.Her hair was curly and they needed to make it flat so they had to use a flat iron.This is the first time they used a flat iron.When they were done they did not turn off the iron!There was a hair on the flat iron and the hair caught on fire and a piece of paper caught on fire!When they were in the middle of the play BOOM the circus blew up!              Many people were injured and some people died.They shut the circus down and people lost there jobs.They were goind to build a new circus but it would take about one year.Now the worlds most popular circus is burned.

Item_Response: My name is Bob Smith.  I am an 11-year-old circus performer.  I travel around North America with my family.  Circus life is far from all fun and games.  Every day, and sometimes twice a day, we entertain a large audience for many hours.  Everyone works from dawn to dusk.  Here is our normal schedule:       6:30 A.M.: Wake up and prepare for yet another long day.  We head to the pie car for a quick breakfast.        8:00 A.M.: Time for a long, boring day of school.  All the kids are packed into an extremely small trailer, which makes learning hard.  Just like a normal, non-traveling school, our school has tests and progress reports.        3:30 P.M.: School's out!!!  But the work is just beginning.  We have to practice for tonight's show, and for the following shows.  While the crew continues to set up for the show, all the performers practice their respective stunts, such as walking on a tightrope, training wild animals, juggling objects, and jumping on to and off of a horse.  Beinng a good circus performer takes, balance, determination, and concentration.       6:00 P.M.: Everybody returns to the pie car for a light dinner.       7:00 P.M.: Showtime.       10:30 P.M.: The show is finally over.  The audience really enjoyed the performance!  I managed to juggle three bowling pins!  However, I am very tired and eager to go to bed.       11:00 P.M.: I hop into bed.       Circus life is a very tough life.  But it is also very fun. So despite the downsides of circus life, I enjoy it and am eager to take the stage for every performance.

Item_Response: My name is Athiallia Selby and I am with a circus that travels all around the world.I am a acrobat.When I fly into the air during a show I feel very free.Shows sometimes last up to 3 hours.While I wait for my perfomance I watch the other performer do their act. After I am done with the show I am congradulated for doing a nice job.I thank everyone and tell them the same.After all of the acts we all go infront of the audience and bow.Everyone cheers.All of the trainers are very proud of their animals. Item_Response: Circus life       By Fenn McCaulley            My name is Fenn.  I love being part of the circus.  I love the gleam of the crowd's teeth as they cheer for us.  I am a juggler for a huge circus.  I Can't even remember anybody because it is so huge.  I always stick close to my dad and mom since the are the ringleaders.  I know we are only supposed to have one but they insisted it being this way       My dad has been with this circus for his entire life.  My mom also.  I love watching the clowns make people laugh.  I hope to be one of the numerous animal trainers.        We usually stay in a town for a week and then do strenuous work to pack up.  That is what I hate the most. I meet lots of people and many new friends.  Our portable school is just like any else.  It has computers and report cards and we have grades like everyone else.  I really strive toward one day going to a real school and meeting regular people.  I want to live in a neighbor- hood and have friends.       One day I decided to watch a circus show.  I pretended I was a kid in the crowd and it was so cool.  I saw lion tamers and people swinging on the trapeze.  I told myself that one day I would be that good.  That's when I realized I love the circus and would live with it forever and cherish every moment.

Item_Response: April 12, 2010   10:30pm                                Dear Diary,                              Show is over! everyone loves this time of night. I finally get to sleep. Too bad I can't party in the pie car with everyone else because of mom and dad. Mom and dad are so mean to me. They say I have to be in the circus 'till I'm 65, and I can't party inthe pie car 'till I'm 18. And you know what? Today is my birthday. I'm turning 18 today, and I didn't even ggo to the party. They completly forgot. Maybe they don't even care about me..... I don't know.            I'm sorry I don't do this every day, but I barely get even a spare second in a week. From 7:00am to 10:30pm every day, I work and practice my horse riding standing and dismounting my horse, Shamrock. I don't even get a full education. I only do school work 3 hours a day, and right now I'm supposed to be in college.            Today my schedule was even worse. Mom made me practice during school, so I missed learning what an antacedent is. Dad made me do the heap of dishes in the pie car, because I didn't put my dish in the sink. Also, the director got mad at me when on of my bells flew off my bracelet Annie gave me last year. I don't even know if Annie is my friend or not. She just is kind to me. We're both the same age, and we have a lot in common, but she has been avoiding me lately.            Although, one part was good today. I finally did everything perfect on my routine during practice, but my directer didn't even notice I did it flawlessly. The only person(thing) that noticed me was Shamrock, and he was licking and slobbering all over me.           Today was horrible, with one good part, but in the circus isn't that bad, especially when I can actually talk to someone(something) that will listen.

Item_Response: My name is Michael Smith. First, I will tell you what a normal day of circus life is like.       6:30 A.M.  I wake up and go to the pie car to have breakfast. I usually have scrambled eggs and pancakes. Everyone is startingto set things up for tonight's show.       9:00 A.M. I go to school. I learn different languages, sometimes on a computer. When I travel the world, I'll have to know how to speak to the audience!       3:00 P.M.  School's over-I usually grab a quick snack and practice juggling or unicycle riding.           6:00 P.M. I have dinner and prepare for tonight's show when I'm finished.           10:30 P.M. The show is over. I am wore out. Tomorrow, I will have to perform again. Now, I'm off to bed.       Circus life can get stressful!               Now, I will tell you what a performance is like.                I wait for my que at the beginning of the show. When I get the signal that I'm suppost to perform, i run out from behind the tent curtain, do a couple of cartwheels as i go, and I get up on the trampolene. I have to jump on a charging horse.            The horse is released, and I get ready for the jump. when the horse gets close, I jump! If I time it right, I will land on the horse and I will be able to gain control of it. It is a terrifying trick, but I've gotten used to it!            Finally, Circus life can be stressfull and even risky at times. It is fun to watch the audience applaud me for my hard work, though. Circus life is stressful, but it is well worth it!

Item_Response: Hi my name is Stacy and i am an acrobat in the circus.The last circus i was in dumped me for a tight rope walker. Now that made me mad! But that's why i came to Rome. So i can get a fresh start as an acrobat!I have been here for a month and am having my first audience tomorrow. I have been going to the town gym to practice.It was tough competition at the try out but i thought i did well and that's all that maters. i hope i get the part.           I got the results and......I GOT THE PART I AM SO EXCITED!!!!!!!!!! Plus the stage crew seemed really nice. My first practice is tomorrow night,my first gig is next week.                                    *Next week at the show*       My first show was very difficult, i messed up twice,and if i mess up again I'm fired!  So i decided i need to practice more before my show in 2 days.        At the gym I worked on all the gymnastic stuff. i practiced for hours and hours until it was completely perfect......That took a while.After that i thought i would go out for ice cream at freezable. I was told it was the best ice cream in the world!       Then i went home and slept i needed my sleep for tomorrows show.       When i woke i looked at the clock. It was 4:30 P.M. I was late and for sure i was going to be fired. So i ran down to the circus as fast as I could and when i got there everyone was upset.      I went around to my booth and got ready but still no one came to there booths. Then  was soon as i knew it everyone was at my side. Yelling 'where have you been we had to cancel the show because you didn't show!' I said 'I'm so sorry it won't happen again.'     after that the little magic man came and said 'But it's ok because here we're all a family and we stick together.' Every one agreed and called back on the show and in the end I found my true family!

Item_Response: Tiara and the Lost Money                       Not long ago, a baby girl was born and named Tiara. She had long black hair and big brown eyes. Her lips were full and her eyelashes long. Her body shape looked as if it was good enough to be a gymnast. There was nothing more she could possibly want. She had her own room, painted rose pink. Her name was painted on one of the walls. By the time she was eight, she was spoiled rotten. She had candy in her room. She had decorations in her room. All the children at her school adored her because she would always get money from her mom, take it to school, and give them some or buy them something.             One day, when Tiara took money to school, she lost her money somewhere in the school. she asked everyone if they saw it but they all had no clue where it was. She began to cry. Everyone in the area looked at her and began whispering in each others ear. She could hear them say, 'Is she really crying over money? I can't be friends with a crybaby so everybody can be talking about me.' Could this be the end of her popularity? All because of crying? She stood up and told every one to stand up and empty their pockets. Right when she said that everybody did so, maybe she didn't lose her popularity after all. as soon as Joe emptied his pockets there it was, low and behold, Tiara's $50.00!              Everyone gasped. 'Joe, how could you?' everyone gasped. Joe apologized to Tiara but she did not forgive him. It is one thing to borrow, but stealing is not the way. Soon it was time to go outside for carpool. When Tiara got into the car she told her mom what happened. As long as Tiara had her money back her mom was not disappointed.

Item_Response: When I wake up at 7:30 I get dressed head up to the pie cart and enjoy breakfast with a bunch of clowns.The pie cart is not very big but it is big enough to eat a meal.After I finish my breakfast I head over to help groom the animals that take place in the show ,but only for a little while because I still have to practice my own performance.I am an acrobat and do a lot of cool tricks that are still pretty dangerous so I help the workers with the light and settings and most important making sure the tightrope is secure.Some people might find this hard but if you have done it all your life it does not seem                         How I get ready is I stretch before I attempt any tricks .Some of the tricks i do are tricks that take a lot of talent such as;I do a front flip of a trampoline and land gracefully on to a horse back  or I  do a front or even side Ariels.Most of the older acrobats can do more stuff than me but for my age I do pretty good.I also need to eat right that's is why in the pie cart there are a lot of healthy food choices such as;fruits ,vegetables,and meats to.                                                                                                                                    Most living things in the circus are humans but there are some pretty exotic animals.My favorite is the dancing monkey in a tutu her name is cocoa she is very young but is also very friendly.She likes to make friends with the other monkeys but since they are so much older then her they are mean to her but she will always be my friend.Next there is the beautiful white horse named beauty how ironic beauty is quite the diva she will not go anywhere near mud so we always need to make sure to keep her stable clean.next there is a penguin named Pepe he loves to dive in water and swim around and play with crushed ice.Also I cant forget about mist a dolphin I haveknown her since i was a baby.She can leap so high and put so much impact on the water that it wets people in the 20th row.                                                            I love to live on a circus but sometimes i miss my friends back in my old neighbor hood  and i really hope that one day i could see them again or they can come watch me perform my tricks so circus life can fit some life styles but if your like me it will all work out. So remember if you wanna live on a circus dont forget the life you used to have.

Item_Response: One day a regular  summer day in San Diego the wind was blowing the streets were buzzing and the circus was ready to do its Wednesday matinee. In the end this would not be a regular day in circus history to find out what happened in this wacky day in circus history read these paragraphs.         The people had just arrived to the Bellini circus people buying popcorn and cotton candy the performers getting ready for the show and the family's waiting impatiently for the show to start. The lead act was the clowns doing some jokes and some other stuff but just as the clowns ended the circus tent collapsed. People were going crazy this was just like when the Minnesota vikings stadium collapsed except there was nobody in the dome when that happened but today there were thousands of people. The circus director was going crazy so he called the fir department. When the fire department got there they evacuated the rest of the people that hadn't already left the structure. Then the manager soon found out all of the circus animals got loose so he had to call animal control to wrangle the animals. Then came news that some people got injured so we called the medics. They ended up being okay they were just minor injuries. There was still major chaos all around and in the tent.''What happened'' and ''What's going on'' were questions a lot of people had when leaving the venue. They found out that people outside the tent did something to make the tent collapse and fall. To this day nobody knows how the tent fell and who did it. It will probably remain unknown forever. At the end of it all nobody died and only one animal they didn't get back a baby elephant.

Item_Response: Hi. I work in a circus. My name is 'Alex the Acrobat.' (As you can probably tell) I play the part of an Acrobat. I work night and day. Most people think that being in a circus means that you get to play all the time, but that is not true. The circus is about hard work and dedication. I've been working at the circus for 10 years and I still haven't gotten the hang of the schedule.The circus may be a fun place to work at, too, despite all the bad stuff, but you still have to travel a lot of tedious road trips. You also have to put up with schools and colleges that are a little too much on the wacky side.                      If you're wondering why I chose to be an acrobat, my answer would be that doing all that work really pays off when you show all your awesome moves, like front flips and jumping off and catching yourself, to the world (where-as other jobs don't pay off as much).                     One really awesome thing that is probably the reason I joined the circus is that instead of sitting in a desk and looking at a book for geography, we get to see our geography lessons come to life as we travel the world, now that is something truly amazing. So if you're looking for a job and love to meet new people and do new things, why not the circus, you got nothing to loose.

Item_Response: Hello, I am Harold. Lots of people call me Harry. I am 10 years old and I am a circus performer. I entered the circus when I was 5 years old, I was very young to be a performer, in fact the youngest in the whole group of performers. I was recognized for my talent of being funny and being great at gymnastics. Today I am a clown and an acrobat. My back round is very interesting.       Right now I am getting ready for a show. In this show I am a clown. I usually juggle and make kids laugh. Sometimes on the set I make other actors laugh too. I n this show I will barely be on stage. Most of the time when I am on stage I am an acrobat. When I am a clown I tell jokes to kids and try to sell stuff. Since I am in the circus I do not get to see my family and it is very hard for me because I miss them so much. Lots of the other people that are in the circus like me even though I am much younger than them.       Circus life is very hard. You have to practice basically all day. This afternoon I practice for nearly four hours. before that I had a delicious breakfast with bacon and eggs in the pie cart. I am lucky to get such good food from the Pie cart. Lots of parts of being the circus is fun too because I get to be the clown and get to use unicycles and juggling balls and make people laugh. In the circus life is fun and hard.       This is it. It is time to go on stage. I only have one part on stage and it isn't very long. I can't wait. First I act as a mime and pretend I am in a box, even though I am not. Now I am done and I have to put my clown uniform on.       You have to change into new clothes very fast in the circus business. Now I am trying to sell cotton candy and other foods and condiments. It is pretty easy. Tonight I have sold lots of food and now I have to entertain the audience. I am now walking over to a baby. He is very cute. I have a great joke to pull on him. I will run up, jump right over his seat and scare him. Ready, set, go! I ran up and scared him but right when he saw me he started crying loudly.I felt bad so bad. He was crying so loudly that the tightrope walkers on stage were balancing on a rope and got distracted by the loud crying. Lots fell and got badly injured. Soon I heard ambulances. The worst thing was it was all my fault.       Lots of people yelled at me because I ruined people on set had never yelled at me since I came here. I was was scared the most of my boss coming toward me. I new I was fired. One thing I noticed was the crowd was laughing as if it was part of the act. Once my boss came close the only two words he said was 'Thank you.' He said 'We made so much money that it doubled most of high paid shows, even though it wasn't part of the show it was still amazing.' What Harry just noticed was that the tightrope walkers were still on there feet and were in their ending pose. What a show!

Item_Response: Things That Happen In The Circus                                    By Cedrik De Guzman                    From jugglers to clowns the circus is filled with many wonderful things. But behind all that fun, many things happen. The circus is very busy. You have to set up for the show, you have to practice for the show, and do chores. Life in the circus is so busy and tough. This is the life in the circus...                   Long busy hours happen in the circus. But you can't just walk in a circus and be like, 'Oh, I want to be a trapeze artist'. You have to have some sort of talent. Like myself I have the talent to be very flexible. So I'm a acrobat. But also, you have to be focused, sometimes I can't do a trick and I fail.                   Sometimes in the circus you feel lonely. I know you have all the people traveling with you but, you are far away from your family. You also spend a lot of time away from home. A lot of the time, I miss my family, my home, and my belongings. It's very tough being in the circus.                    All together everything in the circus is fun. But it also can be very tough. So next time when you see circus perfromers, think about all the hard work they put into their talent. Many things happen in the circus.

Item_Response: LIFE IN A CIRCUS                                                                  Life in a circus seems very fun, but it is very hard work. You can't just say I want to become a circus performer, you have to train for it. For instance, if you want to do acrobats, you have to have the right body and you have to train for it. If you want to do juggling you have to just train for it. It seems so easy, but sometimes it seems as if you kind of risk your life. Like if your somersaulting off of a running horse, that seems like your risking your life, but that's what trainings for.             It also seems that the circus performers are more your family then your regular family. It seems like this because you are traveling so much and your always away from home. You really have to put your heart in it and concentrate because if you don't, then you might mess up and you don't want that to happen in front of all those people.             And of course you don't just go to school and train, you have to do chores too. You might have to feed the animals, groom the animals, help clean up after every show, or just help get ready for every show. And when your in the circus you usually work from sun up to sun down. So your going to be busy every hour of the day.               It also seems that if your in the circus traveling all the time, you might get a really good experience if your paying attention. It seems like this because you get to travel all around the world. You would probably get to travel to Japan, Russia, Ireland, or even Australia.              And it seems that being in a circus makes you famous because you are well known, and people are amazed by what you can do, and since they're so amazed they tell every one to go see the show. Then when the word gets around, people start to know your name and ask for autograghs. And thats why I think that your famous when your a circus performer.               And when your on tour and away from home. It seems as if you really have no place to call home because your always moving from one place to another. Your going to always be thinking about how your going to do on tonights show, or how everyone else is going to do that effects you.               I've always wondered if the circus performers ever missed their real home and family. I've wondered this because they usually call their circus performing friends family and home. But who knows they might not.              And now that I've talked about how hard it is to be a circus performer, would you want to be a circus performer? If you do, then what would you do, would you do juggling or trapeze? What would you do in the long hours of a circus life?               And like I've said, performing in a circus seems very fun, but it is very hard work. It is also a great experience too. So if your interested in going to a circus, then go to one and see the amazing things they've worked so hard on.

Item_Response: Once there was a girl, Lila, and she worked at the circus with her family. She wakes up in the morning and gets dressed. She dressed in normal khakis and a Nike shirt. She walked to the pie car to get some food.As Lila finished, she saw telling a worker to move the tent further right. The man seemed confused, he did`t seem   to like his job. After breakfast, she walked to the school house.            When she got to the schoolhouse she saw her friend typing up a report on a test at the computers. She smiled and waved. She quickly turned around, I guess because she had to finish the test. Lila walked to her desk and waited for class to begin. When class did begin, she had a good time. They took a test, though, which wasn`t   very fun. Finally it was time to leave. When she walked out it was warm and she wanted to play outside but she had to practice. Lila takes care of the animals.            Lila walks over to a leopard named Carter. She`s known him since kindergarten, when she started. Carter purrs as Lila puts the leash on him. They walk around the area were the tents are being set up and booths are being assembled. Carter was so big and strong at one point Lila rode on his back. Her mother saw her and laughed,   ' Carters getting big isn`t he.' she smiled. Lila just nodded.        Lila fed Bacon the elephant. She loved feeding Bacon. When she was little she got to name him. She had just ate breakfast so she named him her favorite food. When she got done feeding all the animals, and grooming the horses she took a break. It was really nice to relax. Sadly, though, she had to stop at 6:30 for dinner. Soon   her family was done because they have to eat fast. They have a show at 10:30 so they had to rush. By the time it was 10:00 Lila was ready to go. She wore a blue uniform that had shiny purple stripes.            The show was starting and Lila was hugging her leopard close. She was very,very anxious to go on stage, but   Carter made her feel fine. Finally it was show time. Lila and Carter ran up stage. Carter couldn`t stand it, but   Lila always made him wear a tutu. Carter jumped through fiery hoops. Lila spun and juggled and flipped and   hurdled through the air.           As the show spiraled on Carter snuggled and purred as he slep on Lila`s feet. Everyone walks back to the trailers for some reason Carter doesn`t want to go in his cage. He never does on show days. Carter and I both   walk to my trailer and we fall asleep. Carter loves it here at the circus and so do I. There is so much things to do   being here.            Sometimes I wonder what it will be like at other places then the circus. Carter doesn`t want to leave, neither   do I. I hope I can stay here forever.

Item_Response: Circus Day                 Angela Brown sat up, yawning. The sun was only just slowly rising up the hills. For a moment, she was confused. What am I doing here? she thought. Suddenly, the moments of the day before came rushing to her mind. She had been selected to perform in the Bellini Circus as an acrobat. She had been led to a trailer that she was to share with another acrobat, Betsy White. As if the thought had conjured her up, Betsy stood before her, calling  cheerfully,  'Time to get ready!'  The tall, freckled girl always seemed to have a smile. Angela quickly scrambled to change out of her pajamas. The shows were at night, so she didn't need her outfit yet.           Betsy showed her around the circus area after they went to the pie car for breakfast. At 9, they had school. Betsy enjoyed it thoroughly and made many friends, some of which came from different countries!           After school, Angela, Betsy, and their friends ate dinner and quickly changed into their outfits. Angela was exhilarated. She loved seeing the audience and feeling like they had come all the way just to see her! After the show, Angela changed out of her outfit. She crawled into bed and fell asleep immediately, she was so exhausted. She dreamed about the circus and the happy times she would  have.

Item_Response: One day a boy named Joe wanted to run away so he could be in the world famous Circus. He is in his room starting to pack up to run away. Five minutes later his mom yelled 'Time to eat'. 'Ok' mumbeld Joe. He ran down the stairs and asked his mom if he could eat in his room and she said 'Yes'. He got his food and ran upstairs and shut the door. He was planning to go out the window and hop on the train that is going to the Circus and it is leaving in five minutes. So he grabbed his suitcase and went out the window. He sprinted to the train staition. He ran on to the train and sat down.            He was scared when he sat down next to this guy with a gun in his pocket, so he moved by a girl with brown hair and blue eyes. The train started to go. The train was going 150 miles per hour. Before he new it they were at the Circus. Joe walked into the back of the Circus tent. He asked this guy if he could be in the Circus and the guy said'What skills do you have'. 'I can shoot out of a cannon' said Joe. 'You show me that' said the guy. They walked over by the cannon Joe asked the guy what his name is and he said 'Bob'.  Bob lets me get in the cannon.             Joe went in the cannon. Bob lit the rope BOOM goes the cannon. Joe lands safely in the big blue net. Bob says you are awsome. Want to be in the show tonight? Nevesly Joe says'Yes'. Than go get ready for tonight. The night came Joe is very nerves. He climbed into the cannon. The crowd counted 5, 4, 3, 2, 1, BOOM goes the cannon. Joe lands safly in the net . He runs to the back of the stage. He forgot something horribal. He needs to go back home. He went to the train staition.            He got on the train and sat by a nice guy named Aiden. The train stopped , Joe hopped off the train and ran home and hopped in bed. The morning came. Joe ran down stairs to eat breakfest. His family did not no he left. He never ever told enyone in the world. When he grew up he was world famos Cannon shooter. He died doing his dream.

Item_Response: Well, the two stories tell you a lot of information. But the first story tells you, what time you wake up and what time everything is. You wake up at 7:00 AM you wake up get dressed eat. 9:00 AM you go to school the school haves one room. 3:30 PM chores and practice feed you're pet and anything else. 6:30 PM time to eat, don't eat to much you have a show tonight. 10:30 PM the show is over and you wiped out you walk back to the trailer and see all the circus offices,concession stands, stables and trailers. In a couple days you will be somewhere else to perform. 12:00 AM you're in bed thinking about the end of you're tour. It will be nice to go back to you're home but you will miss performing. All of the practice you need for your next show will be tiring. You can't just go and join a circus out of no where and become an acrobat or trapeze artist. You need that skill in you, the right body type and you have to be able to be focused. You have to put you're heart into all of your work. It can't be sloppy. Did you know there are millions of people in the world who would like to be in a circus? Well there is! There is a bunch. I learned that being in a circus is a lot of work. ?       You need all of the makeup, practice, strength, flexibility, focus. You need a lot. You will need lots and lots of practice to become a performer for a circus. I learned a clown needs a lot of makeup and they need to be nice and they need to be funny. Circus Acrobats, need makeup, outfits, patience, focus, and most of all they need to put they're heart into their performance. A circus juggler needs skills too juggle all sorts of things. A tightrope walker needs balance practice focus and also put their best into it. The trainers have to train the animals right so they know what to do. The trainers need to make sure they train the animals so they don't get scared and run off and destroy the performance. The crew who makes all the tents,trailers,outfits , and all the other stuff they need to make sure they are in there place. and not some where they shouldn't.      Working in a circus is a ton of work as you see. You need the makeup, outfits, performance and the skills. When you're on a tour you really don't have a place to call 'home'.Sometimes you might think to you're self i miss my family, friends and house back home but on tour you're having fun. Working at a circus is long hours and weekends. When you work at a circus i bet its fun to perform and do all those fun stunts you do. I also learned that yeah the practices are long and hard but when all those people see how amazing the performance is they will wanna come and watch again, or maybe you will inspire them to try out working at a circus. The Performances are 10 whole shows a week yeah its a lot but its worth it. When you work at a circus you travel all over the world to like japan , florida , california, colorado and other states like that. well thats what i learned about the circus life.

Item_Response: My name is Amy,  I'm a circus performer and I have a very busy life, this is a normal day to me, when I get up in the morning, around 7:00 I go to the pie car and eat pancakes and bacon, then I get dressed and go to school at 9:00, after school ends I have very little time to play with my cat, Snicker doodle, and the clowns let me play with there equipment and then I'm off to practice for the coming nights circus.       After I practice, we go to the pie car once again for dinner, After dinner is when things settle down, I have time to play and have quality time with my family and then go to bed. Everyone seems to think that circus life is fun and high flying, well people who think that are wrong, circus life is really tough, for example, you have to have the right body,  talent and you have to be determined.       You cant go to the circus and expect to be a acrobat, lion tamer or stuff like that right off the bat, it takes lots of training to get to the point where you can actually perform in front of a live audience. If you want to be a good performer, you have to give up everything else and focus on the circus.        Although its a very tough and busy life for me and my family, it can also be very fun. When you are a performer you have the chance to travel the world, you meet lots of new people, and the people from the circus are like a family to me.        A downside to this life though, is that you don't really have a place to call your home. You are everywhere and your always thinking about the upcoming show. You work really hard for the circus and sometimes its not fun at all because you have to learn things that are hard for your body to do. You work a lot of long hours during the day and the weekends too.

Item_Response: To be in a circus is fun and hard. The hard part is that you don't keep many friendships because you're always on the road. The first thing you do to start your day is to head to the pie car for pancakes and bacon. You have to have a good breakfest so that's why there's a pie car. Next you have to go to school at 9:00 A.M. The one room schoolhouse travels with them. Like any other school they have computers, test, and report cards.       Many of the people in our school speak many different languages so that's why they come here. Some of the circus performers speak: French, Russian, and Italian. Next at 3:00 P.M. school ends and we have time for a quick break. We usually have fun. Then at 3:30 P.M. it's time for chores and practice. I have to feed, water, and groom the horses that we use in our horseback acts.       Dinnertime for my family is at 6:30 P.M. My family goes to the pie car to eat, but we can't eat a lot beacuse we're performing tonight. We do ten shows a week: one each weekday. 10:30 P.M. The show is over and everyone is wiped out. We walk back to our trailer and start sleeping for the next day.

Item_Response: My family and I are arriving at the circus. We smell the buttery popcorn,the melt-in-your-mouth cotton candy,the roaring of the tiger makes my sisters and I jump but we mustn`t stop now we have just arrived at the world famous Wringling bros. Circus! My family goes through admission and some contortionists walk by, one of them waved to me I blushed, and waved back. We dash to find the best seats we can, but wait what about snacks? My dad said to 'stay put' my sisters and I agreed and eagerly waited for the snacks to arrive and the show to start. My sisters and I were practcally out of our seats after another tiger roared. Finally the show was about to start, but where is dad?            We assumed that there was a long line for the snacks so we sat there and watched the circus acts. Then I saw someone I strangely recognized. Could it be? My Dad in the circus? No way this can`t be happening! This is crazy! My Dad had tricked us! I watched in amazement the stuff I never tought he would be able to do.            My dad went offstage and arrived with snacks. My dad was dressed the same way he was on stage. I stared in amzement and ate my melt-in-my-mouth cotton candy. My Family had the best experience at the circus. Don~t be fooled on how old your dad looks never underestimate your family and definitely not the strange ways of the circus.

Item_Response: The Hard Work of Being in the Circus       by   Bianca Platero                Being in the circus is hard work. Many people want to be in the circus, but they don't know how difficult it will be. Lots and   lots of people want to join the circus, but be careful it will be   a bumpy ride!             First of all, the circus is very complicated and tiring. The circus has a tight schedule. To be honest with you, I wanted to be in the circus and I found out that it is a hard job.If you have a special talent like dance or gymnastics, you will probably be good for the circus. The bad thing is that if your in the circus, you won't be able to see your family.              Second of all, I realized I never wanted to be in the circus because I knew I couldn't be with my family. Traveling everywhere is fun, but wouldn't you like to travel with you family? I would miss my family so much. The circus is fun, but hardworking.The circus is very amazing when you see it in person.                 Third of all, seeing the circus in person is very amazing. If you go and see it in person, I guarantee you will have a blast! There is cotton candy, popcorn, and clowns! I have never been to a circus before, but I  am going to soon because my friends have been to a circus before. They told me that is was very exciting and excellent.                   In conclusion, the circus is all the stuff I explained in the story. I would love to go to a circus show. The circus is very crazy and wacky, but also it is a lot of hard work.

Item_Response: One day, when I was walking to school, I saw a sign on the billboard way up high that said,'Are you ready for a circus in town?'I was surprised. I had never been to a circus. I was planning to go. But on the side of it, it said,  '$55.95 for each person or instead, make a poem about clowns, turn it in, and if you get an approval, you will win a free ticket to the circus.' There was no way I could get that money in time, I thought. Anyways, I only had $0.50 in my piggy bank. I made the right choice. I decided to make a poem.         During school, I was thinking about writing that poem. I wasn't paying attention to all the subjects my teacher had taught. As days and days passed on, I only had two days left until it was to late. At home, I finally picked up my pencil and started to write:                                                                                   Clowns                                                                         Victoria Kozuchi                                                Clowns are funny, Clowns can be colorful                                        Clowns can also come in various shapes and sizes                                   They make kids and babies laugh. They have big red noses.                             So what else can they do? They all have abilities just like me and you!               The next day, I turned it in. The manager liked it and approved it. I was so happy! I got two tickets for me and ....   I didn't have another person to go with. I thought to myself. Then, an answer came to me. On the following day when I was going to the grocery store, I found a girl who was staring at the same poster I saw. She seemed like she was from my school. I asked her if she was going to the circus. She said,'No, I don't have that kind of money.'I asked her if she wanted to come to the circus with me. She replyed,'Sure!'            It was the day of the circus. We didn't have front row seats, but we had second row seats. It was better than nothing. When the show started, the crowd was clapping and cheering. We seemed like we were both amazed at the juggling act and the circus acrobats. Soon horses came running up in the stage and they looked like bright, shiny unicorns. Lastly, a tightrope walker walked across the rope. It felt like he was going to fall, but he didn't. After the show, we met a clown. He made us both two heart shaped balloons. Caroline, the girl who came with me said,'Thank you very much.'and left. I'm sure I'll meet her at school.                                                                                                  THE END

Item_Response: It was finally my act. I was standing backstage, watching Miko, who was juggling, while Justice was flipping through never-ending rings of fire. My palms got really sweaty and I felt queasy as the crowd applauded and Miko and Justice bowed, because now was my act. Sandra stood beside me and recognized my fear. She grabbed my hand and we walked into the ring together. The lights shone on me so bright, I felt like I could pass out. The clapping sounded like mocking in my head. I couldn't tell what everyone was chanting, but it sounded like, 'You can't do it! You can't do it!' over and over again. Suddenly the bar slowly descended down, and I knew it was time. Sandra and I looked at each other, she smiled, I almost burst into tears. It was time.     We simutaneously grabbed the bar and sat upon it. It suddenly rised up and we were about 100 feet above the ground. My throat closed. No net, no pillows, nothing. If I fell, I would die. Blood everywhere. The lights dimmed, and a big bright one shone on us. Glowsticks on. Fear on maximum. This was it.      My legs wrapped around the bar, and I slowly, one by one, let my hands off. I hung upside down for about a minute, then grabbed the bar once again, but this time I was in a tear drop shape. My legs swung off the bar. 'Don't look down, don't look down!' I thought to myself. After several flips, the lights shut off, not quite pitch black. The audience clapped as the bar descended. Once it lowered down low enough that we could touch the ground, we let go and the bar dissapeared up into darkness. As the crowd kept applauding, I leaned over and whispered to Sandra, 'Good thing they didn't say encore!'

Item_Response: I remember the day my parents told me we were going to live on the circus. I was so exited. I was only 3 but I loved the circus. My parents used to be in the circus but then they got married and gave up the circus. But whenever the circus comes to town My parents were in it. So when they got the offer to go in the moving circus the accepted it. I was little so it was easy for me to learn how to tame a elephant or to walk on a rope 50 feet in air with no harness.               My first show was amazing. I'll admit that I was a little scared. OK maybe a lot but I LOVED IT. That day I decided that I was never going to leave the circus. Now that I'm 12 I'm having second thoughts.              I woke up and had my breakfast. Today was Friday the 13. Every Friday the 13 we have cupcakes for breakfast, lunch, and dinner. I chose a chocolate cupcake and started eating it.              I was tired of the circus. Moving every single day could get boring. As I sat in my favorite seat my mom joined me. This was my chance.            'Mom do you ever get bored of the circus?' I asked.             ' Sometimes. But I wait.' She replays.             ' Wait for what?'              ' I wait in till I get a great spot in the circus. I practice in till the manger notice how much better I got and gives me a new spot in the show. Maybe that's what you need.' She replays helping herself to a third cupcake.             ' How did' I say, my jaw hanging wide open.             ' How did I know? A mother knows everything.' And with that she leaves the pie car.             All day long I think about what my mom said. When I practice I try something new. Ins-tide of  juggling I ask one of the clowns if I can borrow their unicycles. They give it to me. I find a nice area with a soft landing. Then I start practicing.             Five weeks later when I'm on my unicycle the manger comes and talks me. He gives me a new place in the show.             ' The clowns say you're good. I hope they're right.'' And he walks away.                              That night at the show I lead the elephants out of their tents. On my unicycle. Blindfolded. I tame the elephants into doing tricks with nothing but my hand. It's nice not being able to see because sometimes the crowd mess you up. When I'm down with my act the crowd goes wild.             That night I don't feel like I hate the circus. I love it even more than ever. I realized that the circus isn't about tricks or clowns. It's about trying new things and loving it. For you it might be sports or a new food. For me it's the circus. Like my mom said you have to wait.

Item_Response: MY FIRST DAY AT THE CIRCUS                         It was my first day working at the circus and I was so excited! First my mom woke me up. Then I ate and we left for the circus.When we got there I bid farewell and told her to come to the show on Saturday.As she left I met a silly clown named Aldo and we quickly became friends.               While we were talking the ringmaster called for everyone to gather round and meet our newest    (drum roll please) PEANUT BOY!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! After he said that, he called me up.As I went up everyone cheered and clapped for me. Then he asked who would like to show me around and help me with any questions. Immediately Aldo raised his hand. The ringmaster said 'How about you Aldo.' Aldo came over and said  ' Come on, Let's go!'                 Day by day Aldo helped me around and introduced me to people.By the Saturday I had made many more friends.That night was the show tons and tons of people were there.Finally the acts began. First , all the clowns came out and did funny things like throwing pies at each other.But I didn't see parts because like everyone wanted peanuts. When I spotted Aldo he looked like he was having a good time.Then I heard a Familiar voice saying ' Peanut boy, over here!'I turned around and guess who I saw, MY MOM! I went over to her and gave her a hug and said 'I missed you' I told about my week  and Aldo. She said 'Sounds like fun'.                    When the show was over I Introduced my mom to Aldo. Then asked if I'm going to stay in the circus. I said 'Even though I had so much fun, I think I want to be with my family'.He said 'Okay'.                    Right as we were about to leave Aldo came after me with a big box. I asked him what it was he said it was a gift for me. I opened it and found a clown makeup kit and a bag of the mysterious marshmallow circus peanuts. I said goodbye and thanks and left. I told my mom ' That  was one of the funnest weeks EVER!'                :)

Item_Response: Life of the Circus                Gritting and daring I looked down hoping this moment would never come. I was 100 feet up in the cold night air preparing for what was about to happen. I'm the clown in Rockie Top  Circus. 'I can't believe that my boss wants me to jump onto  a elephant'! I screamed to myself. Then the announcer announced 'ladies and gentlemen, boys and girls of all ages, please welcome Tairan Smith' he said in a deep voice.             'Aaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaahhhhhhh SLAP!' as I belly flopped onto the rock hard back of the elephant. The show was started! After the show, I was wiped out. We eat at a pie car. ' I'm sick of this job..............I got it! TomorrowI'll run away!            It was cold that morning but I was ready. I set off at 2:15 to start a new life. I was in Idaho and I traveled on foot all the way to California. It took me 4 years to get there. When I got there I saw a poster that said' Rockie Top Circus going out of business IN NEED OF CLOWN'. I thought about all of my friends and sat there for a long time. Finally I decided that there is no place like home.                           Just the Facts       pie car: eating place   unicycles: one wheeled bicycle   groom: clean   matinee: afternoon show   wiped out:tired

Item_Response: Hi my name is Bella Castini and I am going to tell you what it is like to be in the circus. For example what I have to do in the morning, in the afternoon, and at night. After you read this I hope you will won't to see one of our shows some day.                       First, I I am very busy in the morning. At 7:00 A.M. I get dressed and go out to the pie car for breakfast. We have pancakes and bacon. It is delicious. After I eat we have to set up tents and lights for tonights show. 9:00 A.M. is schooltime. Then I walk to the schoolhouse. The schoolhouse is the same as every school they have computers, tests, and report cards. A lot of the people in the circus are from all around the world ,so many of my classmates speak different languages. When we travel around the world thats when we do geography lessons.                           Next, I have to do tons of jobs in the afternoon to get ready for the show tonight. At 3:00 P.M. school is out. After school I played with the clowns unicycles and juggling balss. It was really fun. 3:30 P.M. is chore time, so I start with the horses. I have to feed, water, and groom the horses. Then I have to start my act. I am leaping off a trampoline and landing on the horse's back. It takes a lot of balance and concentraction. Other kids practice juggling and acrobatics. The trainers are working with baby leopards, elephants,lions, and chimpanzees.                               Last, the end of the night is the best part. At 6:30 P.M. we go to the pie car to eat dinner. Circus performers do not eat much befor the show. The circus does ten shows a week, plus a manitee ( a afternoon show) on Wedensday, two on Saturday, and two on Sunday. The show was really fun and everybody enjoyed it. I did my act and did it. It felt amazing! The show was over and everbody is so tired. We walk back to the trailor. In bed I thought when I growup will I still be in the circus?                                   In Conclusion, I hope I will see you some day performing in the circus. The circus is worth being hard because at the end of the night you are very happy that you are in the circus having fun with friends and family.

Item_Response: The circus is all sorts of fun.  You can play games, get your pictures taken, and much more.  If you ask me the circus is really cool.  The bad thing about being in the circus is that you never get to call a place home.  Also you never get to see your family unless they are in the circus with you.                                                             Life in the circus is hard work if you ask me.  I get to see many people which is fun though.  I get to be an acrobat with my parents.  People always ask me for my autograph.  It is amazing to have people ask you for your autograph because it means people really enjoy you.  I love all my fans, but i don't get to autograph everyone oft them because some times their parents think it's late and then they have to leave.  Other people leave because they don't want to wait in the really long lines.  That is what it is like to have all the fans go crazy for you.                                                                                                The disadvantage of being in the circus is that you never really have a place to call home.  I have a home in Mighigan but it is not very big compared to what i am used to.  It only has five bedrooms.  I have three and my parents have two.  One of my bedrooms is used for my bed and clothes from when i was little and not in the circus.  One of them is used for my circus awards.  I put them in there when we do come home but i usally don't have that much.  The other room is used for my circus clothes that don't fit me anymore.                                                                                                 The hard work I put into the circus is fantastic is what all my fans say.  I do miss my grandma and grandpa and all my other family alot though.  When i have shows in Mighigan they will come and see me.  That's why I love it when we have shows in Mighigan.  Also when we have shows in Virginia my aunt ans uncle come and watch because that is where they live.                                                                                                                                  When we are on our break i play with lego's.  One time I built a mansion because my fans know that i locve lego's and they bring me a bunch.  One time a little girl brought me ten boxes of different lego's.  When i get double of something besides lego's I donate them to a charity in Michigan.  When I do performances at local charities when I am in one state the kids go crazy.  Sometimes I got to an orphanage when I am close to one a do gymnastics in the air on a trampoline.                                                                      I have to live in a trailor which stinks.  The good thing is that they are huge.  I have my own bedroom with a queen size bed in it.  I don't have a closet though.  My parents get the closet.  I don't think that is very fare because I have more clothes then they do.                                                             In conclusion the circus life is pretty cool.  There are some ups.  There are also some downs.  An up is that it is really fun getting to go from state to state.  The down is that you barely ever get to see your family.  Now you know what it is like being in the circus.

Item_Response: For those who say or think that being a circus performer is fun and easy, I have one thing to say to you people, and that is YOU ARE WRONG! The circus life is actually pretty hard. There are many things that you are possibly unaware of in the circus business. Downsides are very common and so are upsides, but there can be more of either to different people though.             There are quite a few hardships for circus performers but I'm only going to tell you some of them. First off one of my most deal-able hardships is how tiring the show is. Our circus does 14 shows a week, one morning show and afternoon show every day! Another hardship is that I have to do almost all the cleaning and chores! But the worst part is I am the animal trainer, so I have to clean up after, groom, take care of, bath, and feed the animals! One of the most hardest hardships is that I cannot visit my family because of my very busy schedule and I cannot visit my friends either! So being a circus performer has a lot of downsides.             Circus performing isn't all bad though. It has its own upsides! Such as, getting to travel the world! I get to see many things around the world! Once I saw the Eiffel Tower, The Statue Of Liberty, and The White House! You also get to see the audience compliment you and see them get 'transported to another world'! I also get to learn new things and tricks as I rehearse and practice. And I do love seeing the children's happy faces once they go to our circus! We also get to eat food that is paid for by the circus. Even with many downsides the circus life is still pretty good!             Another thing I forgot to mention was the profits! I am also the 'treasurer' of the circus. I'm not even sure if circuses are even supposed to have one, but anyways I'm in charge of the profits. And that is hard work! I have to pay everyone depending on how many people paid and gave feedback. I also have to use the money and my FREE time to buy new equipment if we want new equipment or if we need to replace broken equipment. I also have to pay for accidents, candy, one-time-use kind of things, and souvenirs, but I don't have to pay the bills!   That's the owner's problem.             So in the end, circus life to me is exhausting, but it is still a pretty good life. So if I were to recommend being a circus performer I would say it depends on if you are a good acrobatic, but this job does pay a lot!

Item_Response: Being in the circus                Hey have you ever heard thata circus life is crazy befor? Because its not always like that.        Hi my name is Micaela lets go on a circus adventrue.            I come for a family of clowns but I'm not a clown in the circus I'm a circus acrobat.        To be a circus acrobat you need to have some skills in dance, gymnastics, and cheer.              At the end of a show its usally 10:00 or 12:00 p.m. I usally dont goo to bed till 2:30 a.m because I'm on my moms tricycle.         But never my dads because if he found out I would be in so much troble that I might not be able to sit down for a week.              So I wake up go to the pie foe eggs and toast. Yummmmmmm!           Oh yea I forgot to tell you what that was. A pie is where clowns, acrobats, jugglers, tightrope walkers have breakefeast and dinner.              My typical day is always busy. Heres my typical day:   7:00 a.m I wake up get dress and then go to the pie for eggs and bacon.           While I eat the crew  is seating up the tents and lights.   9:00 a.m I go to this little room where a teacher teaches me social studies, math, science, and ela.   2:00 p.m schools over and I head to the tent to start practicing.   3:00 p.m I go to the pie for a snake and a break.   3:00 p.m It's dinner time I go to the pie for chicken and mash patatoes.   4:30-6:30 p.m I practice over and over again.   7:00 p.m I go to the pie for a snake and then a little while after the show starts.   12:00 a.m the show ends and I head to our mobile car to get some sleep.             Well thats all the time I have. I have a show to attend to. Maybe I will see you guys again bye.

Item_Response: Hi, my name is Chloe. I've been living in the circus for three years. I'm a lion trainer so I  most likely have the hardest job. Here's a sneak peek on how life in the circus really is.          Living in the circus isn't always fun and games it takes hard work and lots of practice to be in the circus. You also still have to go to school so you have to study for test's and other things on top of practicing for the circus. Right after practice you have to eat dinner and go to bed you get lucky if you have time to play.           Living in the circus is also dangerous you have to be very careful at all times. If you have to deal with animals like me then you have to be very careful. Especially if your dealing with lions or bears like me.         The good side about living in the circus is that you get to do what you love and you're always around you're friends and people who care about you. You can play with the animals which is super fun.         That's how life really is in the circus dangerous, hard work, but it's worth it.

Item_Response: The Circus Show   Hi my name is Alex and I'm in the circus. I do acrobatics on horses. My father just taught me a new trick last night, but he said he taught it to me late and I have a show tonight. I'm really scared to do that trick. The trick is I have to do a back flip off a trampoline onto a horse. Although I love that red striped tent, I really don't want to break a bone in it.       It's a good thing my act is last in the show, so I can practice before I go on. The show starts at three so I have only two hours to practice.       It has been an hour and forty-five minutes I still cant do my trick. We have to get ready for the show, I'm so scared. I put on my costume. I'm watching everyone to their trick perfectly and I cant practice because I'm to nervous. It's my turn. I go out there, I get my stance ready. I say to myself I have to try. I go for it. I land it! I'm so happy. My dad said that he would take us out for ice cream later, but I doubt it.

Item_Response: Hello, my name is Maggie Alberts. In the circus I am in charge of  taking care of the animals. It's a very difficult job if you ask me. My parents own the circus and they are the leading acrobats. They said that when I turn 13 in two months i get to become an acrobat as well.            There are many responsibility to make our circus one of the top circuses in California. We always have to make sure that the tents,flyers,and other things are ready for the big opening night! My uncle Joe also is in our circus as well, he walks on the tightrope and is very good at it.            Circus life is very difficult if you already didn't know that. We get home schooled on the way because we are on the road a lot while we travel the world. We also don't get so much time to rest we get up at about 7:30 in the morning, have breakfast, my favorite is when my mom makes homemade pancakes, to about 8:00 at night and then we eat dinner. After dinner, we have to perform and that geos until about 10:15 usually.             I guess the circus life is in my jeans, and I'm very proud that it is. Circus life may be diffacult, but it always works out in the end because I have fun and that's all that matters.

Item_Response: I was practicing my acrobatics when I was called to the back of the circus.  Apparently everybody else was too.  Our boss told us that instead of performing at a regular show, we would be competing with other circuses.  The first place circus would be known all over the world.  Us people of Big Top Circus were excited.  Our boss also said that only one person would be annonced the best out of all the circuses.  They would be famous all over the world too.  Now we were really excited.  I wasn't really sure if I would get to be the best.  I knew my friend, Drew, should get it.  She was the best trapeze artist out of the whole circus.  The competition was on Saturday, August 21.  That was only a week from today.  I really needed to practice my acrobatics.         It was Wednesday, August 18.  Only two days left to practice.  I almost broke my ankle trying to land back down after doing my last acrobatic practice yesterday.  It was a good thing I didn't.  Then I wouldn't be able to participate in the competition.  I was doing a really cool routine high in the air with Drew.  I would spin and turn and twirl on a rope and then Drew would come down on her trapeze and get me.  I would fly in the air with Drew, let go of her and do a backflip, and then land clean on my feet.  It was a hard routine.         It was now the day of the competition.  I couldn't wait.  Our circus would be judged last.  We had to perform exellent to impress the judges.  It was finally for our circus to go on.  Drew's and I routine would be going last. We really had to impress the judges.  Maybe Drew would get to be the best performer.  If it wasn't me, it should be her.  It was now our turn.  I was nervous and so was Drew.  She was actually shaking.  I walked over to my rope and started spinning and turning.  Drew then came down on her trapeze and I grabbed her legs and flew with her.  Then I let go of her legs, did a backflip, and landed clean on my feet.          I hoped the routine looked great.  It was time to give out the awards.  So far we haven't been called and they were now going to announce who got first place....'And the circus who got first place is..... BIG TOP CIRCUS!'  I was so surprised I started crying a little bit.  Now they were going to announce the best performer.  'And the best performer is....ZOIE BAEZA!'  Now I really started crying.  I was now so shocked ans surprised that I got it.  I would be famous all around the world even if I died right now.  A week later we were already traveling all aroung the world and many people wanted my autograph at the same time.  The Big Top Circus was now a world wide circus, and so was I.

Item_Response: Today is your first day at the circus. You get the job to be an acrobat. You have to be the one to hang on the bars and ropes. You are very afraid of hights, but you have to do it anyway. So you climb up on the ladder and get on the rope. After a few minutes people start to notice you are hanging on a rope. A few people walk by and clap for you and tell you to do a trick. You don't know what to do so you put one foot on the rope and the other in the air. Then you do the same thing with your arms. You balance for about 8 minutes with one foot and one arm in the air and one foot and arm on the rope. People clap and tell you to come back tomorrow. After that day was over you walk home and go to bed after a long day of hard work.   The next day you go to the circus to be an acrobat, but then your boss says you ar going to be a juggler instead. he told me he wanted me to learn to do everything so then I could do different things each day. So before people started showing up I practiced. I didn't notice for a few minutes but out of the corner of my eye two people were watching me practice. They started telling me to juggle bananas, so they gave me some and told me to try. I tried and I was actually really good at it. i could also do jumping jacks while I juggled.       After a couple of days I wsa getting tired of doing acrobat and juggling so I asked if I could try tightrope walking. My boss said of course. So i got up on the tightropoe and tried balancing. I could balance pretty well so i tried a trick. I did a flip and a back flip. People were so amazed. everyone was smiling and it made me smile.       The two days after it was Saturday. It was my day off. I spent the whole day practicing. I loved being at the circus. I couldn't wait till Monday so I made my own circus at my house. I made myself look like a clown. I juggled, did acrobats, and did tightrope walking.

Item_Response: A day at the circus                            The day had come, I was so exited, I jumped out of bed got my cloths on and ran down stairs. I ate my cereal and got in the car. Sadly my parents were not in the car. I ran inside and dragged them into the car. We were on our way to the circus. I was so exited all I said to my parents was, 'are we there yet' about one thousand times. I finally got bored of saying that, so I just sat there quietly.                             Then in the horizon I saw a tent, at first I thought it was just some campers but as I got closer and closer I realized that we were finally here. I was so exited that I couldn't speak. we found a parking spot as quickly as we could. I jumped out of the car and ran inside. It was every thing I dreamed it would be but better. On one side there was the snack shop and on the other there were performers giving out signatures. i ran in the doors there they were our own reserved seats. Once I sat down the lights turned off.                              A small man came out he said,' welcome to the Circus Ole, we hope you have the best night of your lives.' As soon as he finished He turned taller and taller. Then something came out of the sky it was a mini plane, it was awesome. Then acrobats came fling out then landed on a trampoline were they started doing all of these cool moves. Out of no were these performers swinging on these glow in the dark ropes. The strangest thing happened, a elephant was riding on rollerskates.                              Next balloons started falling out of the sky and then got real quite. A mime was stacking chairs in an odd way then I couldn't believe it, he started climbing them. I new he was going to fall at the very top he started staking more and more, he was insane. At the very top he jumped! He was going to die but when he touched the ground it was water, it was impossible.                               Then he started raising from the water and started flying! I never wanted to leave because there was more they started swinging on bars and doing flip. it was the best night of my entirer life. I hope I get to do this agian.

Item_Response: When I was gowing up all of my family was in the circus. My parents were seriously in jured by falling off a platform. I never did want them to go back. They said they had too and they were too weird to get a job somewhere else. I did not want to follow in their steps.   Since I was known as their kid I guess everyone thought that I had to be in. Nope all of those people were wrong I hate the circus. Even though I would be in a store and everyone would rush to me and say ypur the famous kid Mr. Johnson! I told them i was always someone else so they wouldn't bother me.   I sat in the croud watching my parents flipping all over the place and dancing and twirling. I thought it was dumb. So I owned a company named Johnsons Rugs. After the show I told them what I owned and they were so disapointed but the circus wasn't for me.

Item_Response: Hi, i'm Gabby. People call me Gabby the Great. Today, i want to run away from home. I saw a notice in the news paper that said 'Help Wanted, Come if You're Talented'. I am going to miss my family and my best friend Sophie. But when i'm done in the circus i will have a giant mansion and i will invite my parents to live with me. Sophie will have a sleep over with me every night. I would be famous! But first, i need to get in the circus. I already left a note for my family saying that i will be back soon.        I was waiting at the bus station when i saw a little boy come up to me. I asked him if he was lost, but he shook his head. He said that he was going to the circus tryouts. Then, i asked him where his parents were. He looked down at his feet sadly and told me that he didn't have any. I wasn' t just going to leave him there to starve to death, so i brought him with me to the journey.               We both didn't end up getting in the circus. But fortunately, my parents adopted the litte boy and named him Antonio. People call him Tony the Terrific.  That how i got my little brother.                                                                THE END!
